msgid "Day 1: Creation"
msgstr "Hari 1: Penciptaan"

msgid ""
"Genesis 1:1-25 (ESV)\n"
"In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth. The earth was "
"without form and void, and darkness was over the face of the deep. And the "
"Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters. And God said, \"Let "
"there be light,\" and there was light. And God saw that the light was good. "
"And God separated the light from the darkness. God called the light Day, and "
"the darkness he called Night. And there was evening and there was morning, "
"the first day. And God said, \"Let there be an expanse in the midst of the "
"waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters.\" And God made the "
"expanse and separated the waters that were under the expanse from the waters "
"that were above the expanse. And it was so. And God called the expanse "
"Heaven. And there was evening and there was morning, the second day. And God "
"said, \"Let the waters under the heavens be gathered together into one "
"place, and let the dry land appear.\" And it was so. God called the dry land "
"Earth, and the waters that were gathered together he called Seas. And God "
"saw that it was good. And God said, \"Let the earth sprout vegetation, "
"plants yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, "
"each according to its kind, on the earth.\" And it was so. The earth brought "
"forth vegetation, plants yielding seed according to their own kinds, and "
"trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind. And "
"God saw that it was good. And there was evening and there was morning, the "
"third day. And God said, \"Let there be lights in the expanse of the heavens "
"to separate the day from the night. And let them be for signs and for "
"seasons, and for days and years, and let them be lights in the expanse of "
"the heavens to give light upon the earth.\" And it was so. And God made the "
"two great lights—the greater light to rule the day and the lesser light to "
"rule the night—and the stars. And God set them in the expanse of the heavens "
"to give light on the earth, to rule over the day and over the night, and to "
"separate the light from the darkness. And God saw that it was good. And "
"there was evening and there was morning, the fourth day. And God said, \"Let "
"the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures, and let birds fly above "
"the earth across the expanse of the heavens.\" So God created the great sea "
"creatures and every living creature that moves, with which the waters swarm, "
"according to their kinds, and every winged bird according to its kind. And "
"God saw that it was good. And God blessed them, saying, \"Be fruitful and "
"multiply and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the "
"earth.\" And there was evening and there was morning, the fifth day. And God "
"said, \"Let the earth bring forth living creatures according to their kinds—"
"livestock and creeping things and beasts of the earth according to their "
"kinds.\" And it was so. And God made the beasts of the earth according to "
"their kinds and the livestock according to their kinds, and everything that "
"creeps on the ground according to its kind. And God saw that it was good."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God is a powerful, joyful Creator who brings order from chaos, speaks with "
"authority, reveals Himself to be known, and multiplies His goodness through "
"His creation and His people.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to see and celebrate God's creativity, "
"goodness, and the order He brings into the world and into our lives.\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up faithful partners in His mission among this "
"people, reflecting his character and making his story known to the nations."
msgstr ""
"Allah adalah Pencipta yang berkuasa dan penuh sukacita, yang membawa "
"ketertiban dari kekacauan, berbicara dengan otoritas, memperkenalkan diri-"
"Nya agar dikenal, dan memperbanyak kebaikan-Nya melalui ciptaan-Nya dan umat-"
"Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini dapat melihat dan merayakan "
"kreativitas Allah, kebaikan-Nya, dan ketertiban yang Ia bawa ke dunia dan ke "
"dalam hidup kita.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat mitra-mitra yang setia dalam misi-Nya di "
"tengah umat ini, mencerminkan karakter-Nya dan memperkenalkan kisah-Nya "
"kepada bangsa-bangsa."

msgid ""
"Humanity is invited into God's generous, relational design—not as the center "
"of the story, but as participants who receive His abundance, reflect His "
"community, and live within the order He lovingly created.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God to teach people in this place to remember that we are not the "
"main characters, but grateful participants in God's greater story.\n"
"- Ask God to grow hearts among this people to live out of the generosity He "
"has shown—sharing, multiplying, and stewarding what He entrusts to us."
msgstr ""
"Manusia diundang untuk menjadi bagian dari rancangan Allah yang penuh kasih "
"dan relasional—bukan sebagai pusat cerita, tetapi sebagai peserta yang "
"menerima kelimpahan-Nya, mencerminkan komunitas-Nya, dan hidup dalam tatanan "
"yang dengan penuh kasih Ia ciptakan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengajarkan orang-orang di tempat ini untuk mengingat "
"bahwa kita bukanlah tokoh utama, tetapi peserta yang bersyukur dalam kisah "
"besar Allah.\n"
"- Mintalah kepada Allah untuk menumbuhkan hati di antara orang-orang ini "
"agar hidup sesuai dengan kemurahan hati yang telah Ia tunjukkan—berbagi, "
"memperbanyak, dan mengelola apa yang Ia percayakan kepada kita."

msgid ""
"This story reveals that God only creates good. He doesn't create evil, "
"contrary to Islamic doctrine. According to Islamic teaching, Satan was "
"originally a jinn, created by God from smokeless fire. Islam also teaches "
"that God is unknowable, but here we see Him revealing Himself, giving us "
"important information to know about Him. This difference in understanding "
"impacts how Muslims respond to Biblical accounts of nature.\n"
"\n"
"Recovering from metastatic cancer and having finished radiation, Hanen longs "
"to hope in God's power to heal and save. Listening to the story of Creation "
"stirred her heart to praise God's strength. Just a few days later, however, "
"her initial openness gave way to resistance when she adamantly declared that "
"healing can only come through reading the Quran and that she doesn't need to "
"read God's Holy Word from the Torah (Old Testament) and Injil (New "
"Testament).\n"
"\n"
"Pray for God to stir a hunger for reading God's Word from the Bible and for "
"fear to be replaced with faith."
msgstr ""
"Cerita ini mengungkapkan bahwa Allah hanya menciptakan kebaikan. Dia tidak "
"menciptakan kejahatan, bertentangan dengan ajaran Islam. Menurut ajaran "
"Islam, Setan awalnya adalah jin, diciptakan oleh Allah dari api tanpa asap. "
"Islam juga mengajarkan bahwa Allah tidak dapat diketahui, tetapi di sini "
"kita melihat-Nya mengungkapkan diri-Nya, memberikan informasi penting "
"tentang-Nya. Perbedaan pemahaman ini mempengaruhi cara Muslim merespons "
"kisah-kisah Alkitab tentang alam.\n"
"\n"
"Setelah pulih dari kanker metastasis dan menyelesaikan terapi radiasi, Hanen "
"merindukan harapan akan kuasa Allah untuk menyembuhkan dan menyelamatkan. "
"Mendengar kisah Penciptaan menggerakkan hatinya untuk memuji kekuatan Allah. "
"Namun, beberapa hari kemudian, keterbukaannya awalnya berubah menjadi "
"penolakan ketika ia dengan tegas menyatakan bahwa penyembuhan hanya dapat "
"datang melalui membaca Al-Quran dan bahwa ia tidak perlu membaca Firman "
"Allah yang suci dari Taurat (Perjanjian Lama) dan Injil (Perjanjian Baru).\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar Allah membangkitkan kerinduan untuk membaca Firman-Nya dari "
"Alkitab dan agar ketakutan digantikan dengan iman."

msgid ""
"Most Muslims believe God created the world, though they don't regard the "
"Bible's account as accurate.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Christians trying to share Good News with Muslims to confidently "
"invite Muslims to hear this story and to discuss it with others.\n"
"- Pray that a curiosity would be stirred to want to continue to read more "
"stories."
msgstr ""
"Sebagian besar umat Islam percaya bahwa Allah menciptakan dunia, meskipun "
"mereka tidak menganggap kisah Alkitab sebagai yang akurat.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Kristen yang berusaha membagikan Kabar Baik kepada "
"umat Islam dapat dengan percaya diri mengundang umat Islam untuk "
"mendengarkan kisah ini dan mendiskusikannya dengan orang lain.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar rasa ingin tahu terpicu untuk terus membaca lebih banyak "
"kisah."

msgid ""
"Colossians 1:15-22\n"
"Jesus, you are the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of all "
"creation. By you, all things were created in heaven and on earth, visible "
"and invisible, whether thrones or dominions or rulers or authorities. All "
"things were created through you and for you, you are before all things, and "
"in you all things hold together.\n"
"\n"
"We declare, Jesus, that you are the head of the body, the church. You are "
"the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, in everything you are "
"preeminent. For in you, Jesus, all the fullness of God was pleased to dwell "
"and through you, to reconcile to yourself all things, whether on earth or in "
"heaven, making peace by the blood of your cross.\n"
"\n"
"We pray for Muslims in this area who are currently alienated and hostile in "
"mind, doing evil deeds. We pray that they would accept and believe and be "
"reconciled through Christ's body of flesh by His death, and that they would "
"be presented to you as holy and blameless and above reproach before you."
msgstr ""
"Kolose 1:15-22\n"
"Yesus, Engkau adalah gambaran Allah yang tidak kelihatan, Anak sulung segala "
"ciptaan. Melalui Engkau, segala sesuatu diciptakan di surga dan di bumi, "
"yang kelihatan dan yang tidak kelihatan, baik takhta, kerajaan, pemerintah, "
"maupun kuasa. Segala sesuatu diciptakan melalui Engkau dan untuk Engkau; "
"Engkau ada sebelum segala sesuatu, dan dalam Engkau segala sesuatu tetap "
"utuh.\n"
"\n"
"Kami menyatakan, Yesus, bahwa Engkau adalah kepala tubuh, yaitu gereja. "
"Engkau adalah permulaan, yang sulung dari antara orang mati, dalam segala "
"hal Engkau adalah yang utama. Sebab di dalam Engkau, Yesus, seluruh "
"kepenuhan Allah berkenan untuk diam, dan melalui Engkau, Ia berkenan untuk "
"mendamaikan segala sesuatu kepada diri-Nya, baik di bumi maupun di surga, "
"dengan darah salib-Mu.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa untuk umat Muslim di daerah ini yang saat ini terasing dan "
"bermusuhan dalam pikiran, melakukan perbuatan jahat. Kami berdoa agar mereka "
"menerima dan percaya, dan diperdamaikan melalui tubuh daging Kristus oleh "
"kematian-Nya, dan agar mereka dipersembahkan kepada-Mu sebagai orang-orang "
"yang kudus, tak bercela, dan tak tercela di hadapan-Mu."

msgid "Day 2: Creation of Humans"
msgstr "Hari ke-2: Penciptaan Manusia"

msgid ""
"Genesis 1:26-27 (ESV)\n"
"Then God said, \"Let us make man in our image, after our likeness. And let "
"them have dominion over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the "
"heavens and over the livestock and over all the earth and over every "
"creeping thing that creeps on the earth.\" So God created man in his own "
"image, in the image of God he created him; male and female he created them.\n"
"\n"
"Genesis 2:15-25 (ESV)\n"
"The LORD God took the man and put him in the garden of Eden to work it and "
"keep it. And the LORD God commanded the man, saying, \"You may surely eat of "
"every tree of the garden, but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil "
"you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat of it you shall surely die.\" "
"Then the LORD God said, \"It is not good that the man should be alone; I "
"will make him a helper fit for him.\" Now out of the ground the LORD God had "
"formed every beast of the field and every bird of the heavens and brought "
"them to the man to see what he would call them. And whatever the man called "
"every living creature, that was its name. The man gave names to all "
"livestock and to the birds of the heavens and to every beast of the field. "
"But for Adam there was not found a helper fit for him. So the LORD God "
"caused a deep sleep to fall upon the man, and while he slept took one of his "
"ribs and closed up its place with flesh. And the rib that the LORD God had "
"taken from the man he made into a woman and brought her to the man. Then the "
"man said, \"This at last is bone of my bones and flesh of my flesh; she "
"shall be called Woman, because she was taken out of Man.\" Therefore a man "
"shall leave his father and his mother and hold fast to his wife, and they "
"shall become one flesh. And the man and his wife were both naked and were "
"not ashamed."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"A relational, purposeful Creator, God intentionally fashioned humanity "
"through a deliberately ordered process, surrounding us with heavenly "
"community and provision so we are never left alone.\n"
"\n"
"- God made us in His image. Pray for the people of this land not only to "
"recognize that they bear His image, but that it would also transform the way "
"they view others.\n"
"- As they ponder the reality that their friends, family, neighbors, and "
"enemies are all created in God's image, may they more rightly esteem them."
msgstr ""
"Seorang Pencipta yang relasional dan bermakna, Allah secara sengaja "
"membentuk umat manusia melalui proses yang teratur dengan sengaja, "
"mengelilingi kita dengan komunitas surgawi dan pemeliharaan-Nya sehingga "
"kita tidak pernah ditinggalkan sendirian.\n"
"\n"
"- Allah menciptakan kita menurut gambar-Nya. Berdoalah bagi penduduk negeri "
"ini agar tidak hanya menyadari bahwa mereka membawa gambar-Nya, tetapi juga "
"agar hal itu mengubah cara mereka memandang orang lain.\n"
"- Saat mereka merenungkan kenyataan bahwa teman, keluarga, tetangga, dan "
"musuh mereka semua diciptakan menurut gambar Allah, semoga mereka lebih "
"menghargai mereka dengan benar."

msgid ""
"Made as image bearers from the dust of the earth and breathed upon, humanity "
"is fundamentally communal. God created complementary male and female for "
"companionship, multiplication, and stewardship of creation.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for those among this people who feel alone, misunderstood, and "
"isolated. May the truth that he created us for relationship with him and "
"others bring hope and stir a desire to understand more about how a personal "
"relationship is possible with the God who created the heavens and earth."
msgstr ""
"Diciptakan sebagai pencerminan gambar Allah dari debu bumi dan ditiupkan "
"nafas-Nya, manusia pada dasarnya bersifat komunal. Allah menciptakan laki-"
"laki dan perempuan yang saling melengkapi untuk persahabatan, "
"perkembangbiakan, dan penguasaan atas ciptaan-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi mereka di antara umat ini yang merasa sendirian, tidak "
"dipahami, dan terisolasi. Semoga kebenaran bahwa Allah menciptakan kita "
"untuk hubungan dengan-Nya dan sesama membawa harapan dan membangkitkan "
"keinginan untuk memahami lebih lanjut tentang bagaimana hubungan pribadi "
"dengan Allah yang menciptakan langit dan bumi itu mungkin."

msgid ""
"This story shows God's original design for marriage and community–truths "
"that can transform Muslim families.\n"
"\n"
"Ahmed complained about his wife. She didn't clean the house the way she "
"should. She didn't take care of her appearance the way she should. His "
"teenage children stressed him out. He has had a girlfriend on the side for "
"years who he traveled to spend the weekend with. Ultimately, because he "
"didn't value God's design for marriage and whole life commitment, he "
"divorced his wife and married the other woman.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this land who are in disappointing marriages. Pray for "
"opportunities to read the story of Adam and Eve and understand God's "
"original design for marriage.\n"
"- Pray that transformation would happen in their families as they trust "
"God's word, and that he would bring beauty into these broken marriages for "
"his glory."
msgstr ""
"Cerita ini menggambarkan rancangan asli Allah untuk pernikahan dan komunitas—"
"kebenaran yang dapat mengubah keluarga Muslim.  \n"
"\n"
"Ahmed mengeluh tentang istrinya. Dia tidak membersihkan rumah seperti "
"seharusnya. Dia tidak merawat penampilannya seperti seharusnya. Anak-anak "
"remajanya membuatnya stres. Dia telah memiliki pacar selingkuh selama "
"bertahun-tahun yang dia kunjungi untuk menghabiskan akhir pekan bersama. "
"Akhirnya, karena dia tidak menghargai rancangan Allah untuk pernikahan dan "
"komitmen seumur hidup, dia menceraikan istrinya dan menikahi wanita lain.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk umat Muslim di negeri ini yang berada dalam pernikahan "
"yang mengecewakan. Berdoalah agar mereka memiliki kesempatan untuk membaca "
"kisah Adam dan Hawa dan memahami rancangan Allah yang asli untuk "
"pernikahan.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar transformasi terjadi dalam keluarga mereka saat mereka "
"mempercayai firman Allah, dan agar Dia membawa keindahan ke dalam pernikahan "
"yang hancur ini untuk kemuliaan-Nya."

msgid ""
"This story emphasizes that a believer's place of belonging is in God's "
"eternal family -- not cut off, separated, and in isolation.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Christians working in this culture to clearly communicate this "
"concept to all who are cut off from their earthly families because of their "
"decision to follow Jesus.\n"
"- Pray that the truth that God puts the lonely in families would comfort "
"them and remind them that they are not alone."
msgstr ""
"Cerita ini menekankan bahwa tempat seorang percaya berada adalah dalam "
"keluarga abadi Allah — tidak terputus, terpisah, dan terisolasi.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi orang-orang Kristen yang bekerja dalam budaya ini agar "
"dapat menyampaikan konsep ini dengan jelas kepada semua orang yang terputus "
"dari keluarga duniawi mereka karena keputusan mereka untuk mengikuti Yesus.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kebenaran bahwa Allah menempatkan orang-orang yang "
"sendirian dalam keluarga dapat menghibur mereka dan mengingatkan mereka "
"bahwa mereka tidak sendirian."

msgid ""
"The story in Genesis 2:24 continues in Ephesians 5. Father, we pray for "
"marriages among this people group to be transformed by the teachings of "
"Jesus. We pray that men would love their wives the way that Christ loves the "
"church, and we pray for wives to trust their husbands and follow them the "
"way that the church should submit to Christ.\n"
"\n"
"Ephesians 5:31-32 says, \"Therefore a man shall leave his father and mother "
"and hold fast to his wife, and the two shall become one flesh. This mystery "
"is profound, and I am saying that it refers to Christ and the church.\"\n"
"\n"
"Father, we bless this people group that they would experience oneness with "
"Christ, and that this beautiful picture of marriage would point to the "
"ultimate union: this people group united with Christ as one for your glory."
msgstr ""
"Cerita dalam Kejadian 2:24 dilanjutkan dalam Efesus 5. Bapa, kami berdoa "
"agar pernikahan di antara kelompok orang ini diubah oleh ajaran Yesus. Kami "
"berdoa agar para suami mencintai istri mereka seperti Kristus mencintai "
"gereja, dan kami berdoa agar para istri mempercayai suami mereka dan "
"mengikuti mereka seperti gereja harus tunduk kepada Kristus.\n"
"\n"
"Efesus 5:31-32 berkata, \"Oleh karena itu, seorang laki-laki akan "
"meninggalkan ayah dan ibunya dan bersatu dengan istrinya, dan keduanya akan "
"menjadi satu daging. Rahasia ini sangat dalam, dan aku berkata bahwa hal ini "
"mengacu pada Kristus dan gereja.\"\n"
"\n"
"Bapa, kami memberkati kelompok orang ini agar mereka mengalami kesatuan "
"dengan Kristus, dan agar gambaran indah perkawinan ini menunjuk pada "
"persatuan yang ultimate: kelompok orang ini bersatu dengan Kristus sebagai "
"satu untuk kemuliaan-Mu."

msgid "Day 3: Humans Disobey God"
msgstr "Hari ke-3: Manusia Melanggar Perintah Tuhan"

msgid ""
"Genesis 3:1-24 (ESV)\n"
"Now the serpent was more crafty than any other beast of the field that the "
"LORD God had made. He said to the woman, \"Did God actually say, 'You shall "
"not eat of any tree in the garden'?\" And the woman said to the serpent, "
"\"We may eat of the fruit of the trees in the garden, but God said, 'You "
"shall not eat of the fruit of the tree that is in the midst of the garden, "
"neither shall you touch it, lest you die.' \" But the serpent said to the "
"woman, \"You will not surely die. For God knows that when you eat of it your "
"eyes will be opened, and you will be like God, knowing good and evil.\" So "
"when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was a "
"delight to the eyes, and that the tree was to be desired to make one wise, "
"she took of its fruit and ate, and she also gave some to her husband who was "
"with her, and he ate. Then the eyes of both were opened, and they knew that "
"they were naked. And they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves "
"loincloths. And they heard the sound of the LORD God walking in the garden "
"in the cool of the day, and the man and his wife hid themselves from the "
"presence of the LORD God among the trees of the garden. But the LORD God "
"called to the man and said to him, \"Where are you?\" And he said, \"I heard "
"the sound of you in the garden, and I was afraid, because I was naked, and I "
"hid myself.\" He said, \"Who told you that you were naked? Have you eaten of "
"the tree of which I commanded you not to eat?\" The man said, \"The woman "
"whom you gave to be with me, she gave me fruit of the tree, and I ate.\" "
"Then the LORD God said to the woman, \"What is this that you have done?\" "
"The woman said, \"The serpent deceived me, and I ate.\" The LORD God said to "
"the serpent, \"Because you have done this, cursed are you above all "
"livestock and above all beasts of the field; on your belly you shall go, and "
"dust you shall eat all the days of your life. I will put enmity between you "
"and the woman, and between your offspring and her offspring; he shall bruise "
"your head, and you shall bruise his heel.\" To the woman he said, \"I will "
"surely multiply your pain in childbearing; in pain you shall bring forth "
"children. Your desire shall be for your husband, and he shall rule over you."
"\" And to Adam he said, \"Because you have listened to the voice of your "
"wife and have eaten of the tree of which I commanded you, 'You shall not eat "
"of it,' cursed is the ground because of you; in pain you shall eat of it all "
"the days of your life; thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you; and "
"you shall eat the plants of the field. By the sweat of your face you shall "
"eat bread, till you return to the ground, for out of it you were taken; for "
"you are dust, and to dust you shall return.\" The man called his wife's name "
"Eve, because she was the mother of all living. And the LORD God made for "
"Adam and for his wife garments of skins and clothed them. Then the LORD God "
"said, \"Behold, the man has become like one of us in knowing good and evil. "
"Now, lest he reach out his hand and take also of the tree of life and eat, "
"and live forever—\" therefore the LORD God sent him out from the garden of "
"Eden to work the ground from which he was taken. He drove out the man, and "
"at the east of the garden of Eden he placed the cherubim and a flaming sword "
"that turned every way to guard the way to the tree of life."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This passage shows God acting with justice, compassion, and mercy as He "
"engages in dialogue with humanity following their disobedience. Despite this "
"disobedience requiring discipline, He immediately launched a rescue plan to "
"reverse the curse.\n"
"\n"
"We see in Jesus' day that many people did not understand the way of the "
"Messiah. For example, though they had read Genesis 3:15 many times, \"I will "
"put enmity between you and the woman and between your offspring and her "
"offspring. He shall bruise your head and you shall bruise his heel,\" they "
"didn't see Jesus.\n"
"\n"
"- In the same way, Muslims, when they read this passage, don't understand "
"that Jesus is the fulfillment of this promise. Pray that by the Holy Spirit, "
"their eyes would be opened to this reality."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini menunjukkan Allah bertindak dengan keadilan, belas kasihan, dan "
"rahmat saat Ia bercakap-cakap dengan umat manusia setelah mereka melanggar "
"perintah-Nya. Meskipun pelanggaran tersebut memerlukan hukuman, Ia segera "
"meluncurkan rencana penyelamatan untuk membatalkan kutukan tersebut.\n"
"\n"
"Pada zaman Yesus, banyak orang tidak memahami cara kerja Mesias. Misalnya, "
"meskipun mereka telah membaca Kejadian 3:15 berulang kali, \"Aku akan "
"menaruh permusuhan antara engkau dan perempuan itu, antara keturunanmu dan "
"keturunannya. Ia akan meremukkan kepalamu, dan engkau akan meremukkan tumit-"
"Nya,\" mereka tidak mengenali Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"- Demikian pula, umat Muslim, ketika mereka membaca ayat ini, tidak memahami "
"bahwa Yesus adalah penggenapan janji ini. Berdoalah agar oleh Roh Kudus, "
"mata mereka dibuka untuk kenyataan ini."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that disobedience to God's commands, even an act "
"that seems very small and simple, like eating a forbidden fruit, results in "
"eternal separation from him.\n"
"\n"
"- As Muslims read this story, pray for God to reveal their separation from "
"him. Whether they've committed \"big sins\" or \"small sins\", may they "
"recognize their guilt and continue to seek a solution through the reading of "
"God's uncorrupted Word."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa ketidaktaatan terhadap perintah "
"Allah, bahkan perbuatan yang tampak sangat kecil dan sederhana, seperti "
"memakan buah terlarang, mengakibatkan pemisahan abadi dari-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Saat umat Muslim membaca kisah ini, berdoalah agar Allah mengungkapkan "
"pemisahan mereka dari-Nya. Baik mereka telah melakukan \"dosa besar\" maupun "
"\"dosa kecil\", semoga mereka menyadari kesalahan mereka dan terus mencari "
"solusi melalui pembacaan Firman Allah yang suci."

msgid ""
"Jihene jumped in and interrupted Nour, the Christian telling the story of "
"Genesis 3, \"...and they ate the apple that God forbade them to eat and were "
"immediately ashamed of their nakedness. As a result God kicked them out of "
"heaven and sent them to earth.\"\n"
"\n"
"Nour responded, \"Yes, that's what the Quran teaches, but did you know that "
"there are a lot more details to the story in the Taurat (Old Testament) than "
"this summary?\"\n"
"\n"
"Jihene considers herself a good Muslim who has studied Islam, but who has "
"never read the Taurat or Injeel. She is a 'good person with a clean heart' "
"and believes her good deeds will ensure a place in heaven. When she talks "
"with Christians, she often shares her own unique version of Islam that "
"borrows many ideas from Christianity and makes her feel good.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for many Muslims like Jihene to read this story and recognize the "
"stain of sin that we all carry as people who have been disobedient to God.\n"
"- Ask God to stir curiosity to read and discover how God launched a rescue "
"plan for all of us."
msgstr ""
"Jihene menyela dan memotong cerita Nour, seorang Kristen yang sedang "
"menceritakan kisah Kejadian 3, \"...dan mereka memakan buah apel yang "
"dilarang oleh Tuhan, lalu segera merasa malu karena ketelanjangan mereka. "
"Akibatnya, Tuhan mengusir mereka dari surga dan mengirim mereka ke bumi.\"\n"
"\n"
"Nour menjawab, \"Ya, itulah yang diajarkan Al-Quran, tapi tahukah kamu bahwa "
"ada banyak detail lebih lanjut dalam Taurat (Perjanjian Lama) daripada "
"ringkasan ini?\"\n"
"\n"
"Jihene menganggap dirinya sebagai Muslim yang baik yang telah mempelajari "
"Islam, tetapi belum pernah membaca Taurat atau Injil. Dia adalah 'orang baik "
"dengan hati yang bersih' dan percaya bahwa amal baiknya akan menjamin tempat "
"di surga. Ketika dia berbicara dengan orang Kristen, dia sering membagikan "
"versinya sendiri tentang Islam yang meminjam banyak ide dari Kristen dan "
"membuatnya merasa baik.  \n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar banyak Muslim seperti Jihene membaca cerita ini dan "
"menyadari noda dosa yang kita semua bawa sebagai orang yang telah durhaka "
"kepada Allah.  \n"
"- Mintalah kepada Allah untuk membangkitkan rasa ingin tahu untuk membaca "
"dan menemukan bagaimana Allah meluncurkan rencana penyelamatan untuk kita "
"semua."

msgid ""
"This story illustrates the guilt, shame, and fear that covered Adam and Eve "
"when they sinned.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Christians trying to reach Muslims in this area to prayerfully "
"ponder their own testimony of entering God's Kingdom. Pray for them to "
"recall who they were before Christ: ashamed, fearful, and guilty, and who "
"they are now with Christ: forgiven, covered, and hopeful. Ask that they "
"would be able to tell their salvation story in a way that points those they "
"share with to want to read and understand the stories from the Bible.\n"
"- Pray for Christians to effectively describe how God has covered their "
"shame and brought healing into their broken relationship with God in the "
"same way that this story describes."
msgstr ""
"Cerita ini menggambarkan rasa bersalah, malu, dan takut yang melanda Adam "
"dan Hawa ketika mereka berbuat dosa.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi para Kristen yang berusaha menjangkau umat Muslim di daerah "
"ini agar mereka merenungkan dengan sungguh-sungguh kesaksian mereka tentang "
"masuk ke dalam Kerajaan Allah. Berdoalah agar mereka mengingat siapa mereka "
"sebelum Kristus: malu, takut, dan bersalah, dan siapa mereka sekarang "
"bersama Kristus: diampuni, dilindungi, dan penuh harapan. Mohon agar mereka "
"dapat menceritakan kisah keselamatan mereka dengan cara yang mendorong orang-"
"orang yang mereka ajak bicara untuk ingin membaca dan memahami kisah-kisah "
"dari Alkitab.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang Kristen dapat menjelaskan dengan efektif "
"bagaimana Allah telah menutupi rasa malu mereka dan membawa penyembuhan ke "
"dalam hubungan mereka yang rusak dengan Allah, sebagaimana diceritakan dalam "
"kisah ini."

msgid ""
"Father, we pray that the people of this land will rejoice in the truth of "
"Romans 5:15-21, because the free gift is not like the trespass of Genesis 3. "
"For if many died through Adam's trespass, how much more have the grace of "
"God and the free gift by the grace of that one man Jesus Christ abounded for "
"many?\n"
"\n"
"We know that apart from Christ, this people is under judgment following that "
"one trespass that brought condemnation, but the free gift following many "
"trespasses brought justification.\n"
"\n"
"For if because of one man's trespass death reigned through that one man, how "
"much more will those who receive the abundance of grace and the free gift of "
"righteousness reign in life through the one man, Jesus Christ?\n"
"\n"
"May many receive the free gift of righteousness through Jesus Christ. "
"Convict them of sin and may that conviction bring even greater joy and "
"thankfulness for the free gift of righteousness that covers their sin."
msgstr ""
"Bapa, kami berdoa agar umat di negeri ini bersukacita dalam kebenaran Roma "
"5:15-21, karena anugerah yang bebas itu tidak sama dengan pelanggaran dalam "
"Kejadian 3. Sebab jika banyak orang mati karena pelanggaran Adam, betapa "
"lebih besar lagi anugerah Allah dan anugerah yang bebas itu melimpah bagi "
"banyak orang melalui anugerah satu orang, Yesus Kristus.\n"
"\n"
"Kami tahu bahwa tanpa Kristus, umat ini berada di bawah hukuman akibat "
"pelanggaran itu yang membawa kutukan, tetapi anugerah yang diberikan setelah "
"banyak pelanggaran membawa pembenaran.\n"
"\n"
"Sebab jika karena pelanggaran satu orang, maut berkuasa melalui satu orang "
"itu, betapa lebih lagi mereka yang menerima kelimpahan kasih karunia dan "
"anugerah kebenaran akan berkuasa dalam hidup melalui satu orang, Yesus "
"Kristus?\n"
"\n"
"Semoga banyak orang menerima anugerah kebenaran melalui Yesus Kristus. "
"Biarlah mereka disadarkan akan dosa, dan semoga kesadaran itu membawa "
"sukacita dan ucapan syukur yang lebih besar atas anugerah kebenaran yang "
"menutupi dosa mereka."

msgid "Day 4: God Destroys an Evil Humanity"
msgstr "Hari ke-4: Allah menghancurkan umat manusia yang jahat."

msgid ""
"Genesis 6:5-6 (ESV)\n"
"The LORD saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that "
"every intention of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually. And "
"the LORD was sorry that he had made man on the earth, and it grieved him to "
"his heart.\n"
"\n"
"Genesis 6:9-22 (ESV)\n"
"These are the generations of Noah. Noah was a righteous man, blameless in "
"his generation. Noah walked with God. And Noah had three sons, Shem, Ham, "
"and Japheth. Now the earth was corrupt in God's sight, and the earth was "
"filled with violence. And God saw the earth, and behold, it was corrupt, for "
"all flesh had corrupted their way on the earth. And God said to Noah, \"I "
"have determined to make an end of all flesh, for the earth is filled with "
"violence through them. Behold, I will destroy them with the earth. Make "
"yourself an ark of gopher wood. Make rooms in the ark, and cover it inside "
"and out with pitch. This is how you are to make it: the length of the ark "
"300 cubits, its breadth 50 cubits, and its height 30 cubits. Make a roof for "
"the ark, and finish it to a cubit above, and set the door of the ark in its "
"side. Make it with lower, second, and third decks. For behold, I will bring "
"a flood of waters upon the earth to destroy all flesh in which is the breath "
"of life under heaven. Everything that is on the earth shall die. But I will "
"establish my covenant with you, and you shall come into the ark, you, your "
"sons, your wife, and your sons' wives with you. And of every living thing of "
"all flesh, you shall bring two of every sort into the ark to keep them alive "
"with you. They shall be male and female. Of the birds according to their "
"kinds, and of the animals according to their kinds, of every creeping thing "
"of the ground, according to its kind, two of every sort shall come in to you "
"to keep them alive. Also take with you every sort of food that is eaten, and "
"store it up. It shall serve as food for you and for them.\" Noah did this; "
"he did all that God commanded him.\n"
"\n"
"Genesis 7:17-24 (ESV)\n"
"The flood continued forty days on the earth. The waters increased and bore "
"up the ark, and it rose high above the earth. The waters prevailed and "
"increased greatly on the earth, and the ark floated on the face of the "
"waters. And the waters prevailed so mightily on the earth that all the high "
"mountains under the whole heaven were covered. The waters prevailed above "
"the mountains, covering them fifteen cubits deep. And all flesh died that "
"moved on the earth, birds, livestock, beasts, all swarming creatures that "
"swarm on the earth, and all mankind. Everything on the dry land in whose "
"nostrils was the breath of life died. He blotted out every living thing that "
"was on the face of the ground, man and animals and creeping things and birds "
"of the heavens. They were blotted out from the earth. Only Noah was left, "
"and those who were with him in the ark. And the waters prevailed on the "
"earth 150 days."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In the midst of complete brokenness, God is committed to finding a way to "
"restore relationship with His people.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the people of this place to recognize the deep brokenness in "
"their lives and to pursue the God who makes a way to restore relationships."
msgstr ""
"Di tengah-tengah kehancuran yang total, Allah berkomitmen untuk menemukan "
"cara untuk memulihkan hubungan dengan umat-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini menyadari kehancuran yang "
"mendalam dalam hidup mereka dan mengejar Allah yang membuka jalan untuk "
"memulihkan hubungan."

msgid ""
"When man is left to his own devices, he is completely corrupt and will only "
"do evil. There is no hope that we can please God in our own strength. Yet, "
"in this passage, in spite of his imperfections, we see that Noah found favor "
"in God's eyes.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for men and women in this place who genuinely want to please God to "
"be given an opportunity to meet a Christian who will point them to read "
"God's Word.\n"
"- Muslims claim to follow all the prophets (Adam, Abraham, Moses, Noah, "
"David, Jesus, Mohammed) but most never read what any of the prophets (except "
"for their prophet) actually said and did according to the Bible. They only "
"have a few snippets about them in the Koran. Pray for understanding that if "
"they claim to follow all the prophets, they need to know what all the "
"prophets said and taught from the Old and New Testament."
msgstr ""
"Ketika manusia dibiarkan bertindak sesuka hatinya, ia akan menjadi "
"sepenuhnya korup dan hanya akan melakukan kejahatan. Tidak ada harapan bahwa "
"kita dapat menyenangkan Allah dengan kekuatan kita sendiri. Namun, dalam "
"ayat ini, meskipun memiliki kelemahan, kita melihat bahwa Nuh mendapat kasih "
"karunia di mata Allah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk pria dan wanita di tempat ini yang sungguh-sungguh ingin "
"menyenangkan Allah agar diberi kesempatan untuk bertemu dengan seorang "
"Kristen yang akan menuntun mereka untuk membaca Firman Allah.\n"
"- Muslim mengklaim mengikuti semua nabi (Adam, Abraham, Musa, Nuh, Daud, "
"Yesus, Muhammad), tetapi kebanyakan dari mereka tidak pernah membaca apa "
"yang sebenarnya dikatakan dan dilakukan oleh para nabi (kecuali nabi mereka "
"sendiri) menurut Alkitab. Mereka hanya memiliki beberapa potongan informasi "
"tentang mereka dalam Al-Qur'an. Berdoalah agar mereka memahami bahwa jika "
"mereka mengklaim mengikuti semua nabi, mereka perlu mengetahui apa yang "
"dikatakan dan diajarkan oleh semua nabi dari Perjanjian Lama dan Perjanjian "
"Baru."

msgid ""
"\"You can't trust anyone. Everyone is out to take advantage of you. You need "
"to be careful who you trust. I don't have any other person that I've ever "
"shared these deep hopes and dreams with,\" said Miriam. Miriam's words "
"reflect a common struggle among Muslims.\n"
"\n"
"In one sense, Muslims have a deep understanding of the fallen nature of "
"mankind, evident in their lack of trust in people. On the other hand, they "
"put all their hope in earning God's favor through their own works. The story "
"of Noah makes it evident that there is none who are righteous and that we "
"need a Savior who can protect us from the coming flood of consequences of "
"our sin.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this place to realize that we are saved by grace, not "
"by works.\n"
"- Pray with awareness that the revelation of these things to a Muslim's "
"heart is a divine act of grace. Know that this is a spiritual battle and "
"your prayers matter."
msgstr ""
"\"Kamu tidak bisa mempercayai siapa pun. Semua orang berusaha "
"memanfaatkanmu. Kamu harus berhati-hati dalam memilih orang yang kamu "
"percayai. Aku tidak punya orang lain yang pernah aku bagikan harapan dan "
"impian dalam hati ini,\" kata Miriam. Kata-kata Miriam mencerminkan "
"perjuangan umum di kalangan Muslim.\n"
"\n"
"Dalam satu hal, umat Muslim memiliki pemahaman yang mendalam tentang sifat "
"manusia yang jatuh, yang terlihat dari kurangnya kepercayaan mereka terhadap "
"orang lain. Di sisi lain, mereka menaruh semua harapan mereka pada upaya "
"untuk mendapatkan ridha Allah melalui amal perbuatan mereka sendiri. Kisah "
"Nuh menunjukkan bahwa tidak ada yang benar-benar saleh, dan kita membutuhkan "
"Penyelamat yang dapat melindungi kita dari banjir konsekuensi dosa kita.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini menyadari bahwa kita diselamatkan "
"oleh anugerah, bukan oleh perbuatan.\n"
"- Berdoalah dengan kesadaran bahwa pengungkapan hal-hal ini kepada hati "
"seorang Muslim adalah tindakan anugerah ilahi. Ketahuilah bahwa ini adalah "
"pertempuran rohani dan doa-doa Anda penting."

msgid ""
"Isaiah 54:9-10 says, \"'This is like the days of Noah to me. As I swore that "
"the waters of Noah should no more go over the earth, so I have sworn that I "
"will not be angry with you and will not rebuke you. For the mountains may "
"depart and the hills be removed, but my steadfast love shall not depart from "
"you, and my covenant of peace shall not be removed,' says the Lord who has "
"compassion on you.\"\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the church in this place to be grounded in these realities. Pray "
"for believers to know that God's steadfast love will not depart from them.\n"
"- May they interact with their Muslim neighbors and friends and co-workers "
"with firm conviction that the covenant of peace they have with God shall not "
"be removed. Pray that the compassion that God has given them overflow with "
"compassion for the lost around them who do not have this truth."
msgstr ""
"Yesaya 54:9-10 berkata, \"Ini seperti hari-hari Nuh bagiku. Seperti Aku "
"bersumpah bahwa air bah Nuh tidak akan lagi melanda bumi, demikian pula Aku "
"bersumpah bahwa Aku tidak akan marah kepadamu dan tidak akan menegurmu. "
"Sebab gunung-gunung dapat berpindah dan bukit-bukit dapat digeser, tetapi "
"kasih setia-Ku tidak akan berpindah dari kamu, dan perjanjian damai-Ku tidak "
"akan digeser,\" kata Tuhan yang mengasihani kamu.\"\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar gereja di tempat ini teguh dalam kenyataan-kenyataan ini. "
"Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya tahu bahwa kasih setia Allah tidak akan "
"berpindah dari mereka.\n"
"- Semoga mereka berinteraksi dengan tetangga, teman, dan rekan kerja Muslim "
"mereka dengan keyakinan yang teguh bahwa perjanjian damai yang mereka miliki "
"dengan Allah tidak akan dipindahkan. Berdoalah agar belas kasihan yang Allah "
"berikan kepada mereka meluap menjadi belas kasihan bagi orang-orang yang "
"hilang di sekitar mereka yang tidak memiliki kebenaran ini."

msgid ""
"Hebrews 11:7 says, \"By faith Noah, being warned by God concerning events as "
"yet unseen, in reverent fear, constructed an ark for the saving of his "
"household. By this he condemned the world and became an heir of the "
"righteousness that comes by faith.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray for Muslims in this place to be people like Noah who would have a "
"reverent fear of God and who would take action toward the salvation of their "
"household. Ask that they would be people who would gather their children, "
"their siblings, aunts and uncles, and extended families to read God's Holy "
"Word and consequently be transformed by it.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for bold witnesses to emerge among this people who would proclaim the "
"good news that they are heirs of righteousness that comes by faith.\n"
"\n"
"Just as Noah is called a \"herald of righteousness\" in 2 Peter 2:5, may men "
"and women be raised up as heralds of righteousness in every region for God's "
"glory."
msgstr ""
"Ibrani 11:7 berkata, \"Dengan iman, Nuh, yang diperingatkan oleh Allah "
"tentang peristiwa-peristiwa yang belum terjadi, dengan rasa takut yang "
"saleh, membangun sebuah bahtera untuk menyelamatkan keluarganya. Dengan "
"demikian, ia menghukum dunia dan menjadi ahli waris kebenaran yang datang "
"melalui iman.\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini menjadi orang-orang seperti Nuh "
"yang memiliki rasa takut yang saleh kepada Allah dan yang mengambil tindakan "
"untuk keselamatan keluarganya. Mintalah agar mereka menjadi orang-orang yang "
"mengumpulkan anak-anak mereka, saudara-saudara mereka, paman dan bibi, serta "
"keluarga besar mereka untuk membaca Firman Allah yang kudus dan akibatnya "
"diubah olehnya.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar saksi-saksi yang berani muncul di antara umat ini yang akan "
"memberitakan kabar baik bahwa mereka adalah ahli waris kebenaran yang datang "
"melalui iman.\n"
"\n"
"Sama seperti Nuh disebut sebagai \"pengabar kebenaran\" dalam 2 Petrus 2:5, "
"semoga pria dan wanita diangkat sebagai pengabar kebenaran di setiap daerah "
"untuk kemuliaan Allah."

msgid "Day 5: God's Covenant with Noah"
msgstr "Hari ke-5: Perjanjian Allah dengan Nuh"

msgid ""
"Genesis 8:20-22 (ESV)\n"
"Then Noah built an altar to the LORD and took some of every clean animal and "
"some of every clean bird and offered burnt offerings on the altar. And when "
"the LORD smelled the pleasing aroma, the LORD said in his heart, \"I will "
"never again curse the ground because of man, for the intention of man's "
"heart is evil from his youth. Neither will I ever again strike down every "
"living creature as I have done. While the earth remains, seedtime and "
"harvest, cold and heat, summer and winter, day and night, shall not cease."
"\"\n"
"\n"
"Genesis 9:1-17 (ESV)\n"
"And God blessed Noah and his sons and said to them, \"Be fruitful and "
"multiply and fill the earth. The fear of you and the dread of you shall be "
"upon every beast of the earth and upon every bird of the heavens, upon "
"everything that creeps on the ground and all the fish of the sea. Into your "
"hand they are delivered. Every moving thing that lives shall be food for "
"you. And as I gave you the green plants, I give you everything. But you "
"shall not eat flesh with its life, that is, its blood. And for your "
"lifeblood I will require a reckoning: from every beast I will require it and "
"from man. From his fellow man I will require a reckoning for the life of "
"man. \"Whoever sheds the blood of man, by man shall his blood be shed, for "
"God made man in his own image. And you, be fruitful and multiply, teem on "
"the earth and multiply in it.\" Then God said to Noah and to his sons with "
"him, \"Behold, I establish my covenant with you and your offspring after "
"you, and with every living creature that is with you, the birds, the "
"livestock, and every beast of the earth with you, as many as came out of the "
"ark; it is for every beast of the earth. I establish my covenant with you, "
"that never again shall all flesh be cut off by the waters of the flood, and "
"never again shall there be a flood to destroy the earth.\" And God said, "
"\"This is the sign of the covenant that I make between me and you and every "
"living creature that is with you, for all future generations: I have set my "
"bow in the cloud, and it shall be a sign of the covenant between me and the "
"earth. When I bring clouds over the earth and the bow is seen in the clouds, "
"I will remember my covenant that is between me and you and every living "
"creature of all flesh. And the waters shall never again become a flood to "
"destroy all flesh. When the bow is in the clouds, I will see it and remember "
"the everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh "
"that is on the earth.\" God said to Noah, \"This is the sign of the covenant "
"that I have established between me and all flesh that is on the earth.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Here we see God entering a covenant with man. Yet man has no responsibility; "
"God takes it all. We also see that when God makes a promise, nothing could "
"stop Him from keeping it.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for faith to grow in your heart and in the hearts of people serving "
"this people group– that God's promise for all nations to be blessed includes "
"this Muslim people group.\n"
"- Pray for increased expectation that God will fulfill His promise."
msgstr ""
"Di sini kita melihat Allah mengadakan perjanjian dengan manusia. Namun, "
"manusia tidak memiliki tanggung jawab; Allah yang menanggung semuanya. Kita "
"juga melihat bahwa ketika Allah membuat janji, tidak ada yang dapat "
"menghentikan-Nya untuk menepatinya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar iman tumbuh di hati Anda dan di hati orang-orang yang "
"melayani kelompok etnis ini—bahwa janji Allah untuk memberkati semua bangsa "
"termasuk kelompok etnis Muslim ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar harapan akan pemenuhan janji Allah semakin besar."

msgid ""
"God desires us to fill the earth with His glory. Twice God commands Noah, "
"\"Be fruitful and multiply and fill the earth.\"\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up seekers among this people group whose curiosity "
"would be fruitful and multiply, creating more seekers.\n"
"- Pray that God would raise up disciple makers among this people group whose "
"passion would be fruitful and multiply, creating more disciple makers.\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up intercessors among this people group whose faith "
"would be fruitful and multiply, creating more intercessors.\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up church planters among this people group whose "
"sowing would be fruitful and multiply, creating more church planters."
msgstr ""
"Allah menghendaki kita untuk mengisi bumi dengan kemuliaan-Nya. Dua kali "
"Allah memerintahkan Nuh, \"Beranakcuculah dan bertambah banyak, dan isi "
"bumi.\"  \n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat orang-orang yang mencari-Nya di antara "
"kelompok etnis ini, sehingga rasa ingin tahu mereka berbuah dan bertambah "
"banyak, menciptakan lebih banyak orang yang mencari-Nya.  \n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat pembuat murid di antara kelompok etnis "
"ini, sehingga passion mereka berbuah dan bertambah banyak, menciptakan lebih "
"banyak pembuat murid.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat para penengah di antara kelompok etnis "
"ini, di mana iman mereka akan berbuah dan berkembang, menciptakan lebih "
"banyak penengah.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat para pendiri gereja di antara kelompok "
"etnis ini, di mana penaburan mereka akan berbuah dan berkembang, menciptakan "
"lebih banyak pendiri gereja."

msgid ""
"There are a lot of similarities between the Quran's version of Noah's story "
"and the Bible's. The Quran emphasizes Noah's preaching and moral lessons "
"rather than narrative details.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that as Muslims read this story from the Bible their hearts would be "
"drawn into the narrative and that they would understand that it's part of a "
"greater narrative.\n"
"- Pray for a growing hunger to discover the larger Genesis to Revelation "
"narrative and to learn their part in it."
msgstr ""
"Ada banyak kesamaan antara kisah Nuh dalam Al-Quran dan Alkitab. Al-Quran "
"lebih menekankan pada dakwah Nuh dan pelajaran moral daripada detail "
"naratif.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ketika umat Muslim membaca kisah ini dari Alkitab, hati "
"mereka tergerak oleh narasi tersebut dan mereka memahami bahwa kisah ini "
"merupakan bagian dari narasi yang lebih besar.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ada kerinduan yang semakin besar untuk memahami narasi yang "
"lebih luas dari Kitab Kejadian hingga Wahyu dan untuk mengetahui peran "
"mereka di dalamnya."

msgid ""
"Ibrahim came to Christ out of a Muslim background 20 years ago. For years, "
"he led a house church and was involved in outreach that shared Christ with "
"his people. This shifted in recent months, as he has been working with young "
"believers in his city who are pursuing a simple, reproducible discipleship "
"method (DMM). He jokes that he feels like he has been born again a second "
"time, because of all of the beautiful fruit being borne as disciples are "
"continuing to make disciples who in turn are making disciples.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that God would stir a hunger among every Christian, from this people "
"group and outsiders trying to reach them, to be fruitful and multiply. Equip "
"them with tools such as how to share their testimony, how to give a simple "
"Gospel presentation, how to start discovery Bible studies, and prayer "
"walking, so that they can go out into the harvest with confidence that God "
"will lead them to genuine seekers."
msgstr ""
"Ibrahim datang kepada Kristus dari latar belakang Muslim 20 tahun yang lalu. "
"Selama bertahun-tahun, ia memimpin gereja rumah dan terlibat dalam kegiatan "
"misi yang membagikan Injil kepada orang-orangnya. Perubahan terjadi dalam "
"beberapa bulan terakhir, karena ia kini bekerja dengan orang-orang percaya "
"muda di kotanya yang sedang mengejar metode pengikut Kristus yang sederhana "
"dan dapat direplikasi (DMM). Ia bercanda bahwa ia merasa seperti dilahirkan "
"kembali untuk kedua kalinya, karena buah-buah yang indah terus bermunculan "
"saat para pengikut Kristus terus membuat pengikut baru yang pada gilirannya "
"juga membuat pengikut baru.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Tuhan membangkitkan kerinduan di hati setiap orang Kristen, "
"baik dari kelompok etnis ini maupun orang-orang luar yang berusaha "
"menjangkau mereka, untuk menjadi berbuah dan berkembang biak. Berikan mereka "
"alat-alat seperti cara berbagi kesaksian, cara memberikan presentasi Injil "
"yang sederhana, cara memulai studi Alkitab penemuan, dan doa sambil "
"berjalan, sehingga mereka dapat keluar ke ladang panen dengan keyakinan "
"bahwa Tuhan akan memimpin mereka kepada pencari yang sejati."

msgid ""
"The book of Acts describes the early church in Acts 6:7, \"And the word of "
"God continued to increase, and the number of the disciples multiplied "
"greatly in Jerusalem, and a great many of the priests became obedient to the "
"faith.\"\n"
"\n"
"Acts 9:31 also says, \"so the church throughout all Judea and Galilee and "
"Samaria had peace and was being built up and walking in the fear of the Lord "
"and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit, it multiplied.\"\n"
"\n"
"Continuing in Acts 12:24, \"but the word of God increased and multiplied.\"\n"
"\n"
"We pray today that these same words would be spoken of this place. May the "
"Word of God increase among this people group. May many become obedient to "
"the faith here. May the church have peace as it is being built up. May "
"believers among this people group walk in the fear of the Lord and in the "
"comfort of the Holy Spirit. Ultimately may the number of disciples be "
"multiplied greatly."
msgstr ""
"Kitab Kisah Para Rasul menggambarkan gereja mula-mula dalam Kisah Para Rasul "
"6:7, \"Dan firman Allah terus bertambah, dan jumlah murid-murid bertambah "
"banyak di Yerusalem, dan banyak imam yang menjadi taat kepada iman.\"\n"
"\n"
"Kisah Para Rasul 9:31 juga mengatakan, \"sehingga gereja di seluruh Yudea, "
"Galilea, dan Samaria hidup dalam damai, dibangun, dan berjalan dalam takut "
"akan Tuhan serta dalam penghiburan Roh Kudus, sehingga jumlahnya "
"bertambah.\"\n"
"\n"
"Dilanjutkan dalam Kisah Para Rasul 12:24, \"tetapi firman Allah terus "
"bertambah dan berkembang.\"\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa hari ini agar kata-kata yang sama diucapkan tentang tempat ini. "
"Semoga firman Allah bertambah di antara kelompok orang ini. Semoga banyak "
"yang taat kepada iman di sini. Semoga gereja memiliki damai sejahtera saat "
"dibangun. Semoga orang-orang percaya di antara kelompok orang ini berjalan "
"dalam takut akan Tuhan dan dalam penghiburan Roh Kudus. Akhirnya, semoga "
"jumlah murid bertambah dengan pesat."

msgid "Day 6: Tower of Babel"
msgstr "Hari ke-6: Menara Babel"

msgid ""
"Genesis 11:1-9 (ESV)\n"
"Now the whole earth had one language and the same words. And as people "
"migrated from the east, they found a plain in the land of Shinar and settled "
"there. And they said to one another, \"Come, let us make bricks, and burn "
"them thoroughly.\" And they had brick for stone, and bitumen for mortar. "
"Then they said, \"Come, let us build ourselves a city and a tower with its "
"top in the heavens, and let us make a name for ourselves, lest we be "
"dispersed over the face of the whole earth.\" And the LORD came down to see "
"the city and the tower, which the children of man had built. And the LORD "
"said, \"Behold, they are one people, and they have all one language, and "
"this is only the beginning of what they will do. And nothing that they "
"propose to do will now be impossible for them. Come, let us go down and "
"there confuse their language, so that they may not understand one another's "
"speech.\" So the LORD dispersed them from there over the face of all the "
"earth, and they left off building the city. Therefore its name was called "
"Babel, because there the LORD confused the language of all the earth. And "
"from there the LORD dispersed them over the face of all the earth."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God is actively involved with the people He created. He is not far off. He "
"observes and comes down to interact and intervene for humanity's good.\n"
"\n"
"- Today as you pray for this place, thank God for His nearness.\n"
"- Pray for increasing numbers of people in this place to be aware of His "
"presence.\n"
"- Ask God, according to His steadfast love, to intervene when people in this "
"place reject Him and pursue their own desires."
msgstr ""
"Allah secara aktif terlibat dengan umat yang telah Dia ciptakan. Dia tidak "
"jauh dari kita. Dia mengamati dan turun untuk berinteraksi dan campur tangan "
"demi kebaikan umat manusia.\n"
"\n"
"- Hari ini, saat Anda berdoa untuk tempat ini, bersyukurlah kepada Allah "
"atas kedekatan-Nya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar semakin banyak orang di tempat ini menyadari kehadiran-"
"Nya.\n"
"- Mintalah kepada Allah, sesuai dengan kasih setia-Nya, untuk campur tangan "
"ketika orang-orang di tempat ini menolak-Nya dan mengejar keinginan mereka "
"sendiri."

msgid ""
"We are prone to the desire to make a name for ourselves, and to go against "
"God's command of filling the earth. We prefer comfort, security, and staying "
"put.\n"
"\n"
"This is illustrated in the story of Imen, a teacher who lived several hours "
"away from her family. She saw many things in Christianity that appealed to "
"her as she discussed Jesus with a Christian. Often she would say, \"Wow, I "
"really like that. That's really beautiful.\"\n"
"\n"
"But when it came time for her to decide if she wanted to follow Jesus or "
"just be a fan of Him, she felt fear of what the implications would be from "
"her family and community. Ultimately, the comfort and security of staying "
"where she was, like the builders on the 'plain in the land of Shinar', won "
"out.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims to be willing to follow and obey the truth despite the "
"discomfort and unease accompanied by setting their hearts on a heavenly home."
msgstr ""
"Kita cenderung memiliki keinginan untuk mencari nama bagi diri sendiri dan "
"melanggar perintah Allah untuk mengisi bumi. Kita lebih memilih kenyamanan, "
"keamanan, dan tetap tinggal di tempat.  \n"
"\n"
"Hal ini tergambar dalam kisah Imen, seorang guru yang tinggal beberapa jam "
"perjalanan dari keluarganya. Ia melihat banyak hal dalam Kristen yang "
"menarik baginya saat ia berdiskusi tentang Yesus dengan seorang Kristen. "
"Seringkali ia berkata, \"Wow, aku benar-benar suka itu. Itu benar-benar "
"indah.\"\n"
"\n"
"Namun, saat harus memutuskan apakah dia ingin mengikuti Yesus atau hanya "
"menjadi penggemar-Nya, dia merasa takut akan konsekuensi yang akan datang "
"dari keluarganya dan komunitasnya. Pada akhirnya, kenyamanan dan keamanan "
"tetap tinggal di tempatnya, seperti para pembangun di 'dataran di tanah "
"Shinar', menang.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim bersedia mengikuti dan menaati kebenaran "
"meskipun disertai ketidaknyamanan dan kegelisahan saat mereka menaruh hati "
"pada rumah surgawi."

msgid ""
"Muslims would also condemn arrogance and defiance of God, like we see in the "
"story of the Tower of Babel. However, most Muslims do not believe God would "
"'come down to see the city and the tower'.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this place to have their vision of God increased. Pray "
"for their understanding of His all-powerful qualities to grow in their "
"hearts and minds and to comprehend that God would enter into His creation to "
"save them."
msgstr ""
"Muslim juga akan mengutuk kesombongan dan pemberontakan terhadap Allah, "
"seperti yang kita lihat dalam kisah Menara Babel. Namun, kebanyakan Muslim "
"tidak percaya bahwa Allah akan 'turun untuk melihat kota dan menara "
"tersebut'.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini dapat memperdalam pemahaman "
"mereka tentang Allah. Berdoalah agar pemahaman mereka tentang sifat-sifat-"
"Nya yang maha kuasa tumbuh dalam hati dan pikiran mereka, dan agar mereka "
"memahami bahwa Allah akan turun ke dalam ciptaan-Nya untuk menyelamatkan "
"mereka."

msgid ""
"Pray for Christians in this place -- whether Muslim background believers or "
"foreigners who live among this people -- that they would reject the "
"temptation to settle and just be comfortable. Pray that they would have "
"courage to keep going: going into Muslim neighborhoods and homes, and making "
"Muslim friends, all with the goal of sharing the love of God with Muslims "
"and engaging them with His Word.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for churches in this place to resist the temptation to build in such a "
"way as to make a name for themselves, but that everything would be done for "
"the glory of God."
msgstr ""
"Berdoalah untuk orang-orang Kristen di tempat ini — baik yang berlatar "
"belakang Muslim maupun orang asing yang tinggal di antara mereka — agar "
"mereka menolak godaan untuk menetap dan merasa nyaman saja. Berdoalah agar "
"mereka memiliki keberanian untuk terus maju: masuk ke lingkungan dan rumah-"
"rumah Muslim, serta menjalin persahabatan dengan Muslim, semua dengan tujuan "
"untuk membagikan kasih Allah kepada Muslim dan melibatkan mereka dengan "
"Firman-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah bagi gereja-gereja di tempat ini agar menolak godaan untuk "
"membangun dengan cara yang bertujuan untuk mencari nama bagi diri sendiri, "
"tetapi agar segala sesuatu dilakukan untuk kemuliaan Allah."

msgid ""
"In Acts 2, on the day of Pentecost God reverses the division caused in the "
"story of the Tower of Babel. Instead of one language being divided into many "
"languages, we see many languages being understood through one message, "
"bringing unity.\n"
"\n"
"This happened because the main actor in Acts 2 is the Spirit of God. Pray "
"for the Spirit of God to be poured out on this land, resulting in multitudes "
"believing in Jesus and churches being formed and multiplied. Pray that "
"territorialism and division would end. Pray that any existing churches in "
"this place would work together in unity for God's glory."
msgstr ""
"Dalam Kisah Para Rasul 2, pada hari Pentakosta, Allah membalikkan pembagian "
"yang terjadi dalam kisah Menara Babel. Alih-alih satu bahasa dibagi menjadi "
"banyak bahasa, kita melihat banyak bahasa dipahami melalui satu pesan, "
"membawa persatuan.\n"
"\n"
"Hal ini terjadi karena tokoh utama dalam Kisah Para Rasul 2 adalah Roh "
"Allah. Berdoalah agar Roh Allah dicurahkan atas tanah ini, sehingga banyak "
"orang percaya kepada Yesus dan gereja-gereja dibentuk dan berkembang. "
"Berdoalah agar territorialisme dan perpecahan berakhir. Berdoalah agar "
"gereja-gereja yang sudah ada di tempat ini bekerja sama dalam kesatuan untuk "
"kemuliaan Allah."

msgid "Day 7: Abraham Trusted God"
msgstr "Hari ke-7: Abraham Percaya kepada Allah"

msgid ""
"Genesis 12:1–7 (ESV)\n"
"Now the LORD said to Abram, \"Go from your country and your kindred and your "
"father's house to the land that I will show you. And I will make of you a "
"great nation, and I will bless you and make your name great, so that you "
"will be a blessing. I will bless those who bless you, and him who dishonors "
"you I will curse, and in you all the families of the earth shall be blessed."
"\" So Abram went, as the LORD had told him, and Lot went with him. Abram was "
"seventy-five years old when he departed from Haran. And Abram took Sarai his "
"wife, and Lot his brother's son, and all their possessions that they had "
"gathered, and the people that they had acquired in Haran, and they set out "
"to go to the land of Canaan. When they came to the land of Canaan, Abram "
"passed through the land to the place at Shechem, to the oak of Moreh. At "
"that time the Canaanites were in the land. Then the LORD appeared to Abram "
"and said, \"To your offspring I will give this land.\" So he built there an "
"altar to the LORD, who had appeared to him.\n"
"\n"
"Genesis 15:1–6 (ESV)\n"
"After these things the word of the LORD came to Abram in a vision: \"Fear "
"not, Abram, I am your shield; your reward shall be very great.\" But Abram "
"said, \"O Lord GOD, what will you give me, for I continue childless, and the "
"heir of my house is Eliezer of Damascus?\" And Abram said, \"Behold, you "
"have given me no offspring, and a member of my household will be my heir.\" "
"And behold, the word of the LORD came to him: \"This man shall not be your "
"heir; your very own son shall be your heir.\" And he brought him outside and "
"said, \"Look toward heaven, and number the stars, if you are able to number "
"them.\" Then he said to him, \"So shall your offspring be.\" And he believed "
"the LORD, and he counted it to him as righteousness."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God appears to people and speaks through visions. We also learn that He is "
"trustworthy and obedience to Him is worth giving up anything -- including "
"family, land, and country.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to have visions of God speaking to them and "
"calling them to follow Him, even if it is scary or unnerving for them.\n"
"- As Abraham observed the stars and believed the Lord's promise to him, ask "
"God to reveal His power, goodness, and promises to people of this land "
"through creation. Pray that He would woo them to Himself and stir a "
"curiosity in them to seek out the Bible."
msgstr ""
"Allah menampakkan diri-Nya kepada manusia dan berbicara melalui penglihatan. "
"Kita juga belajar bahwa Dia dapat dipercaya, dan ketaatan kepada-Nya layak "
"untuk dikorbankan apa pun — termasuk keluarga, tanah, dan negara.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini mendapatkan penglihatan Allah "
"yang berbicara kepada mereka dan memanggil mereka untuk mengikuti-Nya, "
"meskipun hal itu menakutkan atau mengganggu bagi mereka.\n"
"- Seperti Abraham yang mengamati bintang-bintang dan percaya pada janji "
"Tuhan kepadanya, mintalah kepada Allah untuk mengungkapkan kuasa-Nya, "
"kebaikan-Nya, dan janji-janji-Nya kepada orang-orang di negeri ini melalui "
"ciptaan-Nya. Berdoalah agar Dia menarik mereka kepada-Nya dan membangkitkan "
"rasa ingin tahu dalam diri mereka untuk mencari Alkitab."

msgid ""
"We are not counted as righteous based on our deeds, but by our trust and "
"belief in God. We also learn that God chooses to work through humans to "
"bless others and to reach them with His good news.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up people among this people group like Abraham who "
"would obey Him and share the good news of Jesus with family members, "
"friends, neighbors, and co-workers.\n"
"- Pray for Muslims to repent of thinking their good deeds will cover their "
"sin and earn them a place in heaven. Pray for them to understand that "
"righteousness comes through faith alone."
msgstr ""
"Kita tidak dianggap benar berdasarkan perbuatan kita, tetapi berdasarkan "
"iman dan kepercayaan kita kepada Allah. Kita juga belajar bahwa Allah "
"memilih untuk bekerja melalui manusia untuk memberkati orang lain dan "
"menyampaikan kabar baik-Nya kepada mereka.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat orang-orang di antara kelompok etnis ini "
"seperti Abraham yang akan taat kepada-Nya dan membagikan kabar baik tentang "
"Yesus kepada anggota keluarga, teman, tetangga, dan rekan kerja.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim bertobat dari keyakinan bahwa perbuatan baik "
"mereka akan menutupi dosa mereka dan memberi mereka tempat di surga. "
"Berdoalah agar mereka memahami bahwa kebenaran datang melalui iman saja."

msgid ""
"Narimen had been married for eight years and was unable to have children. "
"Her sister-in-law had three already. When she found out she was pregnant, "
"she was ready to abort because of the cost of raising another child. Narimen "
"pleaded with her to keep the baby, telling her that she would raise the "
"child. The sister-in-law agreed and, as Narimen began to buy things for the "
"baby, her love and hopes for this child grew. When it came time for her "
"sister-in-law to go into labor, she didn't tell Narimen. Ultimately she "
"changed her mind and kept the baby. Narimen was crushed.\n"
"\n"
"Like Sarah who waited for the fulfillment of God's promise, throughout the "
"Muslim world, women carry the shame of infertility.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that Muslims who read the story of Abraham and Sarah would find hope "
"in a God who promises descendants, even if they are spiritual offspring.\n"
"- Pray for hope to grow in their hearts as the covenant-keeping God reveals "
"Himself to them."
msgstr ""
"Narimen telah menikah selama delapan tahun dan tidak dapat memiliki anak. "
"Kakak iparnya sudah memiliki tiga anak. Ketika dia mengetahui bahwa dia "
"hamil, dia siap untuk menggugurkan kandungannya karena biaya untuk "
"membesarkan anak lain. Narimen memohon padanya untuk mempertahankan bayi "
"itu, mengatakan bahwa dia akan membesarkan anak tersebut. Kakak iparnya "
"setuju, dan saat Narimen mulai membeli perlengkapan untuk bayi, cintanya dan "
"harapannya untuk anak itu semakin tumbuh. Ketika saatnya kakak iparnya akan "
"melahirkan, dia tidak memberitahu Narimen. Akhirnya dia berubah pikiran dan "
"mempertahankan bayi itu. Narimen merasa hancur.\n"
"\n"
"Seperti Sarah yang menanti terpenuhinya janji Allah, di seluruh dunia "
"Muslim, wanita-wanita menanggung rasa malu karena ketidaksuburan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim yang membaca kisah Abraham dan Sarah menemukan "
"harapan dalam Allah yang menjanjikan keturunan, meskipun keturunan itu "
"bersifat rohani.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar harapan tumbuh di hati mereka saat Allah yang setia pada "
"perjanjian-Nya menampakkan diri-Nya kepada mereka."

msgid ""
"Pray for Christians in this area who are trying to reach Muslims with the "
"good news of Jesus.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that they would continually be able to testify that God is their "
"shield and their reward. Pray that they would experience His protection, His "
"comfort, and His provision in rich ways.\n"
"- Pray for a desire to grow among all Christians in this region to see "
"generations of believers flowing out of them as streams of spiritual "
"children because of their faithful trust in God.\n"
"- Pray for confidence and faith to grow among Christians in this area– faith "
"that Muslim families are included in the promise that all the families of "
"the earth shall be blessed through Abraham. May they have eyes of faith for "
"the Muslim families all around them -- even extremists and strong followers "
"of Islam."
msgstr ""
"Berdoalah untuk umat Kristen di daerah ini yang berusaha memberitakan kabar "
"baik tentang Yesus kepada umat Muslim.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka terus dapat bersaksi bahwa Allah adalah perisai dan "
"upah mereka. Berdoalah agar mereka mengalami perlindungan-Nya, penghiburan-"
"Nya, dan pemeliharaan-Nya dengan cara yang melimpah.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ada keinginan untuk bertumbuh di antara semua orang Kristen "
"di wilayah ini, sehingga generasi-generasi orang percaya mengalir dari "
"mereka seperti aliran anak-anak rohani, karena kepercayaan mereka yang setia "
"kepada Allah.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar keyakinan dan iman bertumbuh di antara orang Kristen di "
"daerah ini—iman bahwa keluarga-keluarga Muslim termasuk dalam janji bahwa "
"semua keluarga di bumi akan diberkati melalui Abraham. Semoga mereka "
"memiliki mata iman untuk keluarga-keluarga Muslim di sekitar mereka—bahkan "
"ekstremis dan pengikut Islam yang teguh."

msgid ""
"Father, just as Romans 4:17 says that Abraham believed God, \"the one who "
"gives life to the dead and calls into existence the things that do not "
"exist\", give us eyes of faith to believe for multiplying disciples and "
"churches among this people group.\n"
"\n"
"Raise up believers in this area who, like Abraham, would in hope believe "
"against hope and become the spiritual fathers and mothers of a nation, "
"leading multiplying generations to faith in Christ.\n"
"\n"
"We pray that no unbelief would make men and women in this area waver "
"concerning the promise of God, but that they would grow strong in faith as "
"they give glory to God. May they be fully convinced that God is able to do "
"what He has promised."
msgstr ""
"Bapa, sebagaimana tertulis dalam Roma 4:17 bahwa Abraham percaya kepada "
"Allah, \"Yang menghidupkan orang mati dan memanggil hal-hal yang tidak ada "
"menjadi ada\", berikanlah kepada kami mata iman untuk percaya akan "
"pertumbuhan murid-murid dan gereja-gereja di tengah kelompok etnis ini.\n"
"\n"
"Bangkitkanlah orang-orang percaya di daerah ini yang, seperti Abraham, akan "
"percaya dengan penuh harapan meskipun dalam keadaan yang tidak "
"menguntungkan, dan menjadi bapa-bapa dan ibu-ibu rohani bagi suatu bangsa, "
"memimpin generasi-generasi yang berkembang dalam iman kepada Kristus.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa agar ketidakpercayaan tidak membuat pria dan wanita di daerah "
"ini goyah mengenai janji Allah, tetapi agar mereka tumbuh kuat dalam iman "
"saat mereka memuliakan Allah. Semoga mereka sepenuhnya yakin bahwa Allah "
"mampu melakukan apa yang telah Dia janjikan."

msgid "Day 8: Abraham Obeyed God"
msgstr "Hari ke-8: Abraham Menuruti Perintah Allah"

msgid ""
"Genesis 22:1–19 (ESV)\n"
"After these things God tested Abraham and said to him, \"Abraham!\" And he "
"said, \"Here am I.\" He said, \"Take your son, your only son Isaac, whom you "
"love, and go to the land of Moriah, and offer him there as a burnt offering "
"on one of the mountains of which I shall tell you.\" So Abraham rose early "
"in the morning, saddled his donkey, and took two of his young men with him, "
"and his son Isaac. And he cut the wood for the burnt offering and arose and "
"went to the place of which God had told him. On the third day Abraham lifted "
"up his eyes and saw the place from afar. Then Abraham said to his young men, "
"\"Stay here with the donkey; I and the boy will go over there and worship "
"and come again to you.\" And Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and "
"laid it on Isaac his son. And he took in his hand the fire and the knife. So "
"they went both of them together. And Isaac said to his father Abraham, \"My "
"father!\" And he said, \"Here am I, my son.\" He said, \"Behold, the fire "
"and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?\" Abraham said, "
"\"God will provide for himself the lamb for a burnt offering, my son.\" So "
"they went both of them together. When they came to the place of which God "
"had told him, Abraham built the altar there and laid the wood in order and "
"bound Isaac his son and laid him on the altar, on top of the wood. Then "
"Abraham reached out his hand and took the knife to slaughter his son. But "
"the angel of the LORD called to him from heaven and said, \"Abraham, Abraham!"
"\" And he said, \"Here am I.\" He said, \"Do not lay your hand on the boy or "
"do anything to him, for now I know that you fear God, seeing you have not "
"withheld your son, your only son, from me.\" And Abraham lifted up his eyes "
"and looked, and behold, behind him was a ram, caught in a thicket by his "
"horns. And Abraham went and took the ram and offered it up as a burnt "
"offering instead of his son. So Abraham called the name of that place, \"The "
"LORD will provide\"; as it is said to this day, \"On the mount of the LORD "
"it shall be provided.\" And the angel of the LORD called to Abraham a second "
"time from heaven and said, \"By myself I have sworn, declares the LORD, "
"because you have done this and have not withheld your son, your only son, I "
"will surely bless you, and I will surely multiply your offspring as the "
"stars of heaven and as the sand that is on the seashore. And your offspring "
"shall possess the gate of his enemies, and in your offspring shall all the "
"nations of the earth be blessed, because you have obeyed my voice.\" So "
"Abraham returned to his young men, and they arose and went together to "
"Beersheba. And Abraham lived at Beersheba."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that God will ask us to do things that do not make "
"sense to us. He desires obedience to His commands, and He is never contrary "
"to His nature.\n"
"\n"
"Historians agree that child sacrifice was widely practiced during Abraham's "
"day. So, Abraham would have been familiar with a command to sacrifice his "
"child. What was surprising was that God Himself intervened, provided a "
"substitute, showing that He could be completely trusted.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims, when they read this story, to have their trust in God "
"grow.\n"
"- Pray for Christians trying to reach Muslims in this place to rejoice, "
"though now for a little while they are grieved by various trials, so that "
"the tested genuineness of their faith, more precious than gold, that "
"perishes though it is refined by fire, may be found to result in praise and "
"glory and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ (1 Peter 1:6-7)."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa Allah akan meminta kita untuk "
"melakukan hal-hal yang tidak masuk akal bagi kita. Dia menginginkan ketaatan "
"terhadap perintah-Nya, dan Dia tidak pernah bertentangan dengan sifat-Nya.  "
"\n"
"\n"
"Sejarawan sepakat bahwa pengorbanan anak-anak secara luas dilakukan pada "
"zaman Abraham. Jadi, Abraham pasti sudah familiar dengan perintah untuk "
"mengorbankan anaknya. Yang mengejutkan adalah Allah sendiri yang campur "
"tangan, menyediakan pengganti, menunjukkan bahwa Dia dapat sepenuhnya "
"dipercaya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim, ketika membaca kisah ini, semakin mempercayai "
"Allah.\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi orang Kristen yang berusaha menjangkau umat Muslim di "
"tempat ini agar bersukacita, meskipun saat ini mereka sedih karena berbagai "
"cobaan, sehingga kesetiaan iman mereka yang diuji, yang lebih berharga "
"daripada emas yang fana meskipun diuji oleh api, dapat ditemukan "
"menghasilkan pujian, kemuliaan, dan kehormatan pada saat penyingkapan Yesus "
"Kristus (1 Petrus 1:6-7)."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that humans can hear God's voice. We learn that man "
"can be tested by God but that it is ultimately for our good.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this land to hear God's voice, whether through dreams, "
"visions, or the reading of the Bible.\n"
"- Pray for them to grow in hearing His voice and to respond in obedience to "
"what they've understood of what He said."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa manusia dapat mendengar suara Allah. "
"Kita belajar bahwa manusia dapat diuji oleh Allah, namun pada akhirnya hal "
"itu untuk kebaikan kita.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di negeri ini dapat mendengar suara Allah, baik "
"melalui mimpi, penglihatan, maupun pembacaan Alkitab.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka bertumbuh dalam mendengarkan suara-Nya dan "
"menanggapi dengan ketaatan terhadap apa yang mereka pahami dari apa yang Dia "
"katakan."

msgid ""
"Seventy days after Ramadan ends, Muslims gather together in homes to "
"celebrate Eid al-Adha and slaughter a sheep to commemorate this story, "
"though they do not understand the fullness of it. Muslims reject the idea of "
"a substitutionary sacrifice as we understand it in Christ. Yet every year "
"they celebrate this story of a substitutionary sacrifice.\n"
"\n"
"- Ask God to open hearts and open minds. Help them see how he provided a ram "
"to stop Abraham from sacrificing his son to foreshadow his plan to send his "
"only Son hundreds of years later as a substitutionary sacrifice on our "
"behalf."
msgstr ""
"Tujuh puluh hari setelah Ramadan berakhir, umat Muslim berkumpul di rumah-"
"rumah untuk merayakan Idul Adha dan menyembelih seekor domba sebagai "
"peringatan atas kisah ini, meskipun mereka tidak sepenuhnya memahami "
"maknanya. Umat Muslim menolak konsep pengorbanan pengganti sebagaimana kita "
"pahami dalam Kristus. Namun, setiap tahun mereka merayakan kisah pengorbanan "
"pengganti ini.\n"
"\n"
"- Mintalah kepada Allah untuk membuka hati dan pikiran mereka. Bantulah "
"mereka melihat bagaimana Allah menyediakan seekor domba untuk menghentikan "
"Abraham dari menyembelih anaknya, sebagai gambaran rencana-Nya untuk "
"mengutus Anak-Nya yang tunggal ratusan tahun kemudian sebagai korban "
"pengganti bagi kita."

msgid ""
"This story shows us Abraham's radical, immediate, and costly obedience. When "
"God told him to take his son, whom he loves, and to offer him as a burnt "
"offering, the very next morning Abraham rose early and began that journey.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for believers in this place to also exhibit radical, immediate, "
"costly obedience to a good God who loves them and loves the Muslim people "
"surrounding them."
msgstr ""
"Cerita ini menunjukkan ketaatan Abraham yang radikal, segera, dan mahal. "
"Ketika Allah menyuruhnya untuk membawa anaknya yang dikasihinya dan "
"mempersembahkannya sebagai korban bakaran, keesokan paginya Abraham bangun "
"pagi-pagi dan memulai perjalanan itu.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya di tempat ini juga menunjukkan ketaatan "
"yang radikal, segera, dan mahal kepada Allah yang baik yang mengasihi mereka "
"dan mengasihi umat Muslim di sekitar mereka."

msgid ""
"Hebrews 11:17 says, \"By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered up "
"Isaac, and he who had received the promises was in the act of offering up "
"his only son, of whom it was said, 'Through Isaac shall your offspring be "
"named.' He considered that God was able even to raise him from the dead, "
"from which, figuratively speaking, he did receive him back.\"\n"
"\n"
"Lord, grow such a strong confidence and trust in You among believers in this "
"place that they would see miracles happen and His name glorified as many "
"Muslims turn to faith in Jesus.\n"
"\n"
"Unlike the temporary sacrifices of the Old Covenant, we know that it is "
"impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away sins. Pray for "
"Muslims in this place to trust in Christ, who when He offered for all time a "
"single sacrifice for sin, sat down at the right hand of God. May they "
"believe by His single offering, He has perfected for all time those who are "
"being sanctified."
msgstr ""
"Ibrani 11:17 berkata, \"Dengan iman, Abraham, ketika diuji, mempersembahkan "
"Ishak. Dia yang telah menerima janji-janji itu sedang mempersembahkan anak "
"tunggalnya, tentang siapa dikatakan, 'Melalui Ishak, keturunanmu akan "
"dinamai.' Dia percaya bahwa Allah mampu membangkitkannya dari kematian, dan "
"secara kiasan, dia memang menerimanya kembali.\"\n"
"\n"
"Tuhan, tumbuhkanlah keyakinan dan kepercayaan yang kuat kepada-Mu di antara "
"orang-orang percaya di tempat ini, sehingga mereka dapat melihat mujizat "
"terjadi dan nama-Nya dimuliakan ketika banyak Muslim berbalik kepada iman "
"dalam Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"Berbeda dengan korban-korban sementara Perjanjian Lama, kita tahu bahwa "
"darah lembu dan kambing tidak dapat menghapus dosa. Berdoalah bagi umat "
"Muslim di tempat ini agar percaya kepada Kristus, yang ketika Ia "
"mempersembahkan korban tunggal untuk dosa sekali untuk selamanya, duduk di "
"sebelah kanan Allah. Semoga mereka percaya bahwa melalui persembahan tunggal-"
"Nya, Ia telah menyempurnakan untuk selamanya mereka yang sedang disucikan."

msgid "Day 9: God's Call to Moses"
msgstr "Hari ke-9: Panggilan Allah kepada Musa"

msgid ""
"Exodus 2:23-25 (ESV)\n"
"During those many days the king of Egypt died, and the people of Israel "
"groaned because of their slavery and cried out for help. Their cry for "
"rescue from slavery came up to God. And God heard their groaning, and God "
"remembered his covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob. God saw "
"the people of Israel—and God knew.\n"
"\n"
"Exodus 3:1-14 (ESV)\n"
"Now Moses was keeping the flock of his father-in-law, Jethro, the priest of "
"Midian, and he led his flock to the west side of the wilderness and came to "
"Horeb, the mountain of God. And the angel of the LORD appeared to him in a "
"flame of fire out of the midst of a bush. He looked, and behold, the bush "
"was burning, yet it was not consumed. And Moses said, \"I will turn aside to "
"see this great sight, why the bush is not burned.\" When the LORD saw that "
"he turned aside to see, God called to him out of the bush, \"Moses, Moses!\" "
"And he said, \"Here I am.\" Then he said, \"Do not come near; take your "
"sandals off your feet, for the place on which you are standing is holy "
"ground.\" And he said, \"I am the God of your father, the God of Abraham, "
"the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.\" And Moses hid his face, for he was "
"afraid to look at God. Then the LORD said, \"I have surely seen the "
"affliction of my people who are in Egypt and have heard their cry because of "
"their taskmasters. I know their sufferings, and I have come down to deliver "
"them out of the hand of the Egyptians and to bring them up out of that land "
"to a good and broad land, a land flowing with milk and honey, to the place "
"of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, "
"and the Jebusites. And now, behold, the cry of the people of Israel has come "
"to me, and I have also seen the oppression with which the Egyptians oppress "
"them. Come, I will send you to Pharaoh that you may bring my people, the "
"children of Israel, out of Egypt.\" But Moses said to God, \"Who am I that I "
"should go to Pharaoh and bring the children of Israel out of Egypt?\" He "
"said, \"But I will be with you, and this shall be the sign for you, that I "
"have sent you: when you have brought the people out of Egypt, you shall "
"serve God on this mountain.\" Then Moses said to God, \"If I come to the "
"people of Israel and say to them, 'The God of your fathers has sent me to "
"you,'and they ask me, 'What is his name?'what shall I say to them?\" God "
"said to Moses, \"I AM WHO I AM.\" And he said, \"Say this to the people of "
"Israel, 'I AM has sent me to you.' \"\n"
"\n"
"Exodus 7:1-5 (ESV)\n"
"And the LORD said to Moses, \"See, I have made you like God to Pharaoh, and "
"your brother Aaron shall be your prophet. You shall speak all that I command "
"you, and your brother Aaron shall tell Pharaoh to let the people of Israel "
"go out of his land. But I will harden Pharaoh's heart, and though I multiply "
"my signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, Pharaoh will not listen to you. "
"Then I will lay my hand on Egypt and bring my hosts, my people the children "
"of Israel, out of the land of Egypt by great acts of judgment. The Egyptians "
"shall know that I am the LORD, when I stretch out my hand against Egypt and "
"bring out the people of Israel from among them.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God hears, He sees suffering, and He comes to end it at just the right "
"time.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for those who are oppressed in this land to know that their "
"sufferings are seen by God. Pray that they would have hope that He would "
"intervene and for those circumstances to be used to ultimately bring them "
"into a saving relationship with Him.\n"
"- Pray for oppressors in this land to repent. Pray they would not be like "
"Pharaoh whose heart was hard, but that they would have Saul-to-Paul like "
"conversion experiences."
msgstr ""
"Allah mendengarkan, Ia melihat penderitaan, dan Ia datang untuk "
"mengakhirinya pada waktu yang tepat.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi mereka yang tertindas di negeri ini agar mereka tahu bahwa "
"penderitaan mereka dilihat oleh Allah. Berdoalah agar mereka memiliki "
"harapan bahwa Dia akan campur tangan dan agar keadaan tersebut digunakan "
"untuk akhirnya membawa mereka ke dalam hubungan penyelamatan dengan-Nya.\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi para penindas di negeri ini agar mereka bertobat. Berdoalah "
"agar mereka tidak seperti Firaun yang hatinya keras, tetapi agar mereka "
"mengalami pengalaman pertobatan seperti Saul menjadi Paulus."

msgid ""
"Moses' obedience to God's calling impacted an entire nation.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that God would raise up men and women in this land who would "
"faithfully listen to the voice of God, and that it would bring about freedom "
"from sin for multitudes in their nation.\n"
"\n"
"We also learn that God delights to use people who feel inadequate and are "
"humble.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that those who humble themselves in this land today, would be exalted "
"and that God would humble those who exalt themselves over others."
msgstr ""
"Ketaatan Musa terhadap panggilan Allah berdampak pada seluruh bangsa.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat pria dan wanita di negeri ini yang setia "
"mendengarkan suara Allah, dan agar hal itu membawa kebebasan dari dosa bagi "
"banyak orang di negerinya.\n"
"\n"
"Kita juga belajar bahwa Allah senang menggunakan orang-orang yang merasa "
"tidak layak dan rendah hati.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka yang merendahkan diri di negeri ini hari ini, akan "
"ditinggikan, dan agar Allah merendahkan mereka yang meninggikan diri di atas "
"orang lain."

msgid ""
"This story shows us that the proof that God spoke through Moses was when the "
"things that Moses spoke actually came to happen. Pray for Muslims to ponder "
"the meaning of the word 'prophet'. They claim to believe all of the prophets "
"(including Abraham, Moses, Jesus) though most have never read their actual "
"teachings in the Old Testament and New Testament. Pray for God to use "
"believers to challenge this reality and for a curiosity to grow among "
"Muslims all over this land to want to read what all of the prophets taught.\n"
"\n"
"This hunger to know what the prophets truly taught can lead to life-changing "
"encounters. Souad was a divorced woman who feared God and tried to practice "
"Islam correctly. She raised her children to follow Islam. After they were "
"grown and out of the house she bought several expensive Islamic books to do "
"deep research. The further she went, the more doubt began to grow in her "
"heart. She became curious about Jesus. Late one night, she fell on her knees "
"and prayed. The room was filled with light and a voice spoke clearly, \"I am "
"He.\" These were the same words in Arabic that she would later read in the "
"New Testament- Jesus' declaration of His divine identity. After she "
"understood what the prophets taught about Him, she would choose to make Him "
"her Lord and Savior."
msgstr ""
"Cerita ini menunjukkan kepada kita bahwa bukti bahwa Allah berbicara melalui "
"Musa adalah ketika hal-hal yang Musa katakan benar-benar terjadi. Berdoalah "
"agar umat Muslim merenungkan makna kata \"nabi\". Mereka mengaku percaya "
"pada semua nabi (termasuk Abraham, Musa, dan Yesus), meskipun kebanyakan "
"dari mereka belum pernah membaca ajaran-ajaran mereka yang sebenarnya dalam "
"Perjanjian Lama dan Perjanjian Baru. Berdoalah agar Allah menggunakan orang-"
"orang beriman untuk menantang kenyataan ini dan agar rasa ingin tahu tumbuh "
"di kalangan umat Muslim di seluruh negeri ini untuk ingin membaca apa yang "
"diajarkan oleh semua nabi.\n"
"\n"
"Rasa ingin tahu untuk mengetahui apa yang sebenarnya diajarkan oleh para "
"nabi dapat membawa kepada pertemuan yang mengubah hidup. Souad adalah "
"seorang wanita yang bercerai, takut akan Allah, dan berusaha mempraktikkan "
"Islam dengan benar. Dia membesarkan anak-anaknya untuk mengikuti Islam. "
"Setelah mereka dewasa dan meninggalkan rumah, dia membeli beberapa buku "
"Islam yang mahal untuk melakukan penelitian mendalam. Semakin jauh dia "
"meneliti, semakin besar keraguan yang tumbuh di hatinya. Dia menjadi "
"penasaran tentang Yesus. Suatu malam larut, dia berlutut dan berdoa. Ruangan "
"dipenuhi cahaya dan sebuah suara berkata dengan jelas, \"Akulah Dia.\" Kata-"
"kata ini sama dengan yang dia baca kemudian dalam Perjanjian Baru—pengakuan "
"Yesus tentang identitas ilahi-Nya. Setelah dia memahami apa yang diajarkan "
"para nabi tentang-Nya, dia memilih untuk menjadikan-Nya Tuhan dan "
"Juruselamatnya."

msgid ""
"Christians living among Muslim peoples, especially those who have chosen to "
"follow Christ out of a Muslim background, often live in fear of persecution "
"because of their faith.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that God's promise of rescue, freedom, and hope in this story would "
"thrill their hearts and stir them to act with boldness and agreement with "
"all of His commands.\n"
"- Pray for Christians trying to serve Muslims by sharing the Good News of "
"Jesus, despite the inadequacies they feel, to have a heart posture that "
"says, \"Here I am.\""
msgstr ""
"Kristen yang hidup di tengah-tengah masyarakat Muslim, terutama mereka yang "
"telah memilih untuk mengikuti Kristus dari latar belakang Muslim, sering "
"hidup dalam ketakutan akan penganiayaan karena iman mereka.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar janji Allah tentang penyelamatan, kebebasan, dan harapan "
"dalam kisah ini dapat membangkitkan hati mereka dan mendorong mereka untuk "
"bertindak dengan keberanian serta taat pada semua perintah-Nya.\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi umat Kristen yang berusaha melayani umat Muslim dengan "
"membagikan Kabar Baik tentang Yesus, meskipun mereka merasa tidak cukup, "
"agar mereka memiliki sikap hati yang berkata, \"Di sini aku.\""

msgid ""
"Two thousand years later, John 8:56-59 records Jesus saying to a group of "
"religious leaders, \"'Your father Abraham rejoiced that he would see my day. "
"He saw it and was glad.'\"\n"
"\n"
"One religious leader said to Him, \"You're not yet 50 years old, and have "
"you seen Abraham?\" Jesus said to them, \"Truly, truly, I say to you, before "
"Abraham was, I am.\"\n"
"\n"
"This statement so outraged the religious leaders that they picked up stones "
"to stone Him. He used the same title God used in this passage from Exodus 3 "
"to declare who He is. Pray for Muslims in this land to have their eyes "
"opened to the reality that Jesus is greater than Abraham, Moses, and all the "
"prophets and that He came to set His people free – not just from Pharaoh, "
"but from sin."
msgstr ""
"Dua ribu tahun kemudian, Yohanes 8:56-59 mencatat perkataan Yesus kepada "
"sekelompok pemimpin agama, \"'Bapakmu Abraham bersukacita karena ia akan "
"melihat hari-Ku. Ia melihatnya dan bersukacita.'\"\n"
"\n"
"Seorang pemimpin agama berkata kepada-Nya, \"Engkau belum berusia 50 tahun, "
"dan apakah Engkau telah melihat Abraham?\" Yesus berkata kepada mereka, "
"\"Sesungguhnya, sesungguhnya, Aku berkata kepadamu, sebelum Abraham ada, Aku "
"sudah ada.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pernyataan ini begitu membuat marah para pemimpin agama sehingga mereka "
"mengambil batu untuk melempari-Nya. Ia menggunakan gelar yang sama yang "
"digunakan Allah dalam ayat ini dari Keluaran 3 untuk menyatakan siapa diri-"
"Nya. Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di negeri ini membuka mata mereka terhadap "
"kenyataan bahwa Yesus lebih besar daripada Abraham, Musa, dan semua nabi, "
"dan bahwa Ia datang untuk membebaskan umat-Nya – bukan hanya dari Firaun, "
"tetapi dari dosa."

msgid "Day 10: The Passover Sacrifice"
msgstr "Hari ke-10: Korban Paskah"

msgid ""
"Exodus 12:1-3 (ESV)\n"
"The LORD said to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, \"This month shall be "
"for you the beginning of months. It shall be the first month of the year for "
"you. Tell all the congregation of Israel that on the tenth day of this month "
"every man shall take a lamb according to their fathers' houses, a lamb for a "
"household.\n"
"\n"
"Exodus 12:21-31 (ESV)\n"
"Then Moses called all the elders of Israel and said to them, \"Go and select "
"lambs for yourselves according to your clans, and kill the Passover lamb. "
"Take a bunch of hyssop and dip it in the blood that is in the basin, and "
"touch the lintel and the two doorposts with the blood that is in the basin. "
"None of you shall go out of the door of his house until the morning. For the "
"LORD will pass through to strike the Egyptians, and when he sees the blood "
"on the lintel and on the two doorposts, the LORD will pass over the door and "
"will not allow the destroyer to enter your houses to strike you. You shall "
"observe this rite as a statute for you and for your sons forever. And when "
"you come to the land that the LORD will give you, as he has promised, you "
"shall keep this service. And when your children say to you, 'What do you "
"mean by this service?' you shall say, 'It is the sacrifice of the LORD's "
"Passover, for he passed over the houses of the people of Israel in Egypt, "
"when he struck the Egyptians but spared our houses.' \" And the people bowed "
"their heads and worshiped. Then the people of Israel went and did so; as the "
"LORD had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did. At midnight the LORD struck "
"down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, from the firstborn of Pharaoh "
"who sat on his throne to the firstborn of the captive who was in the "
"dungeon, and all the firstborn of the livestock. And Pharaoh rose up in the "
"night, he and all his servants and all the Egyptians. And there was a great "
"cry in Egypt, for there was not a house where someone was not dead. Then he "
"summoned Moses and Aaron by night and said, \"Up, go out from among my "
"people, both you and the people of Israel; and go, serve the LORD, as you "
"have said.\n"
"\n"
"Exodus 12:40–42 (ESV)\n"
"The time that the people of Israel lived in Egypt was 430 years. At the end "
"of 430 years, on that very day, all the hosts of the LORD went out from the "
"land of Egypt. It was a night of watching by the LORD, to bring them out of "
"the land of Egypt; so this same night is a night of watching kept to the "
"LORD by all the people of Israel throughout their generations."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God makes a way for people to escape His righteous judgment -- through the "
"blood of a spotless lamb.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this place to feel the weight of their sin.\n"
"- Pray that their acceptance of God's great mercy would not lead them to "
"passivity, but would drive them to want to know the way that God's mercy "
"could cover over their sins."
msgstr ""
"Allah menyediakan jalan bagi manusia untuk terhindar dari hukuman-Nya yang "
"adil -- melalui darah domba yang tak bercela.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini merasakan beban dosa mereka.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar penerimaan mereka terhadap rahmat besar Allah tidak membuat "
"mereka menjadi pasif, tetapi mendorong mereka untuk ingin mengetahui cara "
"bagaimana rahmat Allah dapat menutupi dosa-dosa mereka."

msgid ""
"Man's efforts to oppose God's plans to set His people free are futile.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this place to have a greater fear of God than a fear "
"of what man could do to them for seeking the truth.\n"
"\n"
"We also learn that God desires us to pass on to our children the stories of "
"the works He has done in our lives from generation to generation.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for seekers and those on a journey among this people group to not "
"only seek God themselves, but to desire to pass on what they have learned to "
"future generations, both biological and spiritual."
msgstr ""
"Upaya manusia untuk menentang rencana Allah dalam membebaskan umat-Nya "
"adalah sia-sia.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini memiliki rasa takut yang lebih "
"besar kepada Allah daripada rasa takut terhadap apa yang dapat dilakukan "
"manusia kepada mereka karena mencari kebenaran.\n"
"\n"
"Kita juga belajar bahwa Allah menghendaki kita untuk meneruskan kisah-kisah "
"tentang karya-Nya dalam hidup kita kepada anak-anak kita dari generasi ke "
"generasi.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar para pencari kebenaran dan mereka yang sedang dalam "
"perjalanan di kalangan kelompok etnis ini tidak hanya mencari Allah sendiri, "
"tetapi juga menginginkan untuk meneruskan apa yang telah mereka pelajari "
"kepada generasi mendatang, baik secara biologis maupun spiritual."

msgid ""
"Sitting, enjoying the fun of a wedding, Samar left to answer a phone call "
"from her husband. He told her that their son's best friend had died in an "
"accident. When Samar went to tell her cousin that she needed to leave "
"because there had been a death of a son, the cousin panicked, initially "
"thinking it was her firstborn son who had died. As the women tried to make "
"sense of what had happened they tried to comfort themselves by saying "
"\"maktoub\" -- it was simply 'written' or predestined by God that this young "
"man would die.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the good news of a God who did not spare His firstborn and only "
"Son so that families all over the world would never experience eternal death "
"and separation from loved ones to penetrate this land.\n"
"- Pray that the crippling fear many Muslims walk with, because of their lack "
"of assurance of God's mercy for them and their loved ones, would drive them "
"to want to understand the unshakable hope followers of Christ carry even in "
"the midst of extreme suffering."
msgstr ""
"Duduk, menikmati keseruan pernikahan, Samar pergi untuk menjawab panggilan "
"telepon dari suaminya. Suaminya memberitahunya bahwa teman terbaik putranya "
"telah meninggal dalam kecelakaan. Ketika Samar pergi memberitahu sepupunya "
"bahwa dia harus pergi karena ada kematian seorang anak laki-laki, sepupunya "
"panik, awalnya mengira bahwa anak sulungnya yang meninggal. Saat para wanita "
"mencoba memahami apa yang terjadi, mereka mencoba menghibur diri dengan "
"mengatakan \"maktoub\" — itu hanyalah \"ditakdirkan\" atau sudah ditakdirkan "
"oleh Tuhan bahwa pemuda itu akan meninggal.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kabar baik tentang Allah yang tidak menyayangkan Anak-Nya "
"yang sulung dan satu-satunya agar keluarga di seluruh dunia tidak pernah "
"mengalami kematian abadi dan pemisahan dari orang-orang yang mereka cintai "
"dapat menembus tanah ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ketakutan yang melumpuhkan yang banyak dialami oleh umat "
"Muslim, karena kurangnya keyakinan akan rahmat Allah bagi mereka dan orang-"
"orang yang mereka cintai, akan mendorong mereka untuk ingin memahami harapan "
"yang tak tergoyahkan yang dibawa oleh pengikut Kristus bahkan di tengah "
"penderitaan yang ekstrem."

msgid ""
"- Pray that just as this story shows the nation of Israel entering into "
"God's redemptive story, believers trying to reach Muslims in this land would "
"agree with their role in God's redemptive story for this place.\n"
"- Pray for Christian families to regularly celebrate the freedom they've "
"experienced from sin by being covered by the blood of the precious Lamb of "
"God, and that testimony would be wisely and boldly proclaimed to their "
"neighbors, coworkers, and friends."
msgstr ""
"- Berdoalah agar, sebagaimana kisah ini menunjukkan bangsa Israel memasuki "
"kisah penebusan Allah, para percaya yang berusaha menjangkau umat Muslim di "
"negeri ini juga menyadari peran mereka dalam kisah penebusan Allah bagi "
"tempat ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar keluarga-keluarga Kristen secara rutin merayakan kebebasan "
"yang mereka alami dari dosa melalui penutup darah Anak Domba Allah yang "
"mulia, dan agar kesaksian itu diproklamasikan dengan bijak dan berani kepada "
"tetangga, rekan kerja, dan teman-teman mereka."

msgid ""
"Lord, we pray that there would be many in this land who would call on you as "
"Father, who judges impartially according to each one's deeds. May they "
"conduct themselves with fear throughout the time of their exile, knowing "
"that they were ransomed from the futile ways inherited from their "
"forefathers, not with perishable things such as silver or gold, but with the "
"precious blood of Christ, like that of a lamb without blemish or spot. (1 "
"Peter 1:17-19)\n"
"\n"
"In Luke 22:14-20 Jesus said: \"'I have earnestly desired to eat this "
"Passover with you before I suffer. For I tell you, I will not eat it until "
"it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God.' And he took a cup and when he had "
"given thanks, he said, 'Take this and divide it among yourselves. For I tell "
"you that from now on, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine until the "
"kingdom of God comes.' And he took bread when he had given thanks, he broke "
"it and gave it to them saying, 'This is my body, which is given for you. Do "
"this in remembrance of me.' And likewise the cup after they had eaten, "
"saying, 'This cup that is poured out for you is the new covenant in my "
"blood.'\" Pray that multitudes of families in this place would take part in "
"the new covenant that Jesus invited them into through His death, burial, and "
"resurrection."
msgstr ""
"Tuhan, kami berdoa agar banyak orang di negeri ini yang memanggil-Mu sebagai "
"Bapa, yang menghakimi dengan adil sesuai dengan perbuatan masing-masing. "
"Semoga mereka hidup dengan takut akan-Mu sepanjang masa pengasingan mereka, "
"mengetahui bahwa mereka telah ditebus dari cara hidup yang sia-sia yang "
"diwarisi dari nenek moyang mereka, bukan dengan barang-barang yang fana "
"seperti perak atau emas, tetapi dengan darah yang mulia dari Kristus, "
"seperti darah domba yang tidak bercela atau bercak. (1 Petrus 1:17-19)\n"
"\n"
"Dalam Lukas 22:14-20 Yesus berkata: \"'Aku sangat rindu untuk makan Paskah "
"ini bersama kalian sebelum Aku menderita. Sebab Aku berkata kepadamu, Aku "
"tidak akan memakannya sampai hal itu tergenapi di dalam Kerajaan Allah.' "
"Lalu Ia mengambil cawan dan setelah mengucap syukur, Ia berkata, 'Ambillah "
"ini dan bagikanlah di antara kalian. Sebab Aku berkata kepadamu, mulai "
"sekarang Aku tidak akan minum buah anggur ini sampai Kerajaan Allah datang.' "
"Lalu Ia mengambil roti, setelah mengucap syukur, Ia memecahkannya dan "
"memberikannya kepada mereka sambil berkata, 'Inilah tubuh-Ku, yang diberikan "
"untuk kamu. Lakukanlah ini sebagai peringatan akan Aku.' Demikian pula cawan "
"itu setelah mereka makan, Ia berkata, 'Cawan ini yang dituangkan untuk kamu "
"adalah perjanjian baru dalam darah-Ku.'\" Berdoalah agar banyak keluarga di "
"tempat ini turut serta dalam perjanjian baru yang Yesus undang mereka masuk "
"melalui kematian, penguburan, dan kebangkitan-Nya."

msgid "Day 11: The Ten Commandments"
msgstr "Hari ke-11: Sepuluh Perintah Allah"

msgid ""
"Exodus 20:1–17 (ESV)\n"
"And God spoke all these words, saying, \"I am the LORD your God, who brought "
"you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery. \"You shall have "
"no other gods before me. \"You shall not make for yourself a carved image, "
"or any likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth "
"beneath, or that is in the water under the earth. You shall not bow down to "
"them or serve them, for I the LORD your God am a jealous God, visiting the "
"iniquity of the fathers on the children to the third and the fourth "
"generation of those who hate me, but showing steadfast love to thousands of "
"those who love me and keep my commandments. \"You shall not take the name of "
"the LORD your God in vain, for the LORD will not hold him guiltless who "
"takes his name in vain. \"Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy. Six "
"days you shall labor, and do all your work, but the seventh day is a Sabbath "
"to the LORD your God. On it you shall not do any work, you, or your son, or "
"your daughter, your male servant, or your female servant, or your livestock, "
"or the sojourner who is within your gates. For in six days the LORD made "
"heaven and earth, the sea, and all that is in them, and rested on the "
"seventh day. Therefore the LORD blessed the Sabbath day and made it holy. "
"\"Honor your father and your mother, that your days may be long in the land "
"that the LORD your God is giving you. \"You shall not murder. \"You shall "
"not commit adultery. \"You shall not steal. \"You shall not bear false "
"witness against your neighbor. \"You shall not covet your neighbor's house; "
"you shall not covet your neighbor's wife, or his male servant, or his female "
"servant, or his ox, or his donkey, or anything that is your neighbor's.\"\n"
"\n"
"Leviticus 6:1-7 (ESV)\n"
"The LORD spoke to Moses, saying, \"If anyone sins and commits a breach of "
"faith against the LORD by deceiving his neighbor in a matter of deposit or "
"security, or through robbery, or if he has oppressed his neighbor or has "
"found something lost and lied about it, swearing falsely—in any of all the "
"things that people do and sin thereby— if he has sinned and has realized his "
"guilt and will restore what he took by robbery or what he got by oppression "
"or the deposit that was committed to him or the lost thing that he found or "
"anything about which he has sworn falsely, he shall restore it in full and "
"shall add a fifth to it, and give it to him to whom it belongs on the day he "
"realizes his guilt. And he shall bring to the priest as his compensation to "
"the LORD a ram without blemish out of the flock, or its equivalent for a "
"guilt offering. And the priest shall make atonement for him before the LORD, "
"and he shall be forgiven for any of the things that one may do and thereby "
"become guilty.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God desires a relationship with His people that will reflect Him to the rest "
"of the world. As Creator, He institutes laws to help them live flourishing "
"lives as citizens in His Kingdom.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this land to view God's commandments not as "
"infringements upon their personal freedom, but as loving guardrails to "
"protect them.\n"
"\n"
"This passage also teaches us that God views our evil acts against others as "
"a breach of faith against the Lord.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims here to recognize the image of God in the people around "
"them and, out of obedience to God, to seek their good and not to take "
"advantage of them.\n"
"- Pray for recognition of all the times they have infringed on the rights of "
"others. May it convict them of their need of God's forgiveness."
msgstr ""
"Allah menginginkan hubungan dengan umat-Nya yang akan mencerminkan-Nya "
"kepada dunia. Sebagai Pencipta, Ia menetapkan hukum-hukum untuk membantu "
"mereka hidup sejahtera sebagai warga negara dalam Kerajaan-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di negeri ini memandang perintah Allah bukan "
"sebagai pelanggaran terhadap kebebasan pribadi mereka, tetapi sebagai pagar "
"cinta yang melindungi mereka.\n"
"\n"
"Ayat ini juga mengajarkan bahwa Allah memandang perbuatan jahat kita "
"terhadap orang lain sebagai pelanggaran iman terhadap Tuhan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di sini mengenali citra Allah dalam orang-orang "
"di sekitar mereka dan, karena ketaatan kepada Allah, mencari kebaikan mereka "
"dan tidak memanfaatkan mereka.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka menyadari semua kali mereka telah melanggar hak "
"orang lain. Semoga hal itu membuat mereka menyadari kebutuhan mereka akan "
"pengampunan Allah."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that humans are incredibly prone to worship things "
"that are not the one true God, the Creator of the heavens and the earth.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God's grace to bring Muslims in this land to repent of all the "
"ways they have treasured idols like money, comfort, esteem of man, self-"
"righteousness, and others.\n"
"- Pray for this conviction to drive them to the Good News of Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa manusia sangat rentan untuk menyembah "
"hal-hal yang bukan Allah yang benar, Pencipta langit dan bumi.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kasih karunia Allah membawa umat Muslim di negeri ini untuk "
"bertobat dari segala cara mereka menyembah berhala seperti uang, kenyamanan, "
"penghormatan manusia, kesombongan diri, dan lainnya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar keyakinan ini mendorong mereka kepada Kabar Baik Yesus."

msgid ""
"Amira is a Muslim from a neighboring country. She faces exploitation and "
"being taken advantage of often when she leaves her home. \"A taxi driver "
"tried to charge me four times the correct price and when I pushed back, he "
"said, 'You're a rich Muslim from another country, you have oil, you can "
"afford it.' I hate the people of this land and their underhanded ways.\" "
"Amira's experience reflects the brokenness and dishonesty that pervades when "
"people ignore God's commands.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for the dishonest financial deals, fraud, theft and lying that plague "
"humanity to reveal the true state of human nature and to drive Muslims in "
"this land to seek a real solution -- the new heart of flesh that God "
"promised in Ezekiel 36:26 to give to His people through Christ."
msgstr ""
"Amira adalah seorang Muslim dari negara tetangga. Ia sering menghadapi "
"eksploitasi dan dimanfaatkan saat meninggalkan rumahnya. \"Seorang sopir "
"taksi mencoba mematok harga empat kali lipat dari harga yang seharusnya, dan "
"ketika saya protes, dia berkata, 'Kamu Muslim kaya dari negara lain, kamu "
"punya minyak, kamu bisa membayarnya.' Saya benci orang-orang di negeri ini "
"dan cara-cara curang mereka.\" Pengalaman Amira mencerminkan kerusakan dan "
"ketidakjujuran yang merajalela ketika orang-orang mengabaikan perintah "
"Allah.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar transaksi keuangan yang curang, penipuan, pencurian, dan "
"kebohongan yang melanda umat manusia mengungkapkan keadaan sejati sifat "
"manusia dan mendorong Muslim di negeri ini untuk mencari solusi yang "
"sesungguhnya — hati daging yang baru yang dijanjikan Allah dalam Yehezkiel "
"36:26 untuk diberikan kepada umat-Nya melalui Kristus."

msgid ""
"The command not to take the name of the Lord in vain includes more than just "
"avoiding swearing; it also means not bearing God's name in an unworthy way. "
"Pray that Christians here would be known for living holy and respectful lives"
"—lives that reflect a genuine fear of God, love for all people, and bring "
"honor to the name of Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Perintah untuk tidak mengucapkan nama Tuhan dengan sia-sia tidak hanya "
"berarti menghindari kata-kata kasar; tetapi juga berarti tidak menggunakan "
"nama Tuhan dengan cara yang tidak pantas. Berdoalah agar orang-orang Kristen "
"di sini dikenal karena hidup yang kudus dan penuh hormat—hidup yang "
"mencerminkan ketakutan yang sejati kepada Tuhan, kasih kepada semua orang, "
"dan membawa kehormatan bagi nama Yesus."

msgid ""
"Paul explains in Romans 7:7, \"Yet if it had not been for the law, I would "
"not have known sin. For I would not have known what it is to covet if the "
"law had not said, 'You shall not covet.'\" He continues in verses 24 and 25, "
"\"Wretched man that I am, who will deliver me from this body of death? "
"Thanks be to God through Jesus Christ our Lord!\"\n"
"\n"
"Then in Romans 8:1-2, \"There is therefore now no condemnation for those who "
"are in Christ Jesus. For the law of the Spirit of life has set you free in "
"Christ Jesus from the law of sin and death.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray that Muslims would understand that God's moral standards and righteous "
"requirements reveal our inability to fully obey on our own, but that Jesus "
"came to set us free from the law of sin and death. Pray that they would "
"experience the same revelation Paul described in Romans 7 and 8."
msgstr ""
"Paulus menjelaskan dalam Roma 7:7, \"Namun, jika tidak ada hukum Taurat, aku "
"tidak akan tahu apa itu dosa. Sebab, aku tidak akan tahu apa artinya "
"menginginkan sesuatu jika hukum Taurat tidak berkata, 'Janganlah kamu "
"menginginkan.'\" Ia melanjutkan dalam ayat 24 dan 25, \"Celakalah aku ini! "
"Siapakah yang akan menyelamatkan aku dari tubuh maut ini? Terpujilah Allah "
"melalui Yesus Kristus, Tuhan kita!\"\n"
"\n"
"Kemudian dalam Roma 8:1-2, \"Oleh karena itu, tidak ada lagi penghukuman "
"bagi mereka yang ada dalam Kristus Yesus. Sebab hukum Roh yang menghidupkan "
"telah membebaskan kamu dalam Kristus Yesus dari hukum dosa dan maut.\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar umat Muslim memahami bahwa standar moral Allah dan tuntutan "
"kebenaran-Nya mengungkapkan ketidakmampuan kita untuk sepenuhnya taat dengan "
"kekuatan sendiri, tetapi Yesus datang untuk membebaskan kita dari hukum dosa "
"dan maut. Berdoalah agar mereka mengalami pengungkapan yang sama seperti "
"yang dijelaskan Paulus dalam Roma 7 dan 8."

msgid "Day 12: Cycles of Disobedience"
msgstr "Hari ke-12: Siklus Ketidaktaatan"

msgid ""
"Judges 2:10-23 (ESV)\n"
"And all that generation also were gathered to their fathers. And there arose "
"another generation after them who did not know the LORD or the work that he "
"had done for Israel. And the people of Israel did what was evil in the sight "
"of the LORD and served the Baals. And they abandoned the LORD, the God of "
"their fathers, who had brought them out of the land of Egypt. They went "
"after other gods, from among the gods of the peoples who were around them, "
"and bowed down to them. And they provoked the LORD to anger. They abandoned "
"the LORD and served the Baals and the Ashtaroth. So the anger of the LORD "
"was kindled against Israel, and he gave them over to plunderers, who "
"plundered them. And he sold them into the hand of their surrounding enemies, "
"so that they could no longer withstand their enemies. Whenever they marched "
"out, the hand of the LORD was against them for harm, as the LORD had warned, "
"and as the LORD had sworn to them. And they were in terrible distress. Then "
"the LORD raised up judges, who saved them out of the hand of those who "
"plundered them. Yet they did not listen to their judges, for they whored "
"after other gods and bowed down to them. They soon turned aside from the way "
"in which their fathers had walked, who had obeyed the commandments of the "
"LORD, and they did not do so. Whenever the LORD raised up judges for them, "
"the LORD was with the judge, and he saved them from the hand of their "
"enemies all the days of the judge. For the LORD was moved to pity by their "
"groaning because of those who afflicted and oppressed them. But whenever the "
"judge died, they turned back and were more corrupt than their fathers, going "
"after other gods, serving them and bowing down to them. They did not drop "
"any of their practices or their stubborn ways. So the anger of the LORD was "
"kindled against Israel, and he said, \"Because this people has transgressed "
"my covenant that I commanded their fathers and have not obeyed my voice, I "
"will no longer drive out before them any of the nations that Joshua left "
"when he died, in order to test Israel by them, whether they will take care "
"to walk in the way of the LORD as their fathers did, or not.\" So the LORD "
"left those nations, not driving them out quickly, and he did not give them "
"into the hand of Joshua."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God is both personal and emotional. In this passage, we see both His anger "
"and compassion motivating Him to act on behalf of His people. We also see "
"that God allows people to choose whom they will love and serve. When they "
"reject Him and follow other gods, he releases them to the consequences of "
"their decisions.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God's true nature to be made known in this place -- His holiness "
"and His love, His compassion and His justice -- and for people to understand "
"how these characteristics are perfectly consistent with one another.\n"
"- Pray for repentance from reshaping God into a more comfortable image, and "
"for hearts to allow Him to speak directly through His Word.\n"
"- Pray that when Muslims read the Bible, God's Word and His character would "
"be clearly understood."
msgstr ""
"Allah adalah pribadi dan penuh kasih sayang. Dalam ayat ini, kita melihat "
"baik kemarahan-Nya maupun belas kasihan-Nya yang mendorong-Nya bertindak "
"demi umat-Nya. Kita juga melihat bahwa Allah membiarkan manusia memilih "
"siapa yang akan mereka cintai dan layani. Ketika mereka menolak-Nya dan "
"mengikuti dewa-dewa lain, Ia membiarkan mereka menghadapi konsekuensi dari "
"keputusan mereka.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar sifat sejati Allah dikenal di tempat ini — kekudusan-Nya "
"dan kasih-Nya, belas kasihan-Nya dan keadilan-Nya — dan agar orang-orang "
"memahami bagaimana karakteristik-karakteristik ini saling konsisten satu "
"sama lain.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ada pertobatan dari upaya untuk membentuk Allah menjadi "
"gambar yang lebih nyaman, dan agar hati-hati mereka membiarkan-Nya berbicara "
"langsung melalui Firman-Nya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ketika Muslim membaca Alkitab, Firman Allah dan karakter-"
"Nya dapat dipahami dengan jelas."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that humanity is quick to forget the works of God in "
"their lives and are easily influenced by the beliefs of those around them. "
"Instead of remembering God's faithfulness, people often drift toward what is "
"popular, familiar, or culturally accepted.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up countercultural people who would resist the ease "
"of following the tide of culture in order to pursue truth and "
"righteousness.\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to repent of idols such as comfort, "
"security, money, relationships, and the approval of others, and to choose "
"instead the covenant-keeping God who delivers them from the bondage to these "
"lesser gods."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa manusia dengan cepat melupakan karya-"
"karya Allah dalam hidup mereka dan mudah terpengaruh oleh keyakinan orang-"
"orang di sekitar mereka. Alih-alih mengingat kesetiaan Allah, orang-orang "
"sering kali terombang-ambing menuju hal-hal yang populer, familiar, atau "
"diterima secara budaya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mengangkat orang-orang yang berlawanan dengan budaya, "
"yang akan menentang kemudahan mengikuti arus budaya demi mengejar kebenaran "
"dan keadilan.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini bertobat dari berhala-berhala "
"seperti kenyamanan, keamanan, uang, hubungan, dan persetujuan orang lain, "
"dan memilih Allah yang setia pada perjanjian-Nya yang membebaskan mereka "
"dari perbudakan terhadap berhala-berhala yang lebih rendah ini."

msgid ""
"Picking olives far out in the country one crisp December morning, Naima, a "
"single woman home on vacation, eagerly shared her thoughts with her family "
"and the visitor in their midst. She talked about angels, evil spirits, the "
"healing power of the Qur'an, and her convictions about true religion. When "
"one of the other olive pickers shared about her faith in the Messiah, Naima "
"immediately responded, \"You Christians worship three gods.\" \"No,\" the "
"believer replied, \"we worship one God.\" \"What about the Trinity?\" Naima "
"accused. The visitor replied, \"If you want to understand that you need to "
"take the time to actually read God's Holy Word and understand the plan He "
"has given to return us back to him in relationship.\" To this Naima "
"dismissively responded, \"The Bible is corrupted. The Jews changed God's "
"word because they didn't like it and that's why God sent the Qur'an.\"\n"
"\n"
"This memorized argument is repeated all around the world, often without "
"understanding its validity or understanding that God's Word does not change "
"or fail. True prophets call people back to the truth of His Word, they do "
"not invent new truth.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims to grow dissatisfied with rehearsed answers and to "
"courageously engage in critical thinking about what they have been taught.\n"
"- Pray that this journey would lead them to encounter truth in God's Word."
msgstr ""
"Pada suatu pagi yang cerah di bulan Desember, Naima, seorang wanita lajang "
"yang sedang berlibur di kampung halamannya, dengan antusias berbagi "
"pemikirannya dengan keluarganya dan seorang tamu yang berada di tengah-"
"tengah mereka. Ia berbicara tentang malaikat, roh jahat, kekuatan "
"penyembuhan Al-Qur'an, dan keyakinannya tentang agama yang benar. Ketika "
"salah satu pemetik zaitun lainnya berbagi tentang imannya kepada Mesias, "
"Naima langsung menanggapi, \"Kalian orang Kristen menyembah tiga dewa.\" "
"\"Tidak,\" jawab orang beriman itu, \"kami menyembah satu Tuhan.\" "
"\"Bagaimana dengan Tritunggal?\" Naima menuduh. Tamu itu menjawab, \"Jika "
"kamu ingin memahami itu, kamu perlu meluangkan waktu untuk benar-benar "
"membaca Firman Suci Allah dan memahami rencana-Nya untuk membawa kita "
"kembali kepada-Nya dalam hubungan.\" Naima menanggapi dengan sinis, "
"\"Alkitab telah diselewengkan. Orang Yahudi mengubah Firman Allah karena "
"mereka tidak menyukainya, dan itulah mengapa Allah mengutus Al-Qur'an.\"\n"
"\n"
"Argumen yang dihafal ini diulang di seluruh dunia, seringkali tanpa memahami "
"validitasnya atau memahami bahwa Firman Allah tidak berubah atau gagal. Nabi-"
"nabi sejati memanggil orang kembali kepada kebenaran Firman-Nya, mereka "
"tidak menciptakan kebenaran baru.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim menjadi tidak puas dengan jawaban yang dihafal "
"dan berani berpikir kritis tentang apa yang telah diajarkan kepada mereka.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar perjalanan ini membawa mereka untuk bertemu dengan "
"kebenaran dalam firman Allah."

msgid ""
"This passage reminds us that God does not have grandchildren. He only has "
"children. Faith must be personally owned, not merely inherited.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for believers in this land to authentically live out and pass on "
"their faith to the next generation.\n"
"- Pray for them to faithfully share their testimony of God's redeeming work "
"in their lives. Pray that they would continually remind themselves and their "
"children of God's living and active power.\n"
"- Ask that children of believers would encounter God personally and develop "
"their own stories of the work of God in their lives that will root them "
"deeply in Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengingatkan kita bahwa Allah tidak memiliki cucu. Dia hanya "
"memiliki anak-anak. Iman harus dimiliki secara pribadi, bukan sekadar "
"diwariskan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya di negeri ini dapat hidup sesuai iman "
"mereka dengan tulus dan meneruskannya kepada generasi berikutnya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka dapat berbagi kesaksian tentang karya penebusan "
"Allah dalam hidup mereka dengan setia. Berdoalah agar mereka terus "
"mengingatkan diri mereka sendiri dan anak-anak mereka tentang kuasa Allah "
"yang hidup dan aktif.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar anak-anak orang percaya dapat bertemu dengan Allah secara "
"pribadi dan mengembangkan kisah mereka sendiri tentang karya Allah dalam "
"hidup mereka, yang akan menanamkan mereka dengan kokoh dalam Yesus."

msgid ""
"In Acts 13, Paul and his companions arrive in Antioch in Pisidia. On the "
"Sabbath, they went into the synagogue and sat down. They began retelling "
"Israel's story, including the story found in our previous passage in "
"Judges.\n"
"\n"
"\"For forty years he put up with them in the wilderness, and after "
"destroying seven nations in the land of Canaan, he gave them their land as "
"an inheritance. All this took about 450 years, and after that he gave them "
"judges until Samuel the prophet...\" (Acts 13:18-20) They continued the "
"story through to Christ, declaring: \"Let it be known to you, therefore, "
"brothers, that through this man, Jesus, forgiveness of sins is proclaimed to "
"you, and by him everyone who believes is freed from everything from which "
"you could not be freed by the law of Moses.\"\n"
"\n"
"Their message received mixed responses. Paul and Barnabas were opposed by "
"some, yet Acts 13:48-49 tells us: \"as many as were appointed to eternal "
"life believed. And the word of the Lord was spreading throughout the whole "
"region.\" Pray for believers to be empowered to preach boldly whether they "
"are reviled or whether the Word of the Lord spreads rapidly, trusting God "
"with the outcome."
msgstr ""
"Dalam Kisah Para Rasul 13, Paulus dan teman-temannya tiba di Antiokhia di "
"Pisidia. Pada hari Sabat, mereka masuk ke sinagoga dan duduk. Mereka mulai "
"menceritakan kembali kisah Israel, termasuk kisah yang terdapat dalam bagian "
"sebelumnya di Kitab Hakim-hakim.\n"
"\n"
"\"Selama empat puluh tahun Ia menanggung mereka di padang gurun, dan setelah "
"menghancurkan tujuh bangsa di tanah Kanaan, Ia memberikan tanah itu kepada "
"mereka sebagai warisan. Semua ini memakan waktu sekitar 450 tahun, dan "
"setelah itu Ia memberikan mereka hakim-hakim hingga Samuel sang nabi...\" "
"(Kisah Para Rasul 13:18-20) Mereka melanjutkan kisah itu hingga kepada "
"Kristus, menyatakan: \"Hendaklah kamu tahu, saudara-saudara, bahwa melalui "
"orang ini, Yesus, pengampunan dosa diproklamasikan kepada kamu, dan oleh "
"Dia, setiap orang yang percaya dibebaskan dari segala sesuatu yang tidak "
"dapat kamu bebaskan oleh hukum Musa.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pesan mereka mendapat tanggapan yang beragam. Paulus dan Barnabas ditentang "
"oleh sebagian orang, namun Kisah Para Rasul 13:48-49 memberitahukan: \"Semua "
"yang telah ditentukan untuk hidup kekal percaya. Dan firman Tuhan tersebar "
"ke seluruh daerah itu.\" Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya diberi kekuatan "
"untuk memberitakan firman Tuhan dengan berani, baik ketika mereka dihina "
"maupun ketika firman Tuhan tersebar dengan cepat, sambil mempercayakan "
"hasilnya kepada Allah."

msgid "Day 13: The Suffering Servant of Christ"
msgstr "Hari ke-13: Hamba yang Menderita Kristus"

msgid ""
"Isaiah 52:13-53:12 (ESV)\n"
"Behold, my servant shall act wisely; he shall be high and lifted up, and "
"shall be exalted. Who has believed what he has heard from us? And to whom "
"has the arm of the LORD been revealed? For he grew up before him like a "
"young plant, and like a root out of dry ground; he had no form or majesty "
"that we should look at him, and no beauty that we should desire him. He was "
"despised and rejected by men; a man of sorrows, and acquainted with grief; "
"and as one from whom men hide their faces he was despised, and we esteemed "
"him not. Surely he has borne our griefs and carried our sorrows; yet we "
"esteemed him stricken, smitten by God, and afflicted. But he was wounded for "
"our transgressions; he was crushed for our iniquities; upon him was the "
"chastisement that brought us peace, and with his stripes we are healed. All "
"we like sheep have gone astray; we have turned—every one—to his own way; and "
"the LORD has laid on him the iniquity of us all. He was oppressed, and he "
"was afflicted, yet he opened not his mouth; like a lamb that is led to the "
"slaughter, and like a sheep that before its shearers is silent, so he opened "
"not his mouth. By oppression and judgment he was taken away; and as for his "
"generation, who considered that he was cut off out of the land of the "
"living, stricken for the transgression of my people? And they made his grave "
"with the wicked and with a rich man in his death, although he had done no "
"violence, and there was no deceit in his mouth. Yet it was the will of the "
"LORD to crush him; he has put him to grief; when his soul makes an offering "
"for guilt, he shall see his offspring; he shall prolong his days; the will "
"of the LORD shall prosper in his hand. Out of the anguish of his soul he "
"shall see and be satisfied; by his knowledge shall the righteous one, my "
"servant, make many to be accounted righteous, and he shall bear their "
"iniquities. Therefore I will divide him a portion with the many, and he "
"shall divide the spoil with the strong, because he poured out his soul to "
"death and was numbered with the transgressors; yet he bore the sin of many, "
"and makes intercession for the transgressors."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The suffering servant described in this passage was despised, rejected, and "
"familiar with pain. Yet it is with His wounds that we are healed. He was "
"silent when He was oppressed, taken away, and killed. He was neither "
"deceitful nor violent. Yet it was God's will that He be crushed, for He bore "
"the sins of many and makes intercession for us before the Father. Isaiah's "
"prophecy would be fulfilled in the life and death of Jesus hundreds of years "
"later. God was intentional in His plan for redemption.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for many in this place to grasp the importance of the prophecy found "
"in Isaiah 52 and 53.\n"
"- Pray for the realization that Jesus' fulfillment of this prophecy "
"testifies to the claims He made to be the Son of God. May they marvel at a "
"God who is able to put all things in place at the perfect time."
msgstr ""
"Hamba yang menderita yang digambarkan dalam ayat ini dihina, ditolak, dan "
"akrab dengan penderitaan. Namun, dengan luka-lukanya itulah kita "
"disembuhkan. Ia diam ketika ditindas, dibawa pergi, dan dibunuh. Ia tidak "
"curang maupun kekerasan. Namun, itulah kehendak Allah bahwa Ia dihancurkan, "
"sebab Ia menanggung dosa banyak orang dan berdoa bagi kita di hadapan Bapa. "
"Nubuat Yesaya akan tergenapi dalam hidup dan kematian Yesus ratusan tahun "
"kemudian. Allah memiliki rencana yang sengaja dalam rencana penebusan-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar banyak orang di tempat ini memahami pentingnya nubuat yang "
"terdapat dalam Yesaya 52 dan 53.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka menyadari bahwa pemenuhan nubuat ini oleh Yesus "
"membuktikan klaim-Nya sebagai Anak Allah. Semoga mereka kagum pada Allah "
"yang mampu menempatkan segala sesuatu pada waktu yang tepat."

msgid ""
"Humans sin; we all go our own way. A Holy God could not tolerate our "
"sinfulness and our relationship with Him is broken. One result of this "
"brokenness is the suffering and pain we experience in this life. However, we "
"have hope because God had a plan to send His servant to bear our sins for "
"us. He sent Jesus to intercede for us so that relationship might be "
"restored.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that Muslims would understand how this prophecy relates to them and "
"that it pointed to the coming of Jesus. Pray that this foretelling would "
"create a vivid picture of the sacrifice Jesus made for us."
msgstr ""
"Manusia berdosa; kita semua berjalan menurut jalan masing-masing. Allah yang "
"Kudus tidak dapat mentolerir kejahatan kita, dan hubungan kita dengan-Nya "
"terputus. Salah satu akibat dari pemutusan ini adalah penderitaan dan "
"kesakitan yang kita alami dalam hidup ini. Namun, kita memiliki harapan "
"karena Allah telah merencanakan untuk mengutus hamba-Nya untuk menanggung "
"dosa-dosa kita. Ia mengutus Yesus untuk berdoa bagi kita agar hubungan itu "
"dapat dipulihkan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim memahami bagaimana nubuat ini berkaitan dengan "
"mereka dan bahwa nubuat itu menunjuk pada kedatangan Yesus. Berdoalah agar "
"nubuat ini menciptakan gambaran yang jelas tentang pengorbanan yang Yesus "
"lakukan untuk kita."

msgid ""
"Khadija cried out, \"God doesn't see. He doesn't care. My children are "
"mocked at school. My husband has abandoned us. We sleep in the car. I can't "
"get a job because of lies that are being told about me.\" Khadija's cry "
"reflects the pain of those who feel unseen and abandoned.\n"
"\n"
"O Jesus, thank you that you do see, and not only do you see, you understand. "
"You have been rejected, lied about, mocked. You lived homeless and were a "
"refugee as a baby. Thank you for carrying our sorrows. You not only know the "
"sin of the world, but they were all laid upon you on the cross. Thank you, "
"Lord, that you received each lash of the whip, each tearing of the thorn, "
"each nail, knowing that these very wounds would heal us. Please Lord, let "
"Muslims see that you are not a God who remains far away waiting for them to "
"rescue themselves with their self-righteousness. You came, knowing that we "
"were sinners and helpless, and you suffered so that we could live. Please "
"Lord, may Muslims see this irresistible love."
msgstr ""
"Khadija berteriak, \"Tuhan tidak melihat. Dia tidak peduli. Anak-anakku "
"diejek di sekolah. Suamiku telah meninggalkan kami. Kami tidur di mobil. Aku "
"tidak bisa mendapatkan pekerjaan karena kebohongan yang disebarkan "
"tentangku.\" Teriakan Khadija mencerminkan penderitaan mereka yang merasa "
"tidak dilihat dan ditinggalkan.\n"
"\n"
"Ya Yesus, terima kasih karena Engkau melihat, dan tidak hanya melihat, "
"tetapi juga mengerti. Engkau telah ditolak, dibohongi, dan diejek. Engkau "
"hidup tanpa tempat tinggal dan menjadi pengungsi saat masih bayi. Terima "
"kasih karena Engkau menanggung kesedihan kami. Engkau tidak hanya tahu dosa "
"dunia, tetapi semua dosa itu diletakkan atas Engkau di salib. Terima kasih, "
"Tuhan, bahwa Engkau menerima setiap cambukan, setiap duri yang menusuk, "
"setiap paku, mengetahui bahwa luka-luka ini akan menyembuhkan kami. Tolong, "
"Tuhan, biarkan umat Muslim melihat bahwa Engkau bukanlah Tuhan yang jauh dan "
"menunggu mereka menyelamatkan diri dengan keangkuhan mereka sendiri. Engkau "
"datang, mengetahui bahwa kami adalah pendosa dan lemah, dan Engkau menderita "
"agar kami dapat hidup. Tolong, Tuhan, biarkan umat Muslim melihat cinta yang "
"tak tertahankan ini."

msgid ""
"Approximately 700 years before the Word came to earth as Jesus, the Spirit "
"inspired the prophet Isaiah to write clearly about the One who would come to "
"redeem us.\n"
"\n"
"- May Christians share this passage with those who do not yet believe, "
"revealing God's loving deliberate plan to come and rescue us Himself.\n"
"- Pray for God's children in this place to be willing to boldly speak the "
"difficult-to-hear news that \"all have gone astray.\" There are none who are "
"righteous. May believers quickly follow that piercing truth with the gospel "
"that God Himself came to bear our sin. He chose death so that we could live."
msgstr ""
"Sekitar 700 tahun sebelum Firman Allah datang ke dunia sebagai Yesus, Roh "
"Kudus mengilhami nabi Yesaya untuk menulis dengan jelas tentang Dia yang "
"akan datang untuk menebus kita.\n"
"\n"
"- Semoga orang-orang Kristen membagikan ayat ini kepada mereka yang belum "
"percaya, mengungkapkan rencana kasih Allah yang sengaja datang untuk "
"menyelamatkan kita sendiri.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar anak-anak Allah di tempat ini bersedia dengan berani "
"menyampaikan kabar yang sulit didengar bahwa \"semua telah sesat.\" Tidak "
"ada yang benar. Semoga orang-orang percaya segera mengikuti kebenaran yang "
"menusuk itu dengan Injil bahwa Allah sendiri datang untuk menanggung dosa "
"kita. Ia memilih kematian agar kita dapat hidup."

msgid ""
"Hebrews 4:15-16 says, \"For we do not have a high priest who is unable to "
"empathize with our weaknesses, but we have one who has been tempted in every "
"way, just as we are – yet he did not sin. Let us then approach God's throne "
"of grace with confidence so that we may receive mercy and find grace to help "
"us in our time of need.\"\n"
"\n"
"There is only One who has never sinned. He chose to live as a human on this "
"earth, understanding and carrying our pain, even unto death. He made a way "
"for us to come right into the throne room of the King where we find grace to "
"help us.\n"
"\n"
"Thank the Lord for the incredible privilege we have to enter into His throne "
"room to intercede on behalf of Muslims, not because of anything we have done "
"but solely because of His grace."
msgstr ""
"Ibrani 4:15-16 berkata, \"Sebab kita tidak mempunyai Imam Besar yang tidak "
"dapat merasakan kelemahan kita, tetapi kita mempunyai Imam Besar yang telah "
"dicobai dalam segala hal sama seperti kita – namun Ia tidak berbuat dosa. "
"Marilah kita mendekati takhta kasih karunia Allah dengan penuh keyakinan, "
"supaya kita menerima rahmat dan menemukan kasih karunia yang menolong kita "
"pada waktu kita membutuhkan.\"\n"
"\n"
"Hanya ada Satu yang tidak pernah berbuat dosa. Ia memilih untuk hidup "
"sebagai manusia di bumi ini, memahami dan menanggung penderitaan kita, "
"bahkan sampai mati. Ia membuka jalan bagi kita untuk masuk ke dalam ruang "
"tahta Raja, di mana kita menemukan kasih karunia untuk menolong kita.\n"
"\n"
"Syukurlah kepada Tuhan atas anugerah yang luar biasa ini, bahwa kita dapat "
"masuk ke dalam ruang tahta-Nya untuk berdoa bagi umat Muslim, bukan karena "
"apa yang telah kita lakukan, tetapi semata-mata karena kasih karunia-Nya."

msgid "Day 14: The Promised Savior"
msgstr "Hari ke-14: Penyelamat yang Dijanjikan"

msgid ""
"Isaiah 9:1-7 (ESV)\n"
"But there will be no gloom for her who was in anguish. In the former time he "
"brought into contempt the land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali, but in "
"the latter time he has made glorious the way of the sea, the land beyond the "
"Jordan, Galilee of the nations. The people who walked in darkness have seen "
"a great light; those who dwelt in a land of deep darkness, on them has light "
"shined. You have multiplied the nation; you have increased its joy; they "
"rejoice before you as with joy at the harvest, as they are glad when they "
"divide the spoil. For the yoke of his burden, and the staff for his "
"shoulder, the rod of his oppressor, you have broken as on the day of Midian. "
"For every boot of the tramping warrior in battle tumult and every garment "
"rolled in blood will be burned as fuel for the fire. For to us a child is "
"born, to us a son is given; and the government shall be upon his shoulder, "
"and his name shall be called Wonderful Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting "
"Father, Prince of Peace. Of the increase of his government and of peace "
"there will be no end, on the throne of David and over his kingdom, to "
"establish it and to uphold it with justice and with righteousness from this "
"time forth and forevermore. The zeal of the LORD of hosts will do this.\n"
"\n"
"Luke 1:26-38 (ESV)\n"
"In the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a city of Galilee "
"named Nazareth, to a virgin betrothed to a man whose name was Joseph, of the "
"house of David. And the virgin's name was Mary. And he came to her and said, "
"\"Greetings, O favored one, the Lord is with you!\" But she was greatly "
"troubled at the saying, and tried to discern what sort of greeting this "
"might be. And the angel said to her, \"Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have "
"found favor with God. And behold, you will conceive in your womb and bear a "
"son, and you shall call his name Jesus. He will be great and will be called "
"the Son of the Most High. And the Lord God will give to him the throne of "
"his father David, and he will reign over the house of Jacob forever, and of "
"his kingdom there will be no end.\" And Mary said to the angel, \"How will "
"this be, since I am a virgin?\" And the angel answered her, \"The Holy "
"Spirit will come upon you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow "
"you; therefore the child to be born will be called holy—the Son of God. And "
"behold, your relative Elizabeth in her old age has also conceived a son, and "
"this is the sixth month with her who was called barren. For nothing will be "
"impossible with God.\" And Mary said, \"Behold, I am the servant of the "
"Lord; let it be to me according to your word.\" And the angel departed from "
"her."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Isaiah 9 describes a heroic Savior who comes to bring light and peace where "
"there was death, captivity, and darkness. He will reign as the perfect king, "
"full of justice and righteousness. We see the initial fulfillment of this "
"prophecy in Luke 1 as God's plan for this Savior begins to unfold. God sends "
"an angelic messenger to announce the upcoming birth of a humble human baby, "
"Jesus. While fully human, the baby carried by Mary was conceived by the "
"power of the Holy Spirit and was the Son of God.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims walking in darkness to see the Great Light, Jesus, "
"prophesied in Isaiah.\n"
"- Pray that they could experience the joy the angelic messenger expressed "
"when announcing the upcoming birth of the Son of God that marked the "
"fulfillment of this long awaited eternal King who would rule with justice "
"and righteousness."
msgstr ""
"Yesaya 9 menggambarkan seorang Penyelamat yang heroik yang datang untuk "
"membawa terang dan damai di tempat yang sebelumnya dipenuhi oleh kematian, "
"penawanan, dan kegelapan. Ia akan memerintah sebagai raja yang sempurna, "
"penuh dengan keadilan dan kebenaran. Kita melihat pemenuhan awal nubuat ini "
"dalam Lukas 1 ketika rencana Allah untuk Penyelamat ini mulai terwujud. "
"Allah mengutus seorang utusan malaikat untuk mengumumkan kelahiran seorang "
"bayi manusia yang rendah hati, Yesus. Meskipun sepenuhnya manusia, bayi yang "
"dikandung Maria dikandung oleh kuasa Roh Kudus dan adalah Anak Allah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang Muslim yang hidup dalam kegelapan dapat melihat "
"Terang yang Besar, Yesus, yang diramalkan dalam Yesaya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka dapat mengalami sukacita yang diungkapkan oleh "
"utusan malaikat ketika mengumumkan kelahiran Anak Allah yang menandai "
"terpenuhinya Raja Abadi yang dinantikan lama yang akan memerintah dengan "
"keadilan dan kebenaran."

msgid ""
"Humanity is separated from God, walking in darkness. Our Creator God sees "
"our great need and, instead of abandoning us, He draws near, offering us the "
"gift of His only Son. The Light enters the world in a most unexpected way. "
"He becomes one of us.\n"
"\n"
"God, we know that we are not who You created us to be. We are separated from "
"You with no hope of accessing You on our own. We stumble in the darkness, "
"slaves to our sins and hurting one another. We praise You for being the King "
"above all, the One who came down to us and gave us hope, destroying what "
"holds us captive and making us holy. We ask that this land would learn who "
"You are and what You did for us, because You came to set them free, as well."
msgstr ""
"Manusia terpisah dari Allah, berjalan dalam kegelapan. Allah Pencipta kita "
"melihat kebutuhan besar kita dan, alih-alih meninggalkan kita, Ia mendekat, "
"menawarkan kita hadiah Anak-Nya yang tunggal. Cahaya masuk ke dunia dengan "
"cara yang paling tak terduga. Ia menjadi salah satu dari kita.\n"
"\n"
"Allah, kami tahu bahwa kami bukanlah siapa yang Engkau ciptakan. Kami "
"terpisah dari Engkau tanpa harapan untuk mendekati-Mu dengan kekuatan kami "
"sendiri. Kita tersandung dalam kegelapan, menjadi budak dosa-dosa kita dan "
"saling menyakiti. Kita memuji-Mu sebagai Raja di atas segala raja, Yang "
"telah turun kepada kita dan memberikan harapan, menghancurkan apa yang "
"menahan kita, dan menjadikan kita kudus. Kami memohon agar negeri ini "
"belajar mengenal siapa Engkau dan apa yang Engkau lakukan bagi kami, karena "
"Engkau datang untuk membebaskan mereka juga."

msgid ""
"The Qur'an denies the Divine Sonship of Christ and the concept of the "
"Trinity. These concepts are common Muslim arguments against Christianity. "
"However, when the Holy Spirit opens eyes, understanding can break through.\n"
"\n"
"Majid had been listening to the witness of a Christian friend and was "
"thinking through his testimony that Jesus was God, come to earth, One with "
"the Father and the Holy Spirit. As he processed aloud he said, \"If I "
"believe God is with me here in my city, and at the same time with my mother "
"in the countryside, I recognize that He is not bound to one place. God the "
"Father can be in heaven and God the Son, Jesus, can be on earth, and God the "
"Spirit can live in us. There are not three gods. There is one God, not bound "
"by place. Just as you can hear an audio message and say, 'This is so-and-"
"so's voice…' Jesus is the Spoken Word sent from God that we might hear Him."
"\" Majid declared his faith in Jesus that very evening.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the Lord to open the eyes and ears of Muslims who have held the "
"argument against the idea of one God in three distinct Persons, Father, Son, "
"and Holy Spirit.\n"
"- Pray that the Lord would reveal to them the astounding way the entire "
"Bible points to the coming of the Eternal One, the Son of God, given as a "
"sacrifice for us."
msgstr ""
"Al-Qur'an menolak konsep Keilahian Anak Allah dan Trinitas. Konsep-konsep "
"ini merupakan argumen umum umat Islam terhadap Kristen. Namun, ketika Roh "
"Kudus membuka mata, pemahaman dapat terpecahkan.\n"
"\n"
"Majid telah mendengarkan kesaksian seorang teman Kristen dan memikirkan "
"kesaksiannya bahwa Yesus adalah Allah yang datang ke dunia, satu dengan Bapa "
"dan Roh Kudus. Saat ia memprosesnya secara lisan, ia berkata, \"Jika aku "
"percaya Allah ada bersamaku di kota ini, dan pada saat yang sama bersamaku "
"di pedesaan, aku menyadari bahwa Dia tidak terikat pada satu tempat. Allah "
"Bapa dapat berada di surga, Allah Anak, Yesus, dapat berada di bumi, dan "
"Allah Roh Kudus dapat tinggal di dalam kita. Tidak ada tiga Allah. Ada satu "
"Allah, yang tidak terikat oleh tempat. Sama seperti kamu dapat mendengar "
"pesan audio dan berkata, 'Ini suara si anu…' Yesus adalah Firman yang "
"diucapkan oleh Allah agar kita dapat mendengarnya.\" Majid menyatakan "
"imannya kepada Yesus pada malam itu juga.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Tuhan membuka mata dan telinga umat Muslim yang telah "
"menentang gagasan tentang satu Allah dalam tiga Pribadi yang berbeda, Bapa, "
"Anak, dan Roh Kudus.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Tuhan menyingkapkan kepada mereka cara yang mengagumkan "
"bagaimana seluruh Alkitab menunjuk pada kedatangan Yang Kekal, Anak Allah, "
"yang diberikan sebagai korban bagi kita."

msgid ""
"Christians play a key role in showing Muslims, who are walking in darkness, "
"the bright light of Christ in them.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that they may have joy, peace, and wisdom while reaching this land.\n"
"- Pray that though the concept of one God in three Persons is difficult to "
"grasp and share, may they delight in its mystery and truth. May their faith "
"in the truth of this profound reality be a beacon of light that draws those "
"walking in darkness."
msgstr ""
"Kristen memainkan peran penting dalam menunjukkan kepada umat Muslim yang "
"hidup dalam kegelapan, cahaya terang Kristus yang ada di dalam diri mereka.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka dapat merasakan sukacita, damai sejahtera, dan "
"kebijaksanaan saat memasuki tanah ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar meskipun konsep tentang satu Allah dalam tiga Pribadi sulit "
"dipahami dan dibagikan, mereka dapat menikmati misteri dan kebenarannya. "
"Semoga iman mereka terhadap kebenaran realitas yang mendalam ini menjadi "
"cahaya penuntun yang menarik mereka yang hidup dalam kegelapan."

msgid ""
"1 Corinthians 2:6-16 describes the wisdom of God, hidden in a mystery, that "
"God determined before the ages for our glory: \"What no eye has seen, nor "
"ear heard, nor the heart of man imagined, what God has prepared for those "
"who love him.\" Yet, \"these things God has revealed to us through the "
"Spirit.\" Paul explains that, \"The natural person does not accept the "
"things of the Spirit of God, for they are folly to him, and he is not able "
"to understand them because they are spiritually discerned.\" He concludes, "
"\"'For who has understood the mind of the Lord so as to instruct him?' But "
"we have the mind of Christ.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray that the Lord will reveal to Muslims the mystery that can only be "
"understood by revelation of the Spirit of God. Ask that they would find "
"peace in recognizing we cannot fully understand God's mind, yet rejoice that "
"through Christ we are given the mind of Christ."
msgstr ""
"1 Korintus 2:6-16 menggambarkan hikmat Allah yang tersembunyi dalam misteri, "
"yang telah Allah tetapkan sebelum dunia diciptakan untuk kemuliaan kita: "
"\"Apa yang mata belum pernah melihat, telinga belum pernah mendengar, dan "
"hati manusia belum pernah membayangkan, itulah yang Allah siapkan bagi "
"mereka yang mengasihi-Nya.\" Namun, \"hal-hal ini Allah telah nyatakan "
"kepada kita melalui Roh.\" Paulus menjelaskan bahwa, \"Orang duniawi tidak "
"menerima hal-hal Roh Allah, karena bagi mereka hal itu adalah kebodohan, dan "
"mereka tidak mampu memahaminya karena hal itu hanya dapat dipahami secara "
"rohani.\" Ia menyimpulkan, \"'Siapakah yang telah memahami pikiran Tuhan "
"sehingga dapat mengajar-Nya?' Tetapi kita memiliki pikiran Kristus.\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar Tuhan mengungkapkan kepada umat Muslim rahasia yang hanya "
"dapat dipahami melalui pengungkapan Roh Allah. Mintalah agar mereka "
"menemukan damai dalam menyadari bahwa kita tidak dapat sepenuhnya memahami "
"pikiran Allah, namun bersukacita karena melalui Kristus kita diberikan "
"pikiran Kristus."

msgid "Day 15: The Birth of Jesus"
msgstr "Hari ke-15: Kelahiran Yesus"

msgid ""
"Luke 2:1-20 (ESV)\n"
"In those days a decree went out from Caesar Augustus that all the world "
"should be registered. This was the first registration when Quirinius was "
"governor of Syria. And all went to be registered, each to his own town. And "
"Joseph also went up from Galilee, from the town of Nazareth, to Judea, to "
"the city of David, which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house "
"and lineage of David, to be registered with Mary, his betrothed, who was "
"with child. And while they were there, the time came for her to give birth. "
"And she gave birth to her firstborn son and wrapped him in swaddling cloths "
"and laid him in a manger, because there was no place for them in the inn. "
"And in the same region there were shepherds out in the field, keeping watch "
"over their flock by night. And an angel of the Lord appeared to them, and "
"the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were filled with fear. And "
"the angel said to them, \"Fear not, for behold, I bring you good news of "
"great joy that will be for all the people. For unto you is born this day in "
"the city of David a Savior, who is Christ the Lord. And this will be a sign "
"for you: you will find a baby wrapped in swaddling cloths and lying in a "
"manger.\" And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly "
"host praising God and saying, \"Glory to God in the highest, and on earth "
"peace among those with whom he is pleased!\" When the angels went away from "
"them into heaven, the shepherds said to one another, \"Let us go over to "
"Bethlehem and see this thing that has happened, which the Lord has made "
"known to us.\" And they went with haste and found Mary and Joseph, and the "
"baby lying in a manger. And when they saw it, they made known the saying "
"that had been told them concerning this child. And all who heard it wondered "
"at what the shepherds told them. But Mary treasured up all these things, "
"pondering them in her heart. And the shepherds returned, glorifying and "
"praising God for all they had heard and seen, as it had been told them."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God is both just and loving. In this passage, we see that Jesus—the Anointed "
"One and God Himself—enters the world in humility. He is born not into wealth "
"or power, but into obscurity. His birth is announced not to kings or "
"religious elites, but to shepherds—men of the lowest social status. In doing "
"so, God reveals His heart: Jesus did not come only for the rich, the "
"powerful, or the respected, but also for the poor, the weak, the overlooked, "
"and sinners.\n"
"\n"
"Jesus is Lord, Messiah, Savior, and King. He is sovereign over all things, "
"the promised Anointed One, the only Rescuer, and the everlasting King from "
"the line of David.\n"
"\n"
"- Praise God and give him glory for doing what we could never do for "
"ourselves—reconciling us to Himself.\n"
"- Pray for many in this place to receive God's offer of peace to those who "
"place their trust in His Son, who came to us as a baby.\n"
"- Because of God's great love and mercy, pray that He would draw the Muslims "
"of this land to Himself. May they recognize Jesus as Savior, Anointed One, "
"and God, giving Him all glory and honor."
msgstr ""
"Allah adalah Maha Adil dan Maha Pengasih. Dalam ayat ini, kita melihat bahwa "
"Yesus—Yang Diurapi dan Allah sendiri—datang ke dunia dengan kerendahan hati. "
"Ia dilahirkan bukan dalam kekayaan atau kekuasaan, melainkan dalam "
"kesederhanaan. Kelahiran-Nya diumumkan bukan kepada raja-raja atau elit "
"agama, melainkan kepada gembala-gembala—orang-orang dengan status sosial "
"terendah. Dengan demikian, Allah memperlihatkan hati-Nya: Yesus tidak datang "
"hanya untuk orang kaya, berkuasa, atau dihormati, tetapi juga untuk orang "
"miskin, lemah, terabaikan, dan pendosa.\n"
"\n"
"Yesus adalah Tuhan, Mesias, Penyelamat, dan Raja. Ia berkuasa atas segala "
"sesuatu, Yang Diurapi yang dijanjikan, Penyelamat satu-satunya, dan Raja "
"yang kekal dari keturunan Daud.\n"
"\n"
"- Pujilah Allah dan berikanlah kemuliaan kepada-Nya karena telah melakukan "
"apa yang tidak pernah dapat kita lakukan sendiri—memperdamaikan kita dengan "
"diri-Nya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar banyak orang di tempat ini menerima tawaran damai Allah "
"bagi mereka yang menaruh kepercayaan pada Anak-Nya, yang datang kepada kita "
"sebagai bayi.\n"
"- Karena kasih dan belas kasihan Allah yang besar, berdoalah agar Ia menarik "
"umat Muslim di negeri ini kepada-Nya. Semoga mereka mengenali Yesus sebagai "
"Juruselamat, Yang Diurapi, dan Allah, memberikan-Nya segala kemuliaan dan "
"hormat."

msgid ""
"This passage reminds us that while people may believe they possess power and "
"control, it is God alone who rules over all things. Caesar Augustus issued a "
"decree for a census, setting in motion the movement of thousands of people—"
"likely for taxation and military purposes. Yet unknowingly, he was serving "
"God's greater purpose: that the Messiah from the line of David would be born "
"in the town of David.\n"
"\n"
"The shepherds show us the beauty of responding to God's revealed truth. "
"Though initially afraid, they believed what God had spoken, went to "
"Bethlehem, and saw with their own eyes. Then they proclaimed what they had "
"witnessed. Joy follows those who listen to God, trust His Word, and speak of "
"what He has done.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that people in this place would acknowledge the sovereignty of God in "
"their own lives. May they find peace and refuge in a God who rules over all "
"things.\n"
"- Pray also that they would find joy in trusting His Word and it would "
"overflow to those around them."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengingatkan kita bahwa meskipun orang-orang mungkin percaya bahwa "
"mereka memiliki kuasa dan kendali, hanya Allah saja yang berkuasa atas "
"segala sesuatu. Kaisar Augustus mengeluarkan perintah untuk sensus, yang "
"memicu pergerakan ribuan orang—mungkin untuk tujuan perpajakan dan militer. "
"Namun tanpa disadari, ia sedang melayani tujuan Allah yang lebih besar: "
"bahwa Mesias dari keturunan Daud akan lahir di kota Daud.\n"
"\n"
"Para gembala menunjukkan kepada kita keindahan merespons kebenaran yang "
"diwahyukan Allah. Meskipun awalnya takut, mereka percaya pada apa yang Allah "
"katakan, pergi ke Betlehem, dan melihat dengan mata kepala sendiri. Kemudian "
"mereka memberitakan apa yang mereka saksikan. Kebahagiaan mengikuti mereka "
"yang mendengarkan Allah, percaya pada Firman-Nya, dan memberitakan apa yang "
"telah Ia lakukan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini mengakui kedaulatan Allah dalam "
"hidup mereka. Semoga mereka menemukan damai dan perlindungan dalam Allah "
"yang memerintah atas segala sesuatu.\n"
"- Berdoalah juga agar mereka menemukan sukacita dalam mempercayai Firman-Nya "
"dan sukacita itu melimpah kepada orang-orang di sekitar mereka."

msgid ""
"Amira heard about the biblical account of Jesus' birth and said, \"We have "
"that same story in the Qur'an. Mary was a virgin and God breathed a baby "
"alive in her. People didn't believe that she had never been with a man and "
"so they drove her out of the village. She was under a date tree and ate the "
"dates which gave her strength. When Jesus was an infant, he spoke to people "
"telling them that his mother had done nothing wrong.\"\n"
"\n"
"Muslims have a sura in the Qur'an about Miriam (Mary). There are also "
"several other writings about Mary and various versions of the story "
"circulate. All the stories agree on the virgin birth, but none recognize "
"Jesus as divine. Muslims believe that Jesus is a prophet with his own "
"miracles just like Moses or Elijah.\n"
"\n"
"Oftentimes the similarities between the stories in the Bible and the stories "
"in the Qur'an lead to the belief that the Muslim faith and the Christian "
"faith are essentially the same.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that Muslims would be able to clearly understand the crucial "
"difference between Jesus being a prophet and Jesus being the Son of God come "
"to save us from our sins.\n"
"- Ask that this revelation would trigger a chain reaction of faith "
"exploration and that would ultimately lead them to the truth of the Gospel."
msgstr ""
"Amira mendengar kisah Alkitab tentang kelahiran Yesus dan berkata, \"Kami "
"juga memiliki kisah yang sama dalam Al-Qur'an. Maria adalah seorang perawan, "
"dan Allah meniupkan kehidupan ke dalam rahimnya. Orang-orang tidak percaya "
"bahwa dia belum pernah berhubungan dengan pria, sehingga mereka mengusirnya "
"dari desa. Dia berada di bawah pohon kurma dan memakan kurma yang memberinya "
"kekuatan. Ketika Yesus masih bayi, dia berbicara kepada orang-orang dan "
"mengatakan bahwa ibunya tidak melakukan kesalahan apa pun.\"  \n"
"\n"
"Muslim memiliki surah dalam Al-Qur'an tentang Miriam (Maria). Ada juga "
"beberapa tulisan lain tentang Maria, dan berbagai versi cerita tersebut "
"beredar. Semua cerita sepakat tentang kelahiran perawan, tetapi tidak ada "
"yang mengakui Yesus sebagai Tuhan. Muslim percaya bahwa Yesus adalah seorang "
"nabi dengan mukjizatnya sendiri, seperti Musa atau Elia.\n"
"\n"
"Seringkali kesamaan antara cerita dalam Alkitab dan cerita dalam Al-Qur'an "
"menyebabkan keyakinan bahwa agama Islam dan agama Kristen pada dasarnya "
"sama.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim dapat memahami dengan jelas perbedaan penting "
"antara Yesus sebagai nabi dan Yesus sebagai Anak Allah yang datang untuk "
"menyelamatkan kita dari dosa-dosa kita.\n"
"- Mintalah agar pencerahan ini memicu reaksi berantai dalam penjelajahan "
"iman dan pada akhirnya membawa mereka kepada kebenaran Injil."

msgid ""
"As Christians interact with Muslims, pray that they would engage in "
"conversations marked by clarity, humility, and grace. Ask God to help them "
"thoughtfully discuss the differences between the Biblical and Islamic "
"accounts of Jesus' birth, and to clearly explain the implications of Luke's "
"Gospel concerning the divinity of Christ.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that believers would have favor with those they speak with, and that "
"they would be filled with love that speaks the truth gently and "
"courageously.\n"
"- Ask that fear of difficult conversations or fear of appearing offensive "
"would not silence the gospel, but that Christians would trust God to work "
"through faithful witness."
msgstr ""
"Saat orang Kristen berinteraksi dengan Muslim, berdoalah agar mereka dapat "
"terlibat dalam percakapan yang ditandai dengan kejernihan, kerendahan hati, "
"dan kasih karunia. Mintalah kepada Tuhan untuk membantu mereka membahas "
"perbedaan antara kisah kelahiran Yesus dalam Alkitab dan Islam dengan "
"bijaksana, serta menjelaskan dengan jelas implikasi Injil Lukas mengenai "
"keilahian Kristus.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya mendapat kasih sayang dari orang-orang "
"yang mereka ajak bicara, dan agar mereka dipenuhi dengan kasih yang "
"menyampaikan kebenaran dengan lembut dan berani.\n"
"- Mintalah agar rasa takut akan percakapan yang sulit atau rasa takut "
"terlihat menyinggung tidak menghalangi pemberitaan Injil, tetapi agar orang "
"Kristen mempercayai Tuhan untuk bekerja melalui kesaksian yang setia."

msgid ""
"Philippians 2:6-8 describes Jesus by saying, \"Who, though he was in the "
"form of God, did not count equality with God a thing to be grasped, but "
"emptied himself, by taking the form of a servant, being born in the likeness "
"of men. And being found in human form, he humbled himself by becoming "
"obedient to the point of death, even death on a cross.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray that those accepting the divinity of Jesus would see His submission to "
"the Father and seek to follow His example. Ask that they would become "
"obedient disciples eager to know more about the character and nature of the "
"Messiah."
msgstr ""
"Filipi 2:6-8 menggambarkan Yesus dengan mengatakan, \"Ia, yang walaupun "
"dalam rupa Allah, tidak menganggap kesetaraan dengan Allah sebagai sesuatu "
"yang harus dipegang erat, tetapi mengosongkan diri-Nya, dengan mengambil "
"rupa seorang hamba, dan menjadi serupa dengan manusia. Dan ketika Ia "
"ditemukan dalam rupa manusia, Ia merendahkan diri-Nya dengan menjadi taat "
"sampai mati, bahkan mati di kayu salib.\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar mereka yang menerima keilahian Yesus dapat melihat kerendahan "
"hati-Nya kepada Bapa dan berusaha meneladani-Nya. Mintalah agar mereka "
"menjadi murid-murid yang taat dan bersemangat untuk mengenal lebih dalam "
"karakter dan sifat Mesias."

msgid "Day 16: John Testifies of the Savior"
msgstr "Hari ke-16: John Bersaksi tentang Sang Penyelamat"

msgid ""
"Mark 1:1-8 (ESV)\n"
"The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God. As it is "
"written in Isaiah the prophet, \"Behold, I send my messenger before your "
"face, who will prepare your way, the voice of one crying in the wilderness: "
"'Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight,' \" John appeared, "
"baptizing in the wilderness and proclaiming a baptism of repentance for the "
"forgiveness of sins. And all the country of Judea and all Jerusalem were "
"going out to him and were being baptized by him in the river Jordan, "
"confessing their sins. Now John was clothed with camel's hair and wore a "
"leather belt around his waist and ate locusts and wild honey. And he "
"preached, saying, \"After me comes he who is mightier than I, the strap of "
"whose sandals I am not worthy to stoop down and untie. I have baptized you "
"with water, but he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit.\"\n"
"\n"
"John 1:29-34 (ESV)\n"
"The next day he saw Jesus coming toward him, and said, \"Behold, the Lamb of "
"God, who takes away the sin of the world! This is he of whom I said, 'After "
"me comes a man who ranks before me, because he was before me.' I myself did "
"not know him, but for this purpose I came baptizing with water, that he "
"might be revealed to Israel.\" And John bore witness: \"I saw the Spirit "
"descend from heaven like a dove, and it remained on him. I myself did not "
"know him, but he who sent me to baptize with water said to me, 'He on whom "
"you see the Spirit descend and remain, this is he who baptizes with the Holy "
"Spirit.' And I have seen and have borne witness that this is the Son of God."
"\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God intentionally sent John to prepare the way for the public ministry of "
"Jesus. John's call to repentance awakened hearts to their need for "
"forgiveness and readied people to receive the Messiah.\n"
"\n"
"It was also the Father's will that Jesus submit to baptism, not because He "
"needed repentance, but to reveal His humility and model His obedience. At "
"that moment, God made Jesus' identity clear to John: He is the Lamb of God "
"who takes away the sin of the world and the Son of God sent from heaven.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that God would prepare the hearts of people in this land to receive "
"the message of Christ.\n"
"- Pray that Jesus' true identity would be revealed to those seeking to "
"follow Him. May the contrast between the titles Jesus held and the actions "
"Jesus took cause wonder and curiosity."
msgstr ""
"Allah dengan sengaja mengutus Yohanes untuk mempersiapkan jalan bagi "
"pelayanan publik Yesus. Panggilan Yohanes untuk bertobat membangkitkan hati "
"orang-orang akan kebutuhan mereka akan pengampunan dan mempersiapkan mereka "
"untuk menerima Mesias.  \n"
"\n"
"Itu juga kehendak Bapa agar Yesus menaati baptisan, bukan karena Dia "
"membutuhkan pertobatan, tetapi untuk menunjukkan kerendahan hati-Nya dan "
"menjadi teladan ketaatan-Nya. Pada saat itu, Allah memperjelas identitas "
"Yesus kepada Yohanes: Dia adalah Anak Domba Allah yang menghapus dosa dunia "
"dan Anak Allah yang diutus dari surga.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Allah mempersiapkan hati orang-orang di negeri ini untuk "
"menerima pesan Kristus.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar identitas sejati Yesus diungkapkan kepada mereka yang "
"mencari untuk mengikuti-Nya. Semoga kontras antara gelar yang dipegang Yesus "
"dan tindakan yang dilakukan-Nya menimbulkan keheranan dan rasa ingin tahu."

msgid ""
"John exemplifies a person called by God for a specific purpose. He submits "
"to God's direction and is used to proclaim repentance and obedience through "
"baptism.\n"
"\n"
"This passage also reveals the universal problem of sin; a problem that no "
"person can resolve on their own. Many in the surrounding region responded by "
"recognizing their need for repentance and taking action, submitting "
"themselves to the call of God.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that the same conviction of sin that drew the people into the "
"wilderness to be baptized by John would lead people in this land to seek "
"freedom from the burden of sin and the forgiveness only God provides.\n"
"- Pray that men and women here would have real encounters with the living "
"God, and that these encounters would compel them to boldly testify to the "
"Son of God and His work of grace in their lives."
msgstr ""
"John merupakan contoh seseorang yang dipanggil oleh Allah untuk tujuan "
"tertentu. Ia tunduk pada arahan Allah dan digunakan untuk memberitakan "
"pertobatan dan ketaatan melalui baptisan.  \n"
"\n"
"Ayat ini juga mengungkapkan masalah dosa yang universal; masalah yang tidak "
"dapat diselesaikan oleh manusia sendiri. Banyak orang di wilayah sekitar "
"merespons dengan menyadari kebutuhan mereka akan pertobatan dan mengambil "
"tindakan, menyerahkan diri mereka pada panggilan Allah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kesadaran akan dosa yang membawa orang-orang ke padang "
"gurun untuk dibaptis oleh John juga membawa orang-orang di negeri ini untuk "
"mencari kebebasan dari beban dosa dan pengampunan yang hanya Allah berikan.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar pria dan wanita di sini mengalami pertemuan yang nyata "
"dengan Allah yang hidup, dan agar pertemuan-pertemuan ini mendorong mereka "
"untuk dengan berani bersaksi tentang Anak Allah dan karya anugerah-Nya dalam "
"hidup mereka."

msgid ""
"One of the Qur'anic verses that many Muslims memorize and often quote says, "
"\"He [God] neither begets nor is born.\" From their earliest education they "
"are taught to deny that Jesus is the Son of God.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the Holy Spirit, who bears witness about Jesus (John 15:26), to "
"work in the hearts of men and women across the Muslim world to understand "
"the Truth of what all the Old Testament prophets were teaching us about who "
"Jesus would be.\n"
"- Pray for hearts to remember the lamb they sacrifice every year in honor of "
"God's intervention for Abraham and for them to understand what it means when "
"John says, \"Behold, the Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world!\""
msgstr ""
"Salah satu ayat Al-Qur'an yang banyak dihapal dan sering dikutip oleh umat "
"Islam berbunyi, \"Dia [Allah] tidak melahirkan dan tidak dilahirkan.\" Sejak "
"pendidikan awal mereka, mereka diajarkan untuk menolak bahwa Yesus adalah "
"Anak Allah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Roh Kudus, yang bersaksi tentang Yesus (Yohanes 15:26), "
"bekerja di hati pria dan wanita di seluruh dunia Muslim untuk memahami "
"Kebenaran tentang apa yang diajarkan oleh semua nabi Perjanjian Lama kepada "
"kita tentang siapa Yesus akan menjadi.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar hati mereka mengingat domba yang mereka kurbankan setiap "
"tahun sebagai penghormatan atas campur tangan Allah bagi Abraham, dan agar "
"mereka memahami arti kata-kata Yohanes, \"Lihatlah, Anak Domba Allah yang "
"menghapus dosa dunia!\""

msgid ""
"Miriam, an elderly lady, put her faith in Jesus and simple step by simple "
"step began to follow Him. She had no idea what He had in store for the day "
"of her baptism. She had read about Jesus' baptism and His promise to baptize "
"with the Holy Spirit. She didn't know that she would go into the water "
"legally blind and that she would emerge from the water with her eyesight "
"fully restored. Even better, this miraculous healing emboldened her to share "
"her faith with her children and grandchildren.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for God to move miraculously in the lives of Muslim people. Pray that "
"the stories of His provision would reach the ears of those ready to come to "
"Him."
msgstr ""
"Miriam, seorang wanita tua, menaruh imannya pada Yesus dan dengan langkah "
"demi langkah yang sederhana mulai mengikuti-Nya. Dia tidak tahu apa yang "
"telah disiapkan-Nya untuk hari pembaptisannya. Dia telah membaca tentang "
"pembaptisan Yesus dan janji-Nya untuk membaptis dengan Roh Kudus. Dia tidak "
"tahu bahwa dia akan masuk ke dalam air dalam keadaan buta secara hukum dan "
"akan keluar dari air dengan penglihatannya sepenuhnya pulih. Lebih baik "
"lagi, penyembuhan ajaib ini memberanikan dia untuk berbagi imannya dengan "
"anak-anak dan cucunya.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar Allah bertindak ajaib dalam hidup orang-orang Muslim. "
"Berdoalah agar kisah-kisah tentang pemeliharaan-Nya sampai ke telinga mereka "
"yang siap datang kepada-Nya."

msgid ""
"Isaiah 40:3-5 is the Old Testament passage echoed in Mark 1. It describes a "
"wilderness responding to God's call, making way for the Lord to move. We "
"pray for the reality of these promises in this place:\n"
"\n"
"In the spiritual wilderness of this place, O God, prepare the way for your "
"Messiah.\n"
"\n"
"We ask you to make straight in the desert a highway for our God. Provide "
"clear paths for people to come to know You. We pray for copies of Scripture "
"to be accessible and distributable in this place.\n"
"\n"
"We pray for every valley of fear, despair, doubt, and hopelessness that "
"hinders people from seeking Christ to be lifted up.\n"
"\n"
"We pray for every mountain and hill of false religion, persecution, "
"spiritual pacts and bonds, and work of the enemy to be made low.\n"
"\n"
"May the glory of the Lord be revealed and all flesh of this land see it "
"together."
msgstr ""
"Yesaya 40:3-5 adalah bagian dari Perjanjian Lama yang diulang dalam Markus "
"1. Bagian ini menggambarkan padang gurun yang merespons panggilan Allah, "
"membuka jalan bagi Tuhan untuk bertindak. Kami berdoa agar janji-janji ini "
"menjadi kenyataan di tempat ini:  \n"
"\n"
"Di padang gurun rohani tempat ini, ya Allah, persiapkanlah jalan bagi Mesias-"
"Mu.  \n"
"\n"
"Kami memohon agar Engkau meluruskan jalan di padang gurun bagi Allah kami. "
"Sediakanlah jalan yang jelas bagi orang-orang untuk mengenal Engkau. Kami "
"berdoa agar salinan Kitab Suci dapat diakses dan didistribusikan di tempat "
"ini.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa agar setiap lembah ketakutan, keputusasaan, keraguan, dan "
"keputusasaan yang menghalangi orang-orang untuk mencari Kristus diangkat.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa agar setiap gunung dan bukit agama palsu, penganiayaan, "
"perjanjian dan ikatan rohani, serta pekerjaan musuh diturunkan.\n"
"\n"
"Semoga kemuliaan Tuhan dinyatakan dan semua daging di negeri ini melihatnya "
"bersama-sama."

msgid "Day 17: Temptation and Ministry of Jesus"
msgstr "Hari ke-17: Godaan dan Pelayanan Yesus"

msgid ""
"Luke 4:1-22 (ESV)\n"
"And Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, returned from the Jordan and was led by "
"the Spirit in the wilderness for forty days, being tempted by the devil. And "
"he ate nothing during those days. And when they were ended, he was hungry. "
"The devil said to him, \"If you are the Son of God, command this stone to "
"become bread.\" And Jesus answered him, \"It is written, 'Man shall not live "
"by bread alone.' \" And the devil took him up and showed him all the "
"kingdoms of the world in a moment of time, and said to him, \"To you I will "
"give all this authority and their glory, for it has been delivered to me, "
"and I give it to whom I will. If you, then, will worship me, it will all be "
"yours.\" And Jesus answered him, \"It is written, \" 'You shall worship the "
"Lord your God, and him only shall you serve.' \" And he took him to "
"Jerusalem and set him on the pinnacle of the temple and said to him, \"If "
"you are the Son of God, throw yourself down from here, for it is written, \" "
"'He will command his angels concerning you, to guard you,' and \" 'On their "
"hands they will bear you up, lest you strike your foot against a stone.' \" "
"And Jesus answered him, \"It is said, 'You shall not put the Lord your God "
"to the test.' \" And when the devil had ended every temptation, he departed "
"from him until an opportune time. And Jesus returned in the power of the "
"Spirit to Galilee, and a report about him went out through all the "
"surrounding country. And he taught in their synagogues, being glorified by "
"all. And he came to Nazareth, where he had been brought up. And as was his "
"custom, he went to the synagogue on the Sabbath day, and he stood up to "
"read. And the scroll of the prophet Isaiah was given to him. He unrolled the "
"scroll and found the place where it was written, \"The Spirit of the Lord is "
"upon me, because he has anointed me to proclaim good news to the poor. He "
"has sent me to proclaim liberty to the captives and recovering of sight to "
"the blind, to set at liberty those who are oppressed, to proclaim the year "
"of the Lord's favor.\" And he rolled up the scroll and gave it back to the "
"attendant and sat down. And the eyes of all in the synagogue were fixed on "
"him. And he began to say to them, \"Today this Scripture has been fulfilled "
"in your hearing.\" And all spoke well of him and marveled at the gracious "
"words that were coming from his mouth. And they said, \"Is not this Joseph's "
"son?\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- This passage teaches us that God became fully man and was tempted in every "
"way we are, yet was without sin. Pray for this reality to comfort and "
"challenge believers as they become more like Jesus to resist Satan's "
"temptations for power and comfort in their lives.\n"
"- We also learn that God has permitted Satan to have some level of authority "
"on this side of eternity. Pray for people in this place to rightly attribute "
"evil to Satan, but to not misunderstand that Satan's power is limited and "
"his defeat has already been secured.\n"
"- We learn that Jesus is the complete fulfillment of all the prophecies of "
"Scripture. Pray for Muslim eyes and hearts to be opened to see the supremacy "
"of Christ over every other prophet and holy man. May their hearts swell as "
"they rightly see Him for who He has revealed Himself to be through Scripture."
msgstr ""
"- Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa Allah menjadi manusia sepenuhnya "
"dan mengalami godaan dalam segala hal seperti kita, namun tanpa dosa. "
"Berdoalah agar kenyataan ini menghibur dan menantang para percaya agar "
"semakin menyerupai Yesus dalam menahan godaan Setan akan kekuasaan dan "
"kenyamanan dalam hidup mereka.\n"
"- Kita juga belajar bahwa Allah telah mengizinkan Setan memiliki tingkat "
"otoritas tertentu di sisi ini dari kekekalan. Berdoalah agar orang-orang di "
"tempat ini dapat dengan benar mengaitkan kejahatan dengan Setan, namun tidak "
"salah paham bahwa kuasa Setan terbatas dan kekalahannya telah dipastikan.\n"
"- Kita belajar bahwa Yesus adalah pemenuhan sempurna dari semua nubuat Kitab "
"Suci. Berdoalah agar mata dan hati orang Muslim dibuka untuk melihat "
"keunggulan Kristus di atas semua nabi dan orang suci lainnya. Semoga hati "
"mereka membesar saat mereka dengan benar melihat-Nya sebagaimana Ia telah "
"menyatakan diri-Nya melalui Kitab Suci."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that all of the bad news that humanity faces is "
"firmly and finally replaced with good news through Christ.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the poor in this land, that they would respond and find hope in "
"the Good News Jesus offers.\n"
"- Pray for those who are in bondage to evil spirits in this place. Pray for "
"them to experience the liberty Jesus provides and to be set free from all of "
"the ways the enemy is trying to keep them in darkness.\n"
"- Pray for miracles of healing for those who are blind, both spiritually and "
"physically. Pray for the name of Jesus to be revered and honored through "
"these healings.\n"
"- Pray for the oppressed -- women in abusive marriages, minorities in "
"exploitative work environments, those in slavery, and trafficked people -- "
"to be given liberty. Pray for the oppressors to repent and to find "
"forgiveness of sins in Christ."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa semua kabar buruk yang dihadapi umat "
"manusia secara pasti dan akhir digantikan dengan kabar baik melalui "
"Kristus.  \n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk orang-orang miskin di negeri ini, agar mereka merespons "
"dan menemukan harapan dalam Kabar Baik yang ditawarkan Yesus.  \n"
"- Berdoalah untuk mereka yang terikat oleh roh-roh jahat di tempat ini. "
"Berdoalah agar mereka mengalami kebebasan yang diberikan Yesus dan "
"dibebaskan dari segala cara musuh mencoba menahan mereka dalam kegelapan.\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk mujizat penyembuhan bagi mereka yang buta, baik secara "
"rohani maupun fisik. Berdoalah agar nama Yesus dihormati dan dimuliakan "
"melalui penyembuhan-penyembuhan ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk mereka yang tertindas — perempuan dalam pernikahan yang "
"penuh kekerasan, minoritas dalam lingkungan kerja yang eksploitatif, mereka "
"yang diperbudak, dan korban perdagangan manusia — agar diberikan kebebasan. "
"Berdoalah agar para penindas bertobat dan menemukan pengampunan dosa dalam "
"Kristus."

msgid ""
"Riadh was in his early twenties when he became curious about Christianity. "
"Despite being young, he was financially independent and affluent. He was "
"running a business and making a lot of money. The Christian who was sharing "
"the Gospel with him was excited about Riadh's hunger. But then Riadh started "
"to back away. When the Christian asked him why, he said, \"I made a pact "
"with good Muslim spirits, but they are the ones who have made me rich. They "
"don't want me to continue. I think I need a break from pursuing this.\"\n"
"\n"
"Riadh had taken the enemy up on his offer to receive authority and glory "
"from him and with it came complete bondage. Pray for people in this land to "
"be set free from every pact and agreement they have made with darkness and "
"to come into the glorious and freeing light of Christ."
msgstr ""
"Riadh berusia awal dua puluhan ketika ia mulai tertarik pada Kristen. "
"Meskipun masih muda, ia sudah mandiri secara finansial dan berkecukupan. Ia "
"menjalankan sebuah bisnis dan menghasilkan banyak uang. Seorang Kristen yang "
"berbagi Injil dengannya merasa bersemangat melihat kerinduan Riadh. Namun, "
"Riadh mulai mundur. Ketika orang Kristen itu bertanya mengapa, ia menjawab, "
"\"Saya telah membuat perjanjian dengan roh-roh Muslim yang baik, tetapi "
"mereka lah yang telah membuat saya kaya. Mereka tidak ingin saya terus "
"melakukannya. Saya pikir saya perlu istirahat dari mengejar ini.\"\n"
"\n"
"Riadh telah menerima tawaran musuh untuk menerima kekuasaan dan kemuliaan "
"darinya, dan dengan itu datanglah ikatan yang lengkap. Berdoalah agar orang-"
"orang di negeri ini dibebaskan dari setiap perjanjian dan kesepakatan yang "
"mereka buat dengan kegelapan, dan agar mereka masuk ke dalam cahaya yang "
"mulia dan membebaskan dari Kristus."

msgid ""
"Pray for Christians in this place who are seeking to share Good News with "
"Muslims to operate in the power of the Spirit. Pray for their hearts to be "
"meditating on Scripture so that they can respond to Satan's temptations with "
"God's Word. Pray for the Church to continue to live out the fulfillment of "
"the Isaiah scroll in their land -- to be ministers of justice, mercy, "
"compassion, and liberators."
msgstr ""
"Berdoalah untuk para Kristen di tempat ini yang berusaha membagikan Kabar "
"Baik kepada umat Muslim agar mereka dapat bertindak dalam kuasa Roh Kudus. "
"Berdoalah agar hati mereka merenungkan Firman Allah sehingga mereka dapat "
"menanggapi godaan Setan dengan Firman Allah. Berdoalah agar Gereja terus "
"hidup sesuai dengan penggenapan gulungan Yesaya di tanah mereka — menjadi "
"pelayan keadilan, belas kasihan, kasih sayang, dan pembebas."

msgid ""
"Jesus fasted for 40 days and the rest of Luke 4 flows out of that time with "
"the Father. Pray for Christians in this place to practice true fasting and "
"for it to be a testimony to Muslims who don't know that Christians fast nor "
"what true fasting really means:\n"
"\n"
"Pray for the fasting that God calls for (Isaiah 58:6-8): to loose the bonds "
"of wickedness, to undo the straps of the yoke, to let the oppressed go free, "
"and to break every yoke. Pray for people in this land to share their bread "
"with the hungry and bring the homeless poor into their homes. When they see "
"the naked, give them means to cover them.\n"
"\n"
"Then bless true fasters in this land. That their light would break forth "
"like the dawn, and healing spring up speedily. We ask for their "
"righteousness to go before them, and the glory of the Lord to be their rear "
"guard.\n"
"\n"
"May men and women in this land experience the promise of Isaiah 58:10-11, "
"\"If you pour yourself out for the hungry and satisfy the desire of the "
"afflicted, then shall your light rise in the darkness and your gloom be as "
"the noonday. And the Lord will guide you continually and satisfy your desire "
"in scorched places and make your bones strong. And you shall be like a "
"watered garden, like a spring of water whose waters do not fail.\""
msgstr ""
"Yesus berpuasa selama 40 hari, dan sisa dari Lukas 4 berlanjut dari waktu "
"itu bersama Bapa. Berdoalah agar umat Kristen di tempat ini mempraktikkan "
"puasa yang sejati, dan agar hal itu menjadi kesaksian bagi umat Muslim yang "
"tidak tahu bahwa umat Kristen berpuasa maupun apa arti puasa yang sejati:\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar puasa yang dipanggil oleh Allah (Yesaya 58:6-8): untuk "
"melepaskan ikatan kejahatan, melepaskan tali kuk, membebaskan orang yang "
"tertindas, dan memecahkan setiap kuk. Berdoalah agar orang-orang di negeri "
"ini berbagi roti mereka dengan orang yang lapar dan membawa orang miskin "
"yang tidak punya rumah ke dalam rumah mereka. Ketika mereka melihat orang "
"yang telanjang, berikanlah mereka cara untuk menutupi diri mereka.\n"
"\n"
"Kemudian berkatilah orang-orang yang berpuasa dengan benar di negeri ini. "
"Agar cahaya mereka bersinar seperti fajar, dan penyembuhan tumbuh dengan "
"cepat. Kami memohon agar keadilan mereka mendahului mereka, dan kemuliaan "
"Tuhan menjadi penjaga belakang mereka.\n"
"\n"
"Semoga pria dan wanita di negeri ini mengalami janji Yesaya 58:10-11, \"Jika "
"kamu mencurahkan dirimu untuk orang yang lapar dan memuaskan keinginan orang "
"yang tertindas, maka cahayamu akan bersinar di kegelapan dan kegelapanmu "
"akan menjadi seperti siang hari. Dan Tuhan akan memimpinmu terus-menerus dan "
"memuaskan keinginanmu di tempat-tempat yang gersang dan membuat tulang-"
"tulangmu kuat. Dan kamu akan menjadi seperti taman yang dibasahi, seperti "
"mata air yang airnya tidak pernah kering.\""

msgid "Day 18: Jesus Heals and Forgives"
msgstr "Hari ke-18: Yesus Menyembuhkan dan Mengampuni"

msgid ""
"Luke 5:17-32 (ESV)\n"
"On one of those days, as he was teaching, Pharisees and teachers of the law "
"were sitting there, who had come from every village of Galilee and Judea and "
"from Jerusalem. And the power of the Lord was with him to heal. And behold, "
"some men were bringing on a bed a man who was paralyzed, and they were "
"seeking to bring him in and lay him before Jesus, but finding no way to "
"bring him in, because of the crowd, they went up on the roof and let him "
"down with his bed through the tiles into the midst before Jesus. And when he "
"saw their faith, he said, \"Man, your sins are forgiven you.\" And the "
"scribes and the Pharisees began to question, saying, \"Who is this who "
"speaks blasphemies? Who can forgive sins but God alone?\" When Jesus "
"perceived their thoughts, he answered them, \"Why do you question in your "
"hearts? Which is easier, to say, 'Your sins are forgiven you,'or to say, "
"'Rise and walk'? But that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on "
"earth to forgive sins\"—he said to the man who was paralyzed—\"I say to you, "
"rise, pick up your bed and go home.\" And immediately he rose up before them "
"and picked up what he had been lying on and went home, glorifying God. And "
"amazement seized them all, and they glorified God and were filled with awe, "
"saying, \"We have seen extraordinary things today.\" After this he went out "
"and saw a tax collector named Levi, sitting at the tax booth. And he said to "
"him, \"Follow me.\" And leaving everything, he rose and followed him. And "
"Levi made him a great feast in his house, and there was a large company of "
"tax collectors and others reclining at table with them. And the Pharisees "
"and their scribes grumbled at his disciples, saying, \"Why do you eat and "
"drink with tax collectors and sinners?\" And Jesus answered them, \"Those "
"who are well have no need of a physician, but those who are sick. I have not "
"come to call the righteous but sinners to repentance.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- This passage teaches us that God responds to faith. Pray for faith to grow "
"among the people of this land; that even if they have faith the size of a "
"mustard seed, God would take that faith and do extraordinary things for His "
"glory.\n"
"- This passage also teaches us that God is not afraid to sit with sinners. "
"Though it was scandalous, Jesus went to the homes of sinners and tax "
"collectors and ate with them. Pray for Christians who are willing to live "
"out this example. Pray for believing men and women to build genuine, loving "
"relationships with Muslim families—to eat with them, share life with them, "
"and bring them the good news of Jesus."
msgstr ""
"- Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa Allah merespons iman. Berdoalah "
"agar iman tumbuh di antara penduduk negeri ini; bahwa meskipun iman mereka "
"sebesar biji sesawi, Allah akan mengambil iman itu dan melakukan hal-hal "
"luar biasa untuk kemuliaan-Nya.\n"
"- Ayat ini juga mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa Allah tidak takut untuk duduk "
"bersama orang berdosa. Meskipun hal itu dianggap skandal, Yesus pergi ke "
"rumah-rumah orang berdosa dan pemungut pajak, dan makan bersama mereka. "
"Berdoalah agar orang-orang Kristen bersedia hidup sesuai teladan ini. "
"Berdoalah agar pria dan wanita yang beriman membangun hubungan yang sejati "
"dan penuh kasih dengan keluarga Muslim—makan bersama mereka, berbagi "
"kehidupan dengan mereka, dan membawa kabar baik tentang Yesus kepada mereka."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that our faith and actions impact others. Pray for "
"God to raise up brave men and women among this people group who would go to "
"extraordinary lengths to bring their friends to Christ's feet.\n"
"\n"
"\"Did I tell you I went on the pilgrimage to Mecca this year?\" Rania "
"proudly asked. \"Yes, Auntie, you did.\" \"Hmmm,\" Rania continued unfazed, "
"\"I spent 21 days in Saudi Arabia.\" Rania then went on to list other good "
"deeds she had done. Religion, with its lists of dos and don'ts, has a way of "
"slanting our orientation and causing us to focus on how much better we are "
"than other people we are comparing ourselves to.\n"
"\n"
"Jesus said, \"Those who are well have no need of a physician, but those who "
"are sick. I have not come to call the righteous but sinners to "
"repentance\" (Luke 5:32). Not from any sense of superiority, but in a spirit "
"of humility, pray for God to reveal spiritual sickness to Muslims in this "
"land and to stir them to seek out the Good Physician who alone can fully "
"heal their sin problem."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa iman dan tindakan kita berdampak pada "
"orang lain. Berdoalah agar Tuhan mengangkat pria dan wanita yang berani di "
"antara kelompok etnis ini yang bersedia melakukan segala cara untuk membawa "
"teman-teman mereka ke hadapan Kristus.\n"
"\n"
"\"Apakah aku sudah cerita padamu bahwa aku pergi ziarah ke Mekah tahun "
"ini?\" tanya Rania dengan bangga. \"Ya, Tante, kamu sudah cerita.\" "
"\"Hmmm,\" Rania melanjutkan tanpa terganggu, \"Aku menghabiskan 21 hari di "
"Arab Saudi.\" Rania lalu melanjutkan dengan menyebutkan perbuatan baik lain "
"yang telah dilakukannya. Agama, dengan daftar perintah dan larangan, "
"seringkali memengaruhi orientasi kita dan membuat kita fokus pada seberapa "
"baik kita dibandingkan dengan orang lain yang kita bandingkan.\n"
"\n"
"Yesus berkata, \"Orang yang sehat tidak memerlukan dokter, tetapi orang yang "
"sakit. Aku tidak datang untuk memanggil orang benar, tetapi orang berdosa "
"agar bertobat\" (Lukas 5:32). Bukan dari rasa superioritas, tetapi dengan "
"semangat kerendahan hati, berdoalah agar Allah mengungkapkan penyakit rohani "
"kepada umat Muslim di negeri ini dan menggerakkan mereka untuk mencari "
"Dokter yang Baik yang satu-satunya dapat sepenuhnya menyembuhkan masalah "
"dosa mereka."

msgid ""
"Muslims' objections to Christ sound very much like the Pharisees of Jesus' "
"day. \"Who is this who speaks blasphemies? Who can forgive sins but God "
"alone?\" They don't object to the idea that He did miracles; rather, they "
"object to the authority He claimed -- that He is the Son of God and has the "
"power to forgive sins.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for miracles to take place in this land that confirm the authority of "
"Jesus as the Son of God. Thank Him for the many signs and wonders He is "
"pouring out all over the Muslim world and pray for those to result in "
"families, neighborhoods, friend groups, and repenting of self-righteousness "
"and clinging to Christ's true righteousness."
msgstr ""
"Penolakan umat Muslim terhadap Kristus sangat mirip dengan penolakan para "
"Farisi pada zaman Yesus. \"Siapakah orang ini yang berani mengucapkan kata-"
"kata penghujatan? Siapakah yang berhak mengampuni dosa selain Allah saja?\" "
"Mereka tidak menentang fakta bahwa Dia melakukan mujizat; melainkan, mereka "
"menentang klaim otoritas-Nya — bahwa Dia adalah Anak Allah dan memiliki "
"kuasa untuk mengampuni dosa.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar mujizat terjadi di negeri ini yang membuktikan otoritas Yesus "
"sebagai Anak Allah. Bersyukurlah kepada-Nya atas banyak tanda dan keajaiban "
"yang Ia curahkan di seluruh dunia Muslim, dan berdoalah agar hal itu "
"menghasilkan pertobatan keluarga, lingkungan, kelompok teman, dan melepaskan "
"diri dari keadilan diri sendiri serta berpegang teguh pada keadilan sejati "
"Kristus."

msgid ""
"We know very little about the four people who carried the paralytic to "
"Jesus, but we can assume that they did this with significant effort and "
"sacrifice on their part.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for God to raise up believers who will work together to bring the "
"good news to this people. Pray for the unity among believers, that "
"collaboration would be one of the means God uses to bring the gospel to this "
"land.\n"
"- Pray that every way the enemy has sown disunity through fear, persecution, "
"or mistrust would be replaced with joyful cooperation and unified effort to "
"bring the lost of this land to the feet of Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Kami tahu sangat sedikit tentang empat orang yang membawa orang lumpuh itu "
"kepada Yesus, tetapi kita dapat menduga bahwa mereka melakukannya dengan "
"usaha dan pengorbanan yang besar.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Tuhan mengangkat orang-orang percaya yang akan bekerja sama "
"untuk membawa kabar baik kepada bangsa ini. Berdoalah agar ada kesatuan di "
"antara orang-orang percaya, sehingga kerja sama menjadi salah satu cara yang "
"Tuhan gunakan untuk membawa Injil ke tanah ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar setiap cara yang musuh gunakan untuk menabur perpecahan "
"melalui ketakutan, penganiayaan, atau ketidakpercayaan digantikan dengan "
"kerja sama yang penuh sukacita dan usaha yang bersatu untuk membawa orang-"
"orang yang hilang di tanah ini ke kaki Yesus."

msgid ""
"Another account of a lame man being healed is found in Acts chapter 3.\n"
"\n"
"\"And Peter directed his gaze at him, as did John, and said, \"Look at us.\" "
"And he fixed his attention on them, expecting to receive something from "
"them. But Peter said, \"I have no silver and gold, but what I do have I give "
"to you. In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, rise up and walk.\" And he "
"took him by the right hand and raised him up, and immediately his feet and "
"ankles were made strong.\"\n"
"\n"
"Lord, we pray for the continuation of the work you began through the early "
"church today in this land and among this people. Just as this healing led to "
"Peter and John having to publicly proclaim Christ, may miracles today result "
"in the bold testimony to the One who heals. May Christ be treasured and "
"revered among the people of this place."
msgstr ""
"Cerita lain tentang seorang pria lumpuh yang disembuhkan terdapat dalam "
"Kitab Kisah Para Rasul bab 3.  \n"
"\n"
"\"Dan Petrus menatapnya, demikian pula Yohanes, lalu berkata, 'Lihatlah "
"kami.' Lalu ia memusatkan perhatiannya pada mereka, mengharapkan sesuatu "
"dari mereka. Tetapi Petrus berkata, 'Aku tidak punya perak atau emas, tetapi "
"apa yang aku miliki, aku berikan kepadamu. Dalam nama Yesus Kristus dari "
"Nazaret, bangunlah dan berjalanlah.' Dan ia memegang tangannya yang kanan "
"dan mengangkatnya, dan seketika itu juga kakinya dan pergelangan kakinya "
"menjadi kuat.\"\n"
"\n"
"Tuhan, kami berdoa agar pekerjaan yang Engkau mulai melalui gereja mula-mula "
"hari ini di negeri ini dan di antara bangsa ini terus berlanjut. Sama "
"seperti penyembuhan ini menyebabkan Petrus dan Yohanes harus secara terbuka "
"memberitakan Kristus, semoga mujizat hari ini menghasilkan kesaksian yang "
"berani tentang Dia yang menyembuhkan. Semoga Kristus dihargai dan dihormati "
"di antara orang-orang di tempat ini."

msgid "Day 19: Jesus' Power"
msgstr "Hari ke-19: Kuasa Yesus"

msgid ""
"Mark 4:35-5:20 (ESV)\n"
"On that day, when evening had come, he said to them, \"Let us go across to "
"the other side.\" And leaving the crowd, they took him with them in the "
"boat, just as he was. And other boats were with him. And a great windstorm "
"arose, and the waves were breaking into the boat, so that the boat was "
"already filling. But he was in the stern, asleep on the cushion. And they "
"woke him and said to him, \"Teacher, do you not care that we are perishing?"
"\" And he awoke and rebuked the wind and said to the sea, \"Peace! Be still!"
"\" And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm. He said to them, \"Why "
"are you so afraid? Have you still no faith?\" And they were filled with "
"great fear and said to one another, \"Who then is this, that even the wind "
"and the sea obey him?\" They came to the other side of the sea, to the "
"country of the Gerasenes. And when Jesus had stepped out of the boat, "
"immediately there met him out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit. He "
"lived among the tombs. And no one could bind him anymore, not even with a "
"chain, for he had often been bound with shackles and chains, but he wrenched "
"the chains apart, and he broke the shackles in pieces. No one had the "
"strength to subdue him. Night and day among the tombs and on the mountains "
"he was always crying out and cutting himself with stones. And when he saw "
"Jesus from afar, he ran and fell down before him. And crying out with a loud "
"voice, he said, \"What have you to do with me, Jesus, Son of the Most High "
"God? I adjure you by God, do not torment me.\" For he was saying to him, "
"\"Come out of the man, you unclean spirit!\" And Jesus asked him, \"What is "
"your name?\" He replied, \"My name is Legion, for we are many.\" And he "
"begged him earnestly not to send them out of the country. Now a great herd "
"of pigs was feeding there on the hillside, and they begged him, saying, "
"\"Send us to the pigs; let us enter them.\" So he gave them permission. And "
"the unclean spirits came out, and entered the pigs, and the herd, numbering "
"about two thousand, rushed down the steep bank into the sea and were drowned "
"in the sea. The herdsmen fled and told it in the city and in the country. "
"And people came to see what it was that had happened. And they came to Jesus "
"and saw the demon-possessed man, the one who had had the legion, sitting "
"there, clothed and in his right mind, and they were afraid. And those who "
"had seen it described to them what had happened to the demon-possessed man "
"and to the pigs. And they began to beg Jesus to depart from their region. As "
"he was getting into the boat, the man who had been possessed with demons "
"begged him that he might be with him. And he did not permit him but said to "
"him, \"Go home to your friends and tell them how much the Lord has done for "
"you, and how he has had mercy on you.\" And he went away and began to "
"proclaim in the Decapolis how much Jesus had done for him, and everyone "
"marveled."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Jesus' authority extends over nature.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the people of this place to turn to Jesus, the One with authority "
"over both the literal and metaphorical storms in life.\n"
"\n"
"Jesus also has authority over evil spirits.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for every spiritual pact people in this land have made under folk "
"Islam to be broken in the name of Jesus.\n"
"- Pray for Muslims who rely on offering sacrifices at the graves of dead "
"'saints' to receive blessings. Pray for all of the effects of charms, pins "
"sewn into clothing, wall hangings, and superstitious incantations to be "
"broken in the name of Jesus. Pray for people in this land to experience the "
"freedom of Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Wewenang Yesus meliputi alam semesta.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar penduduk tempat ini berbalik kepada Yesus, Dia yang "
"memiliki wewenang atas badai-badai dalam hidup, baik secara harfiah maupun "
"kiasan.\n"
"\n"
"Yesus juga memiliki wewenang atas roh-roh jahat.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar setiap perjanjian rohani yang dibuat oleh orang-orang di "
"negeri ini di bawah Islam tradisional dihancurkan dalam nama Yesus.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim yang bergantung pada persembahan korban di "
"kuburan para 'santo' yang telah meninggal untuk menerima berkat, agar semua "
"efek dari jimat, jarum yang dijahit ke pakaian, hiasan dinding, dan mantra-"
"mantra mistis dihancurkan dalam nama Yesus. Berdoalah agar orang-orang di "
"negeri ini mengalami kebebasan dalam Yesus."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us how prone humanity is to respond in fear instead of "
"living in faith. Jesus' disciples were afraid of the storm. The people of "
"the Gerasenes were afraid of the demoniac, then they were afraid of his "
"healing.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the power of fear to be broken in the lives of the people in this "
"place.\n"
"- Pray for Christians who are still living in fear to experience the freedom "
"that Jesus came to give them. Pray that they would be encouraged and "
"empowered to walk in faith instead.\n"
"- Pray for the lost who are in bondage to the fear of eternal damnation when "
"asking questions, thinking critically, reading the Bible, or exploring the "
"claims of Christ. Pray for these bonds to be broken, for faith to grow in "
"them that Jesus is exactly who He says He is in the New Testament."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita betapa mudahnya manusia merespons dengan "
"ketakutan daripada hidup dalam iman. Murid-murid Yesus takut akan badai. "
"Orang-orang Gerasa takut akan orang yang kerasukan setan, lalu mereka takut "
"akan kesembuhannya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kuasa ketakutan dihancurkan dalam hidup orang-orang di "
"tempat ini.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang Kristen yang masih hidup dalam ketakutan dapat "
"mengalami kebebasan yang Yesus datang untuk berikan kepada mereka. Berdoalah "
"agar mereka didorong dan diberdayakan untuk hidup dalam iman.\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi orang-orang yang hilang yang terikat oleh ketakutan akan "
"hukuman kekal saat bertanya, berpikir kritis, membaca Alkitab, atau "
"menyelidiki klaim Kristus. Berdoalah agar ikatan-ikatan ini dihancurkan, "
"agar iman tumbuh dalam diri mereka bahwa Yesus adalah tepat seperti yang Dia "
"katakan dalam Perjanjian Baru."

msgid ""
"Though it may be contrary to official Islamic doctrine, throughout the "
"Muslim world, many people enter into the spiritual realm to seek blessing, "
"protection, and success from spirits. Sarra had made a pact with one of "
"these spirits to help her succeed in her studies. When she met a Christian "
"and started going to their small home church, the spirit she made a pact "
"with didn't like it. Eventually, she found that she was failing in school. "
"She decided grades and success in school were of greater worth than Jesus "
"and walked away from Him and from her Christian family. The small house "
"church would continue to pray for her even though she wasn't in attendance. "
"She sensed their prayers and would call someone in the group and tell them "
"to stop praying for her. A couple of years later, the unrelenting grace of "
"Jesus that wouldn't give up on her won her heart and she repented and turned "
"back to Him. Pray for many, many more stories of freedom for the people of "
"this land. May there be multitudes who would testify to Jesus' power and "
"boundless grace."
msgstr ""
"Meskipun hal ini bertentangan dengan ajaran Islam resmi, di seluruh dunia "
"Muslim, banyak orang memasuki dunia spiritual untuk mencari berkah, "
"perlindungan, dan kesuksesan dari roh-roh. Sarra telah membuat perjanjian "
"dengan salah satu roh tersebut untuk membantunya sukses dalam studinya. "
"Ketika dia bertemu dengan seorang Kristen dan mulai menghadiri gereja kecil "
"mereka, roh yang dia perjanjian dengannya tidak menyukainya. Akhirnya, dia "
"menyadari bahwa dia gagal dalam sekolah. Dia memutuskan bahwa nilai dan "
"kesuksesan di sekolah lebih berharga daripada Yesus, dan dia menjauh dari-"
"Nya dan dari keluarganya yang Kristen. Gereja rumah kecil itu terus "
"mendoakannya meskipun dia tidak hadir. Dia merasakan doa-doa mereka dan "
"menelepon seseorang di kelompok itu untuk meminta mereka berhenti "
"mendoakannya. Beberapa tahun kemudian, kasih karunia Yesus yang tak kenal "
"lelah dan tak pernah menyerah padanya memenangkan hatinya, dan dia bertobat "
"serta kembali kepada-Nya. Berdoalah agar banyak sekali kisah kebebasan bagi "
"orang-orang di negeri ini. Semoga banyak orang yang bersaksi tentang kuasa "
"Yesus dan kasih karunia-Nya yang tak terbatas."

msgid ""
"Right now there are Christians in this land who are facing intense storms in "
"life: threats from family members, the possibility of losing children, "
"financial uncertainty, unemployment, and being thrown in prison because of "
"their faith in Christ. There are also believers facing storms because of the "
"fallen world we live in: cancer, depression, underemployment, strained "
"relationships, and loneliness.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Jesus' words, \"Peace! Be still!\" to comfort them in their "
"storms and to grow faith in their hearts. Pray that the peace of Christ "
"would be strongly felt by them today and each day."
msgstr ""
"Saat ini, ada orang-orang Kristen di negeri ini yang sedang menghadapi badai "
"kehidupan yang dahsyat: ancaman dari anggota keluarga, kemungkinan "
"kehilangan anak-anak, ketidakpastian finansial, pengangguran, dan dipenjara "
"karena iman mereka kepada Kristus. Ada juga orang-orang percaya yang "
"menghadapi badai karena dunia yang jatuh ini: kanker, depresi, pengangguran, "
"hubungan yang tegang, dan kesepian.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kata-kata Yesus, \"Damai! Tenanglah!\" menghibur mereka di "
"tengah badai dan menumbuhkan iman di hati mereka. Berdoalah agar damai "
"Kristus dirasakan dengan kuat oleh mereka hari ini dan setiap hari."

msgid ""
"Today we pray Ephesians 6:10-20 for our brothers and sisters among this "
"people -- that they would be strong in the Lord and in the strength of His "
"might. May they put on the whole armor of God that they would be able to "
"stand against the schemes of the devil. For we do not wrestle against flesh "
"and blood, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the "
"cosmic powers over this present darkness, against the spiritual forces of "
"evil in the heavenly places.\n"
"\n"
"May the people of this land take up the whole armor of God, that they would "
"be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to stand firm. "
"May they stand, therefore, having fastened on the belt of truth and having "
"put on the breastplate of righteousness. And as shoes for their feet, put on "
"the readiness given by the gospel of peace.\n"
"\n"
"In all circumstances may the people of this land take up the shield of faith "
"with which they can extinguish all the flaming darts of the evil one. Put "
"the helmet of salvation firmly on their heads and the sword of the Spirit in "
"their hands, which is the Word of God, praying at all times in the Spirit "
"with all prayer and supplication.\n"
"\n"
"So Lord, to this end, keep us alert with all perseverance, making "
"supplication for all the saints. We pray for our brothers and sisters in "
"this land that words would be given to them to open their mouths boldly to "
"proclaim the mystery of the gospel."
msgstr ""
"Hari ini kita berdoa berdasarkan Efesus 6:10-20 untuk saudara-saudari kita "
"di tengah-tengah umat ini -- agar mereka kuat dalam Tuhan dan dalam kekuatan "
"kuasa-Nya. Semoga mereka mengenakan seluruh perlengkapan perang Allah agar "
"dapat berdiri teguh melawan tipu daya iblis. Sebab kita tidak berjuang "
"melawan daging dan darah, tetapi melawan penguasa-penguasa, melawan otoritas-"
"otoritas, melawan kuasa-kuasa kosmik yang menguasai kegelapan saat ini, "
"melawan kekuatan-kekuatan rohani yang jahat di tempat-tempat surgawi.  \n"
"\n"
"Semoga umat di negeri ini mengenakan seluruh perlengkapan perang Allah, agar "
"mereka dapat bertahan pada hari yang jahat, dan setelah melakukan semuanya, "
"tetap teguh berdiri. Semoga mereka berdiri, dengan mengikatkan ikat pinggang "
"kebenaran dan mengenakan baju zirah keadilan. Dan sebagai sepatu kaki "
"mereka, kenakan kesiapan yang diberikan oleh Injil damai.  \n"
"\n"
"Dalam segala keadaan, semoga orang-orang di negeri ini mengenakan perisai "
"iman dengan mana mereka dapat memadamkan semua panah api si jahat. "
"Kenakanlah helm keselamatan dengan kokoh di kepala mereka dan pedang Roh di "
"tangan mereka, yaitu Firman Allah, berdoa dengan segala doa dan permohonan "
"dalam Roh pada segala waktu.\n"
"\n"
"Oleh karena itu, Tuhan, untuk tujuan ini, jaga kami tetap waspada dengan "
"segala ketekunan, berdoa untuk semua orang kudus. Kami berdoa untuk saudara-"
"saudari kami di negeri ini agar kata-kata diberikan kepada mereka untuk "
"membuka mulut mereka dengan berani dan memberitakan rahasia Injil."

msgid "Day 20: Forgiveness and Sacrifice"
msgstr "Hari ke-20: Pengampunan dan Pengorbanan"

msgid ""
"Luke 18:9-30 (ESV)\n"
"He also told this parable to some who trusted in themselves that they were "
"righteous, and treated others with contempt: \"Two men went up into the "
"temple to pray, one a Pharisee and the other a tax collector. The Pharisee, "
"standing by himself, prayed thus: 'God, I thank you that I am not like other "
"men, extortioners, unjust, adulterers, or even like this tax collector. I "
"fast twice a week; I give tithes of all that I get.' But the tax collector, "
"standing far off, would not even lift up his eyes to heaven, but beat his "
"breast, saying, 'God, be merciful to me, a sinner!' I tell you, this man "
"went down to his house justified, rather than the other. For everyone who "
"exalts himself will be humbled, but the one who humbles himself will be "
"exalted.\" Now they were bringing even infants to him that he might touch "
"them. And when the disciples saw it, they rebuked them. But Jesus called "
"them to him, saying, \"Let the children come to me, and do not hinder them, "
"for to such belongs the kingdom of God. Truly, I say to you, whoever does "
"not receive the kingdom of God like a child shall not enter it.\" And a "
"ruler asked him, \"Good Teacher, what must I do to inherit eternal life?\" "
"And Jesus said to him, \"Why do you call me good? No one is good except God "
"alone. You know the commandments: 'Do not commit adultery, Do not murder, Do "
"not steal, Do not bear false witness, Honor your father and mother.' \" And "
"he said, \"All these I have kept from my youth.\" When Jesus heard this, he "
"said to him, \"One thing you still lack. Sell all that you have and "
"distribute to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven; and come, "
"follow me.\" But when he heard these things, he became very sad, for he was "
"extremely rich. Jesus, seeing that he had become sad, said, \"How difficult "
"it is for those who have wealth to enter the kingdom of God! For it is "
"easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich person "
"to enter the kingdom of God.\" Those who heard it said, \"Then who can be "
"saved?\" But he said, \"What is impossible with men is possible with God.\" "
"And Peter said, \"See, we have left our homes and followed you.\" And he "
"said to them, \"Truly, I say to you, there is no one who has left house or "
"wife or brothers or parents or children, for the sake of the kingdom of God, "
"who will not receive many times more in this time, and in the age to come "
"eternal life.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- God exalts the humble and humbles those who exalt themselves. Pray for the "
"poor among this people, those looked down upon because of their lack of "
"education, their family name, or having the \"wrong\" skin color or a "
"disability. Pray they will have an opportunity to hear about the One who "
"exalts the humble, for them to have their story rewritten by the good news "
"of Jesus.\n"
"- This passage also teaches us that God turns impossibilities into "
"possibilities. Nothing is too hard for Him. As we look at the daunting needs "
"of the Muslim world, stir Christian hearts to trust that they are not "
"impossible for God."
msgstr ""
"- Allah meninggikan orang yang rendah hati dan merendahkan orang yang "
"meninggikan diri sendiri. Berdoalah untuk orang-orang miskin di antara umat "
"ini, mereka yang dihina karena kurangnya pendidikan, nama keluarga, atau "
"memiliki warna kulit yang \"salah\" atau cacat. Berdoalah agar mereka "
"memiliki kesempatan untuk mendengar tentang Dia yang meninggikan orang yang "
"rendah hati, agar kisah hidup mereka ditulis ulang oleh kabar baik Yesus.\n"
"- Ayat ini juga mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa Allah mengubah hal-hal yang "
"mustahil menjadi mungkin. Tidak ada yang terlalu sulit bagi-Nya. Saat kita "
"melihat kebutuhan yang menakutkan di dunia Muslim, doronglah hati orang "
"Kristen untuk percaya bahwa hal-hal itu tidak mustahil bagi Allah."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches how prone humanity is to compare ourselves to one "
"another instead of a Holy God. We think if we are better than some arbitrary "
"standard we set for ourselves, then we'll be accepted by God. Pray for these "
"illusions to be broken and for God to humble those who think their good "
"deeds will somehow make them acceptable to a holy and perfect God on their "
"own merits.\n"
"\n"
"The rich ruler illustrates this reality. He had a checklist of laws he "
"believed he was keeping, yet he still sensed something was missing. Jesus "
"went after his heart and exposed what he was truly worshipping.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims to feel like something is still lacking no matter how "
"well they follow the rules.\n"
"- Pray for Jesus to penetrate their hearts, that they would turn from self-"
"righteousness and to Jesus and His Kingdom."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan betapa mudahnya manusia membandingkan diri kita satu "
"sama lain daripada membandingkan diri kita dengan Allah yang Kudus. Kita "
"berpikir bahwa jika kita lebih baik dari standar sembarangan yang kita "
"tetapkan untuk diri kita sendiri, maka kita akan diterima oleh Allah. "
"Berdoalah agar ilusi-ilusi ini hancur dan agar Allah merendahkan mereka yang "
"berpikir bahwa perbuatan baik mereka akan somehow membuat mereka diterima "
"oleh Allah yang Kudus dan Sempurna atas dasar prestasi mereka sendiri.\n"
"\n"
"Raja kaya ini menggambarkan kenyataan tersebut. Dia memiliki daftar hukum "
"yang dia yakini telah dia patuhi, namun dia tetap merasa ada yang kurang. "
"Yesus menyingkap hati dia dan mengungkapkan apa yang sebenarnya dia sembah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim merasa ada yang kurang meskipun mereka "
"mengikuti aturan dengan baik.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Yesus menembus hati mereka, sehingga mereka berbalik dari "
"keangkuhan diri dan menuju Yesus dan Kerajaan-Nya."

msgid ""
"All who acknowledge God's existence, including Muslims, long for God to show "
"them mercy, while also desiring His judgment to fall on those who have "
"wronged them. Many struggle to recognize the depth of their own sin and, as "
"a result, are taught to evaluate themselves in comparison to others rather "
"than before a holy God. This can lead to standing in judgment over those "
"they perceive to be less worthy of the Lord's grace.\n"
"\n"
"Islam offers no resolution for how God can be perfectly merciful and "
"perfectly just in the way the cross of Christ does. Pray that humility would "
"lead Muslims in this land to seek the words and teachings of Jesus, and that "
"they would come to treasure Him above their own self-earned righteousness."
msgstr ""
"Semua orang yang mengakui keberadaan Allah, termasuk umat Islam, mendambakan "
"agar Allah menunjukkan rahmat-Nya kepada mereka, sambil juga menginginkan "
"agar hukuman-Nya menimpa mereka yang telah menzalimi mereka. Banyak orang "
"kesulitan untuk menyadari kedalaman dosa mereka sendiri, dan sebagai "
"akibatnya, mereka diajarkan untuk menilai diri mereka sendiri dengan "
"membandingkan diri dengan orang lain daripada di hadapan Allah yang suci. "
"Hal ini dapat menyebabkan mereka berdiri sebagai hakim atas mereka yang "
"dianggap kurang layak menerima kasih karunia Tuhan.\n"
"\n"
"Islam tidak menawarkan solusi tentang bagaimana Allah dapat menjadi "
"sepenuhnya pengasih dan sepenuhnya adil sebagaimana yang ditunjukkan oleh "
"salib Kristus. Berdoalah agar kerendahan hati membawa umat Islam di negeri "
"ini untuk mencari kata-kata dan ajaran Yesus, dan agar mereka menghargai-Nya "
"di atas kebenaran diri mereka sendiri yang diperoleh dengan usaha sendiri."

msgid ""
"Amira was an intelligent, educated woman and a devoted Muslim with a "
"successful career. She had much to lose when she heard the good news of "
"Jesus and became aware of His loving pursuit of her. In time, He won her "
"heart, and she counted everything as loss for the sake of knowing Christ "
"(Philippians 3:8). Gaining Jesus became more precious to her than career, "
"family, worldly success, or comfort.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for Amira and for many more like her in this land who have taken Jesus "
"at His word: \"Truly, I say to you, there is no one who has left house or "
"wife or brothers or parents or children, for the sake of the kingdom of God, "
"who will not receive many times more in this time, and in the age to come "
"eternal life.\" (Luke 18:29-30). Pray that they would be strengthened, "
"encouraged, and sustained as they follow Him faithfully."
msgstr ""
"Amira adalah seorang wanita cerdas, berpendidikan, dan Muslim yang taat "
"dengan karier yang sukses. Dia memiliki banyak hal yang bisa hilang ketika "
"dia mendengar kabar baik tentang Yesus dan menyadari bahwa Dia dengan penuh "
"kasih mengejarnya. Seiring waktu, Dia memenangkan hatinya, dan dia "
"menganggap segala sesuatu sebagai kerugian demi mengenal Kristus (Filipi 3:8)"
". Mendapatkan Yesus menjadi lebih berharga baginya daripada karier, "
"keluarga, kesuksesan duniawi, atau kenyamanan.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah untuk Amira dan banyak orang lain seperti dia di negeri ini yang "
"telah menerima Yesus sesuai dengan firman-Nya: \"Sesungguhnya, Aku berkata "
"kepadamu, tidak ada seorang pun yang telah meninggalkan rumah atau istri "
"atau saudara atau orang tua atau anak-anak, demi Kerajaan Allah, yang tidak "
"akan menerima berlipat ganda di zaman ini, dan di zaman yang akan datang "
"hidup yang kekal.\" (Lukas 18:29-30). Berdoalah agar mereka diperkuat, "
"didorong, dan dipertahankan saat mereka mengikuti-Nya dengan setia."

msgid ""
"Lord, we know that all of us were dead in our trespasses and sins. We once "
"walked in those sins, following the course of this world, following the "
"prince of the power of the air, and the spirit that is now at work in the "
"sons of disobedience. We once lived in the passions of our flesh, carrying "
"out the desires of the body and the mind, and were by nature children of "
"wrath, like the rest of mankind.\n"
"\n"
"But we pray in faith that, like us, many Muslims in this land would testify "
"to the reality that You, God, being rich in mercy, because of your great "
"love with which you loved us, even when we were dead in our trespasses, made "
"us alive together with Christ. We pray for many to testify that by grace "
"they have been saved, raised up with Christ, and seated with Him in the "
"heavenly places, so that in the coming ages, You might show the immeasurable "
"riches of Your grace and kindness towards us and them in Christ Jesus.\n"
"\n"
"May there be many this year who would say, \"By grace we have been saved "
"through faith. And this is not our own doing: it is the gift of God, not a "
"result of works, so that we would have no reason to boast.\" (Ephesians "
"2:1-9)"
msgstr ""
"Tuhan, kami tahu bahwa kami semua dahulu mati dalam pelanggaran dan dosa-"
"dosa kami. Kami dahulu hidup dalam dosa-dosa itu, mengikuti jalan dunia ini, "
"mengikuti pangeran kuasa udara, dan roh yang sekarang bekerja di dalam anak-"
"anak ketidaktaatan. Kami dahulu hidup dalam nafsu daging kami, melakukan "
"keinginan tubuh dan pikiran, dan oleh nature kami adalah anak-anak murka, "
"seperti sisa umat manusia.\n"
"\n"
"Tetapi kami berdoa dengan iman bahwa, seperti kami, banyak Muslim di negeri "
"ini akan bersaksi tentang kenyataan bahwa Engkau, Allah, yang kaya dalam "
"belas kasihan, karena kasih-Mu yang besar dengan yang Engkau kasihi kami, "
"bahkan ketika kami mati dalam pelanggaran kami, telah menghidupkan kami "
"bersama dengan Kristus. Kami berdoa agar banyak orang bersaksi bahwa oleh "
"kasih karunia mereka telah diselamatkan, dibangkitkan bersama Kristus, dan "
"didudukkan bersama-Nya di tempat-tempat yang mulia di surga, sehingga pada "
"zaman-zaman yang akan datang, Engkau dapat memperlihatkan kekayaan kasih "
"karunia dan kebaikan-Mu yang tak terukur kepada kami dan mereka dalam "
"Kristus Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"Semoga banyak orang tahun ini yang akan berkata, \"Oleh kasih karunia kami "
"telah diselamatkan melalui iman. Dan ini bukan karena perbuatan kami: ini "
"adalah anugerah Allah, bukan karena perbuatan, sehingga kami tidak memiliki "
"alasan untuk membanggakan diri.\" (Efesus 2:1-9)"

msgid "Day 21: Love God and Love Your Neighbor"
msgstr "Hari ke-21: Kasihilah Allah dan Kasihilah Sesamamu"

msgid ""
"Luke 10:25-37 (ESV)\n"
"And behold, a lawyer stood up to put him to the test, saying, \"Teacher, "
"what shall I do to inherit eternal life?\" He said to him, \"What is written "
"in the Law? How do you read it?\" And he answered, \"You shall love the Lord "
"your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your "
"strength and with all your mind, and your neighbor as yourself.\" And he "
"said to him, \"You have answered correctly; do this, and you will live.\" "
"But he, desiring to justify himself, said to Jesus, \"And who is my neighbor?"
"\" Jesus replied, \"A man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and he "
"fell among robbers, who stripped him and beat him and departed, leaving him "
"half dead. Now by chance a priest was going down that road, and when he saw "
"him he passed by on the other side. So likewise a Levite, when he came to "
"the place and saw him, passed by on the other side. But a Samaritan, as he "
"journeyed, came to where he was, and when he saw him, he had compassion. He "
"went to him and bound up his wounds, pouring on oil and wine. Then he set "
"him on his own animal and brought him to an inn and took care of him. And "
"the next day he took out two denarii and gave them to the innkeeper, saying, "
"'Take care of him, and whatever more you spend, I will repay you when I come "
"back.' Which of these three, do you think, proved to be a neighbor to the "
"man who fell among the robbers?\" He said, \"The one who showed him mercy.\" "
"And Jesus said to him, \"You go, and do likewise.\"\n"
"\n"
"Luke 6:27-31 (ESV)\n"
"\"But I say to you who hear, Love your enemies, do good to those who hate "
"you, bless those who curse you, pray for those who abuse you. To one who "
"strikes you on the cheek, offer the other also, and from one who takes away "
"your cloak do not withhold your tunic either. Give to everyone who begs from "
"you, and from one who takes away your goods do not demand them back. And as "
"you wish that others would do to you, do so to them."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that God is content to let His Word speak for "
"itself. In the New Testament, Jesus is asked 180 direct questions, yet He "
"answers only a handful of them directly. Instead, He often answered through "
"parables.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for multitudes of Muslims in this region to read God's Word and for "
"God to speak to them through it even if they do not have a believer beside "
"them to explain every detail.\n"
"- Pray that obedience to the things they learn would result in strong "
"disciples who listen and obey God's Word."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa Allah rela membiarkan Firman-Nya "
"berbicara sendiri. Dalam Perjanjian Baru, Yesus ditanya 180 pertanyaan "
"langsung, namun Ia hanya menjawab sebagian kecil di antaranya secara "
"langsung. Sebaliknya, Ia sering menjawab melalui perumpamaan.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar banyak orang Muslim di wilayah ini membaca Firman Allah dan "
"agar Allah berbicara kepada mereka melalui Firman-Nya, meskipun mereka tidak "
"memiliki orang percaya di samping mereka untuk menjelaskan setiap detail.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ketaatan terhadap hal-hal yang mereka pelajari menghasilkan "
"murid-murid yang kuat yang mendengarkan dan menaati Firman Allah."

msgid ""
"People are prone to justify their actions. Someone once said humans are the "
"best prosecutors when it comes to accusing those who have wronged us and the "
"best defense attorneys when it comes to defending our own actions. Pray for "
"the lost in this place to recognize that they cannot even live up to the "
"standards they set for others -- much less God's standards. Pray for this "
"awareness and conviction to drive them to seek out a Bible or to talk to a "
"Christian."
msgstr ""
"Manusia cenderung membenarkan tindakan mereka sendiri. Seseorang pernah "
"berkata, manusia adalah jaksa terbaik ketika menuduh orang yang telah "
"menyakiti kita dan pengacara pembela terbaik ketika membela tindakan kita "
"sendiri. Berdoalah agar orang-orang yang tersesat di tempat ini menyadari "
"bahwa mereka bahkan tidak mampu memenuhi standar yang mereka tetapkan untuk "
"orang lain — apalagi standar Allah. Berdoalah agar kesadaran dan keyakinan "
"ini mendorong mereka untuk mencari Alkitab atau berbicara dengan seorang "
"Kristen."

msgid ""
"Rached grew up in a loving family that felt Islam was an important part of "
"their identity but didn't rule every aspect of their lives. They valued "
"education and encouraged Rached to pursue his dreams of becoming an "
"architect. Eventually Rached would grow up to be a nominal Muslim with a "
"worldview that sounded more agnostic than Muslim. When he would meet with a "
"Christian to discuss the Bible, his skepticism would pour out about all "
"religions. Like many nominal Muslims, he prefers to believe that Islam and "
"Christianity are basically the same thing -- some people follow Jesus and "
"some people follow Mohammed. But this passage in Luke 6:27-31 is one Rached, "
"and others like him, can't get around. Islam has no equivalent to \"love "
"your enemies\" and \"do good to those who hate you.\"\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for nominal Muslims in this place to have the opportunity to read the "
"New Testament and to have the capacity to acknowledge the profound "
"differences in the message of the New Testament and the message of the "
"Qur'an.\n"
"- Pray for devout Muslims in this place to ponder what it means to love God "
"with all their heart, soul, strength, and mind and to love their neighbor as "
"themselves. Pray that Muslims would truly seek to love God with their minds "
"-- acknowledging that He created our minds and that we can ask questions and "
"He is more than capable of handling our doubts."
msgstr ""
"Rached dibesarkan dalam keluarga yang penuh kasih sayang, yang menganggap "
"Islam sebagai bagian penting dari identitas mereka namun tidak mengendalikan "
"setiap aspek kehidupan mereka. Mereka menghargai pendidikan dan mendorong "
"Rached untuk mengejar mimpinya menjadi arsitek. Akhirnya, Rached tumbuh "
"menjadi seorang Muslim nominal dengan pandangan dunia yang terdengar lebih "
"agnostik daripada Muslim. Ketika ia bertemu dengan seorang Kristen untuk "
"membahas Alkitab, keraguan-keraguannya tentang semua agama pun mengalir "
"keluar. Seperti banyak Muslim nominal, ia lebih suka percaya bahwa Islam dan "
"Kristen pada dasarnya sama — sebagian orang mengikuti Yesus dan sebagian "
"lain mengikuti Muhammad. Namun, ayat dalam Lukas 6:27-31 adalah sesuatu yang "
"Rached dan orang-orang seperti dia tidak bisa abaikan. Islam tidak memiliki "
"padanan untuk \"cintailah musuhmu\" dan \"berbuat baiklah kepada mereka yang "
"membencimu.\"\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Muslim nominal di tempat ini memiliki kesempatan untuk "
"membaca Perjanjian Baru dan memiliki kemampuan untuk mengakui perbedaan "
"mendasar antara pesan Perjanjian Baru dan pesan Al-Qur'an.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Muslim yang taat di tempat ini merenungkan arti mencintai "
"Allah dengan segenap hati, jiwa, kekuatan, dan pikiran, serta mencintai "
"sesama seperti mencintai diri sendiri. Berdoalah agar Muslim benar-benar "
"berusaha mencintai Allah dengan pikiran mereka — mengakui bahwa Dia "
"menciptakan pikiran kita dan bahwa kita dapat mengajukan pertanyaan, dan Dia "
"lebih dari mampu menangani keraguan kita."

msgid ""
"- Pray for Christians in this area trying to love Muslims and share the "
"Gospel to live like the Good Samaritan. Pray for them to have opportunities "
"to sacrificially love and serve the needs of those who are different from "
"them.\n"
"- Pray that the light of Christians living out Jesus' command to love their "
"enemies, do good to those who hate them, bless those who curse them, and "
"pray for those who hurt them -- would shine as bright as the noonday sun. "
"Pray for the onlooking Muslim neighbors, coworkers, family members, and "
"friends to be impacted. May they ask questions about where the strength "
"comes from to do such countercultural actions."
msgstr ""
"- Berdoalah untuk umat Kristen di daerah ini yang berusaha mencintai umat "
"Muslim dan membagikan Injil agar hidup seperti Samaria yang baik. Berdoalah "
"agar mereka memiliki kesempatan untuk mencintai dan melayani dengan ikhlas "
"kebutuhan mereka yang berbeda dari mereka.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar cahaya orang-orang Kristen yang hidup sesuai perintah Yesus "
"untuk mengasihi musuh mereka, berbuat baik kepada mereka yang membenci "
"mereka, memberkati mereka yang mengutuk mereka, dan berdoa untuk mereka yang "
"menyakiti mereka — akan bersinar seterang matahari tengah hari. Berdoalah "
"agar tetangga Muslim, rekan kerja, anggota keluarga, dan teman-teman yang "
"menyaksikan hal ini terpengaruh. Semoga mereka bertanya-tanya dari mana "
"kekuatan itu berasal untuk melakukan tindakan yang bertentangan dengan "
"budaya."

msgid ""
"Today we will pray Romans 12:9-21 over this land. Ask God to empower "
"Christians from a Muslim background in this place to love one another with "
"brotherly affection and outdo one another in showing honor.\n"
"\n"
"Empower them to rejoice in hope, be patient in tribulation, and be constant "
"in prayer. Give them strength and resources to contribute to the needs of "
"the saints and to practice hospitality.\n"
"\n"
"Strengthen your church to bless those who persecute them, blessing and not "
"cursing. Pray that believers would rejoice with their Muslim neighbors who "
"rejoice at weddings and births. Pray for them to weep with their Muslim "
"neighbors who weep at funerals and times of tragedy.\n"
"\n"
"May Christians in this place live in harmony with one another. May they not "
"be proud, but associate with the lowly. May they repay no one evil for evil, "
"but seek to do what is honorable in the sight of all. And if possible, so "
"far as it depends on them, may they live peaceably with everyone, including "
"family members who persecute them, speak against them, curse them, spit on "
"them, or abuse them. Give them grace to entrust justice to the wrath of "
"God.\n"
"\n"
"And may they find that if their enemy is hungry, they feed him; If he is "
"thirsty, they give him something to drink. We bless believers in this place "
"to not be overcome by evil, but to overcome evil with good."
msgstr ""
"Hari ini kita akan berdoa menggunakan Roma 12:9-21 untuk tanah ini. Mohon "
"kepada Tuhan untuk memberdayakan orang-orang Kristen yang berasal dari latar "
"belakang Muslim di tempat ini agar saling mengasihi dengan kasih "
"persaudaraan dan saling mengungguli dalam menghormati satu sama lain.\n"
"\n"
"Berdayakan mereka untuk bersukacita dalam pengharapan, bersabar dalam "
"penderitaan, dan tetap setia dalam doa. Berikan mereka kekuatan dan sumber "
"daya untuk berkontribusi pada kebutuhan para kudus dan untuk mempraktikkan "
"keramahan.\n"
"\n"
"Kuatkan gereja-Mu untuk memberkati mereka yang menganiaya mereka, memberkati "
"dan bukan mengutuk. Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya bersukacita bersama "
"tetangga Muslim mereka yang bersukacita dalam pernikahan dan kelahiran. "
"Berdoalah agar mereka menangis bersama tetangga Muslim mereka yang menangis "
"dalam pemakaman dan saat-saat tragedi.\n"
"\n"
"Semoga orang-orang Kristen di tempat ini hidup dalam harmoni satu sama lain. "
"Semoga mereka tidak sombong, tetapi bergaul dengan orang-orang yang rendah "
"hati. Semoga mereka tidak membalas kejahatan dengan kejahatan, tetapi "
"berusaha melakukan apa yang mulia di mata semua orang. Dan jika "
"memungkinkan, sejauh tergantung pada mereka, semoga mereka hidup dengan "
"damai dengan semua orang, termasuk anggota keluarga yang menganiaya mereka, "
"menentang mereka, mengutuk mereka, meludahi mereka, atau menyiksa mereka. "
"Berikanlah mereka kasih karunia untuk menyerahkan keadilan kepada murka "
"Allah.\n"
"\n"
"Dan semoga mereka menemukan bahwa jika musuh mereka lapar, mereka memberinya "
"makan; jika ia haus, mereka memberinya minum. Kami memberkati orang-orang "
"percaya di tempat ini agar tidak dikalahkan oleh kejahatan, tetapi "
"mengalahkan kejahatan dengan kebaikan."

msgid "Day 22: God Seeks the Lost"
msgstr "Hari ke-22: Allah Mencari yang Hilang"

msgid ""
"Luke 15:1-32 (ESV)\n"
"Now the tax collectors and sinners were all drawing near to hear him. And "
"the Pharisees and the scribes grumbled, saying, \"This man receives sinners "
"and eats with them.\" So he told them this parable: \"What man of you, "
"having a hundred sheep, if he has lost one of them, does not leave the "
"ninety-nine in the open country, and go after the one that is lost, until he "
"finds it? And when he has found it, he lays it on his shoulders, rejoicing. "
"And when he comes home, he calls together his friends and his neighbors, "
"saying to them, 'Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep that was lost.' "
"Just so, I tell you, there will be more joy in heaven over one sinner who "
"repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who need no repentance. \"Or "
"what woman, having ten silver coins, if she loses one coin, does not light a "
"lamp and sweep the house and seek diligently until she finds it? And when "
"she has found it, she calls together her friends and neighbors, saying, "
"'Rejoice with me, for I have found the coin that I had lost.' Just so, I "
"tell you, there is joy before the angels of God over one sinner who repents."
"\" And he said, \"There was a man who had two sons. And the younger of them "
"said to his father, 'Father, give me the share of property that is coming to "
"me.' And he divided his property between them. Not many days later, the "
"younger son gathered all he had and took a journey into a far country, and "
"there he squandered his property in reckless living. And when he had spent "
"everything, a severe famine arose in that country, and he began to be in "
"need. So he went and hired himself out to one of the citizens of that "
"country, who sent him into his fields to feed pigs. And he was longing to be "
"fed with the pods that the pigs ate, and no one gave him anything. \"But "
"when he came to himself, he said, 'How many of my father's hired servants "
"have more than enough bread, but I perish here with hunger! I will arise and "
"go to my father, and I will say to him, \"Father, I have sinned against "
"heaven and before you. I am no longer worthy to be called your son. Treat me "
"as one of your hired servants.\" ' And he arose and came to his father. But "
"while he was still a long way off, his father saw him and felt compassion, "
"and ran and embraced him and kissed him. And the son said to him, 'Father, I "
"have sinned against heaven and before you. I am no longer worthy to be "
"called your son.' But the father said to his servants, 'Bring quickly the "
"best robe, and put it on him, and put a ring on his hand, and shoes on his "
"feet. And bring the fattened calf and kill it, and let us eat and celebrate. "
"For this my son was dead, and is alive again; he was lost, and is found.'And "
"they began to celebrate. \"Now his older son was in the field, and as he "
"came and drew near to the house, he heard music and dancing. And he called "
"one of the servants and asked what these things meant. And he said to him, "
"'Your brother has come, and your father has killed the fattened calf, "
"because he has received him back safe and sound.' But he was angry and "
"refused to go in. His father came out and entreated him, but he answered his "
"father, 'Look, these many years I have served you, and I never disobeyed "
"your command, yet you never gave me a young goat, that I might celebrate "
"with my friends. But when this son of yours came, who has devoured your "
"property with prostitutes, you killed the fattened calf for him!' And he "
"said to him, 'Son, you are always with me, and all that is mine is yours. It "
"was fitting to celebrate and be glad, for this your brother was dead, and is "
"alive; he was lost, and is found.' \""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Three beautiful pictures of lost things are described in this passage. They "
"reveal how much God rejoices when the lost are returned to Him and the "
"extreme lengths He is willing to go in order to find them.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Christians all over the world to agree with God about this and to "
"follow their Master in going after them, even at great cost, in order to "
"restore them to God. Pray that today will be a day of great rejoicing in "
"heaven over sinners repenting."
msgstr ""
"Tiga gambar indah tentang hal-hal yang hilang dijelaskan dalam bagian ini. "
"Mereka mengungkapkan betapa besar sukacita Allah ketika yang hilang kembali "
"kepada-Nya dan sejauh mana Ia bersedia pergi untuk menemukannya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Kristen di seluruh dunia setuju dengan Allah mengenai "
"hal ini dan mengikuti Tuhan mereka dalam mencari mereka, bahkan dengan biaya "
"yang besar, agar mereka dapat dipulihkan kepada Allah. Berdoalah agar hari "
"ini menjadi hari sukacita besar di surga atas pertobatan para pendosa."

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that there are two lost sons. One son is lost "
"because he rejected relationship with the Father and sinfully wastes his "
"life with reckless living. The other son is lost because he keeps all the "
"rules -- not out of love for the Father, but for what he hopes to gain from "
"him. The world is filled with both kinds of people: those who live in open "
"rebellion like the younger son and those who, like the older son, pursue "
"religious obedience in hopes of earning God's favor.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for both types of sons in this land to repent and to be restored to "
"true relationship with their Heavenly Father."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa ada dua anak yang hilang. Anak "
"pertama hilang karena ia menolak hubungan dengan Bapa dan menghamburkan "
"hidupnya dengan cara yang sembrono dan berdosa. Anak yang lain hilang karena "
"ia mematuhi semua aturan—bukan karena cinta kepada Bapa, tetapi karena apa "
"yang ia harapkan untuk diperoleh dari-Nya. Dunia dipenuhi dengan kedua jenis "
"orang ini: mereka yang hidup dalam pemberontakan terbuka seperti anak bungsu "
"dan mereka yang, seperti anak sulung, mengejar ketaatan agama dengan harapan "
"memperoleh kasih karunia Allah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar kedua jenis anak ini di negeri ini bertobat dan dipulihkan "
"ke dalam hubungan yang sejati dengan Bapa Surgawi mereka."

msgid ""
"Islam does not teach that God is a Father, nor that He gently goes after the "
"lost, picking them up and placing them on His shoulders like the lost sheep "
"described in this passage.\n"
"\n"
"Ines suffered from bipolar disorder and had a difficult relationship with "
"her husband. She had only known threats of God's judgment and punishment, "
"not His gentle love. When she met Christ, she struggled to understand what "
"she was experiencing. She said, \"I feel an overwhelming amount of joy. But "
"you know, I got used to being sad, I didn't even know how to live with joy "
"anymore. I was confused, scared, and I always wanted to cry. Now, I feel so "
"much joy—real joy from my heart. I don't know what it is that made God love "
"me like this. He is present with me all the time, in every moment, in every "
"second. I always feel Him telling me, 'You are safe. Do not be afraid.'\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray for many in this land to experience the same joy described in Luke 15 – "
"the joy of the lost son as the Father runs towards him – this same joy that "
"Ines struggled to put into words."
msgstr ""
"Islam tidak mengajarkan bahwa Allah adalah Bapa, atau bahwa Dia dengan "
"lembut mencari yang hilang, mengangkat mereka, dan menempatkan mereka di "
"pundak-Nya seperti domba yang hilang yang dijelaskan dalam ayat ini.\n"
"\n"
"Ines menderita gangguan bipolar dan memiliki hubungan yang sulit dengan "
"suaminya. Dia hanya mengenal ancaman hukuman dan siksaan Allah, bukan kasih-"
"Nya yang lembut. Ketika dia bertemu dengan Kristus, dia kesulitan memahami "
"apa yang dia alami. Dia berkata, \"Saya merasa begitu bahagia. Tapi kamu "
"tahu, aku terbiasa merasa sedih, aku bahkan tidak tahu lagi bagaimana hidup "
"dengan sukacita. Aku bingung, takut, dan selalu ingin menangis. Sekarang, "
"aku merasa begitu banyak sukacita—sukacita yang sejati dari hatiku. Aku "
"tidak tahu apa yang membuat Allah mencintaiku seperti ini. Dia selalu ada "
"bersamaku, di setiap saat, di setiap detik. Aku selalu merasa Dia berkata "
"padaku, 'Kamu aman. Jangan takut.'\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar banyak orang di negeri ini mengalami sukacita yang sama "
"seperti yang dijelaskan dalam Lukas 15—sukacita anak yang hilang saat Bapa "
"berlari menghampirinya—sukacita yang sama yang Ines kesulitan untuk "
"mengungkapkannya dengan kata-kata."

msgid ""
"- Pray for Christians in this place to have their vision and heart expanded "
"to grasp how deeply God loves the lost Muslims in this area. Pray that their "
"hearts would continue to soften and that they would become more like their "
"Father -- going after the lost sheep, sweeping the house in search for the "
"coin, and running towards lost sons returning home.\n"
"- Pray for their hearts to be cleansed of any \"older brother\" tendencies "
"that would rather see Muslims remain distant than be restored to the Father "
"through repentance. Pray that believers in this land would rejoice and "
"celebrate every time a lost sinner comes home."
msgstr ""
"- Berdoalah agar umat Kristen di tempat ini memiliki visi dan hati yang "
"diperluas untuk memahami betapa dalam kasih Allah terhadap umat Muslim yang "
"hilang di daerah ini. Berdoalah agar hati mereka terus melembut dan mereka "
"menjadi semakin serupa dengan Bapa mereka — mencari domba yang hilang, "
"menyapu rumah untuk mencari koin yang hilang, dan berlari menyambut anak-"
"anak yang hilang yang kembali ke rumah.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar hati mereka dibersihkan dari kecenderungan \"saudara "
"sulung\" yang lebih memilih melihat Muslim tetap jauh daripada dipulihkan "
"kepada Bapa melalui pertobatan. Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya di tanah "
"ini bersukacita dan merayakan setiap kali seorang pendosa yang hilang pulang "
"ke rumah."

msgid ""
"Thank you God, for the way this story points us to our perfect heavenly "
"Father and to our true, noble, and selfless Older Brother.\n"
"\n"
"We pray for many in this land to live as described in Romans 8:12-17, "
"according to the Spirit. \"For all who are led by the Spirit of God are sons "
"of God.\" We ask that You would free people here from the spirit of slavery "
"to fall back into fear, and that they may receive the Spirit of adoption as "
"sons, by whom they would cry, \"Abba! Father.\"\n"
"\n"
"Holy Spirit, please bear witness that many among this people are children of "
"God. And if children, then heirs -- heirs of God and fellow heirs with "
"Christ – provided we suffer with Him in order that we may also be glorified "
"with Him."
msgstr ""
"Terima kasih Tuhan, karena kisah ini menuntun kita kepada Bapa Surgawi yang "
"sempurna dan kepada Saudara Tua kita yang sejati, mulia, dan tanpa pamrih.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa agar banyak orang di negeri ini hidup sesuai dengan yang "
"tertulis dalam Roma 8:12-17, menurut Roh. \"Sebab semua yang dipimpin oleh "
"Roh Allah adalah anak-anak Allah.\" Kami memohon agar Engkau membebaskan "
"orang-orang di sini dari roh perbudakan yang membuat mereka kembali ke dalam "
"ketakutan, dan agar mereka menerima Roh pengangkatan sebagai anak-anak, oleh "
"siapa mereka akan berseru, \"Abba! Bapa.\"\n"
"\n"
"Roh Kudus, tolong bersaksi bahwa banyak di antara orang-orang ini adalah "
"anak-anak Allah. Dan jika anak-anak, maka mereka adalah ahli waris — ahli "
"waris Allah dan ahli waris bersama Kristus — asalkan kita menderita bersama-"
"Nya agar kita juga dimuliakan bersama-Nya."

msgid "Day 23: Different Responses to God"
msgstr "Hari ke-23: Respons yang Berbeda terhadap Allah"

msgid ""
"Matthew 13:1-9 (ESV)\n"
"That same day Jesus went out of the house and sat beside the sea. And great "
"crowds gathered about him, so that he got into a boat and sat down. And the "
"whole crowd stood on the beach. And he told them many things in parables, "
"saying: \"A sower went out to sow. And as he sowed, some seeds fell along "
"the path, and the birds came and devoured them. Other seeds fell on rocky "
"ground, where they did not have much soil, and immediately they sprang up, "
"since they had no depth of soil, but when the sun rose they were scorched. "
"And since they had no root, they withered away. Other seeds fell among "
"thorns, and the thorns grew up and choked them. Other seeds fell on good "
"soil and produced grain, some a hundredfold, some sixty, some thirty. He who "
"has ears, let him hear.\"\n"
"\n"
"Matthew 13:18-23 (ESV)\n"
"\"Hear then the parable of the sower: When anyone hears the word of the "
"kingdom and does not understand it, the evil one comes and snatches away "
"what has been sown in his heart. This is what was sown along the path. As "
"for what was sown on rocky ground, this is the one who hears the word and "
"immediately receives it with joy, yet he has no root in himself, but endures "
"for a while, and when tribulation or persecution arises on account of the "
"word, immediately he falls away. As for what was sown among thorns, this is "
"the one who hears the word, but the cares of the world and the deceitfulness "
"of riches choke the word, and it proves unfruitful. As for what was sown on "
"good soil, this is the one who hears the word and understands it. He indeed "
"bears fruit and yields, in one case a hundredfold, in another sixty, and in "
"another thirty.\"\n"
"\n"
"Matthew 13:44-46 (ESV)\n"
"\"The kingdom of heaven is like treasure hidden in a field, which a man "
"found and covered up. Then in his joy he goes and sells all that he has and "
"buys that field. \"Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a merchant in search "
"of fine pearls, who, on finding one pearl of great value, went and sold all "
"that he had and bought it."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God uses simple, ordinary things that everyone understands – seeds, soil, "
"and planting – to communicate deep truths about His Kingdom.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this land to have opportunities to learn about God's "
"Kingdom in simple, culturally relevant ways.\n"
"- Pray that they would hear this story and examine the condition of their "
"heart.\n"
"- Pray they would desire to have hearts like the fourth type of soil – "
"hearts that not only hear and understand God's Word, but also go on to bear "
"multiplicative fruit."
msgstr ""
"Allah menggunakan hal-hal sederhana dan biasa yang dipahami oleh semua orang "
"– benih, tanah, dan penanaman – untuk menyampaikan kebenaran yang mendalam "
"tentang Kerajaan-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di negeri ini memiliki kesempatan untuk belajar "
"tentang Kerajaan Allah dengan cara yang sederhana dan relevan secara "
"budaya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka mendengarkan kisah ini dan memeriksa kondisi hati "
"mereka.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka menginginkan hati seperti jenis tanah keempat – hati "
"yang tidak hanya mendengarkan dan memahami Firman Allah, tetapi juga "
"menghasilkan buah yang berlipat ganda."

msgid ""
"Human hearts are affected by internal and external factors -- persecution, "
"the cares of the world, greed, concern over what people think, to name just "
"a few.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims to have ears to hear and minds to understand when they "
"encounter the Word of God.\n"
"- Pray for roots to grow deep into HIm so they might be sustained when "
"persecution and tribulation come.\n"
"- Pray for hearts to rightly discern the fleeting pleasures of wealth and "
"comfort and to pursue what will last forever."
msgstr ""
"Hati manusia dipengaruhi oleh faktor internal dan eksternal -- penganiayaan, "
"kekhawatiran dunia, keserakahan, kekhawatiran tentang apa yang dipikirkan "
"orang lain, dan masih banyak lagi.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim memiliki telinga untuk mendengarkan dan pikiran "
"untuk memahami ketika mereka bertemu dengan Firman Allah.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar akar mereka tumbuh dalam-dalam ke dalam-Nya sehingga mereka "
"dapat bertahan ketika penganiayaan dan cobaan datang.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar hati mereka dapat membedakan dengan benar kesenangan "
"sementara dari kekayaan dan kenyamanan, dan mengejar apa yang akan bertahan "
"selamanya."

msgid ""
"Faten was a busy, divorced mother of four young adult and teenaged children. "
"When her teenage daughter began to be curious about Christianity, Faten was "
"open-minded to this interest and not stressed. Over time, her daughter's "
"interest decreased, but Faten herself continued to pursue an understanding "
"of Jesus.\n"
"\n"
"As time passed, when she had opportunities to listen to the Bible, she would "
"begin to fall asleep even while sitting upright – though she had once been "
"alert and engaged. She liked what she heard about Jesus, but the concerns of "
"the world and spiritual oppression she experienced as she tried to move "
"towards the Light weighed heavily on her and dulled her interest.\n"
"\n"
"Father, we don't understand all of Faten's story, but You do. We trust that "
"her story is not finished. For every Muslim seeker in this land, by Your "
"grace, please continue their story. May they be good soil that bears fruit "
"thirty, sixty, and a hundredfold."
msgstr ""
"Faten adalah seorang ibu tunggal yang sibuk dengan empat anak dewasa muda "
"dan remaja. Ketika putrinya yang remaja mulai tertarik pada Kristen, Faten "
"bersikap terbuka terhadap minat tersebut dan tidak merasa tertekan. Seiring "
"waktu, minat putrinya berkurang, tetapi Faten sendiri terus berusaha "
"memahami tentang Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"Seiring berjalannya waktu, ketika ia memiliki kesempatan untuk mendengarkan "
"Alkitab, ia mulai tertidur bahkan saat duduk tegak – meskipun sebelumnya ia "
"selalu waspada dan terlibat. Ia menyukai apa yang didengarnya tentang Yesus, "
"tetapi kekhawatiran dunia dan penindasan rohani yang ia alami saat berusaha "
"mendekati Cahaya memberatkan hatinya dan memudarkan minatnya.\n"
"\n"
"Bapa, kami tidak memahami seluruh kisah Faten, tetapi Engkau mengerti. Kami "
"percaya bahwa kisahnya belum selesai. Bagi setiap pencari Muslim di negeri "
"ini, oleh kasih karunia-Mu, tolong lanjutkan kisah mereka. Semoga mereka "
"menjadi tanah yang subur yang menghasilkan buah tiga puluh, enam puluh, dan "
"seratus kali lipat."

msgid ""
"As Christians live among this people day by day, grow their conviction that "
"the Kingdom of heaven is a treasure and a pearl of great price, worth giving "
"up everything to attain.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this land to see that Christians' true hope is not "
"found in money, family, passports, possessions, or personalities. Their hope "
"is that they found a treasure hidden in a field and in joy they sold all "
"they had to buy the field.\n"
"- Pray that Christians would share this truth in ways that help Muslims "
"understand that this treasure is available to them as well."
msgstr ""
"Sebagai orang Kristen yang hidup di tengah-tengah masyarakat ini setiap "
"hari, semakin tumbuh keyakinan mereka bahwa Kerajaan Surga adalah harta "
"karun dan mutiara yang berharga, yang layak untuk ditukar dengan segala "
"sesuatu demi mendapatkannya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di negeri ini menyadari bahwa harapan sejati "
"orang Kristen tidak terletak pada uang, keluarga, paspor, harta benda, atau "
"kepribadian. Harapan mereka adalah menemukan harta yang tersembunyi di "
"ladang dan dengan sukacita menjual segala yang mereka miliki untuk membeli "
"ladang itu.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang Kristen membagikan kebenaran ini dengan cara yang "
"membantu umat Muslim memahami bahwa harta ini juga tersedia bagi mereka."

msgid ""
"Father, we pray according to Philippians 3:8-14 that you would raise up men "
"and women from this land who can say, \"Whatever gain I had, I count it as "
"loss for the sake of Christ.\" May they count everything as loss because of "
"the surpassing worth of knowing Christ Jesus their Lord.\n"
"\n"
"For His sake would they be able to say they've suffered the loss of all "
"things and count them as rubbish in order that they may gain Christ and be "
"found in Him, not having a righteousness of their own that comes from the "
"law, but that which comes through faith in Christ, the righteousness from "
"God that depends on faith.\n"
"\n"
"We pray that the people of this land would know Christ and the power of His "
"resurrection, share in His sufferings, become like Him in His death, and by "
"any means possible attain the resurrection from the dead.\n"
"\n"
"May God raise up people in this place who would press on to make this their "
"own, because Christ Jesus has made them His own. May they be able to say "
"they forget what lies behind and strain forward to what lies ahead, pressing "
"on toward the goal for the prize of the upward call of God in Christ Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Bapa, kami berdoa sesuai dengan Filipi 3:8-14 agar Engkau mengangkat pria "
"dan wanita dari tanah ini yang dapat berkata, \"Apa pun keuntungan yang "
"pernah aku miliki, aku anggap sebagai kerugian demi Kristus.\" Semoga mereka "
"menganggap segala sesuatu sebagai kerugian karena nilai yang melampaui "
"segala sesuatu dalam mengenal Kristus Yesus, Tuhan mereka.\n"
"\n"
"Demikianlah, demi Dia, mereka dapat berkata bahwa mereka telah menderita "
"kerugian segala sesuatu dan menganggapnya sebagai sampah, agar mereka dapat "
"memperoleh Kristus dan ditemukan di dalam-Nya, bukan memiliki kebenaran "
"sendiri yang berasal dari hukum, tetapi kebenaran yang berasal dari iman "
"kepada Kristus, kebenaran dari Allah yang bergantung pada iman.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa agar orang-orang di negeri ini mengenal Kristus dan kuasa "
"kebangkitan-Nya, turut merasakan penderitaan-Nya, menjadi serupa dengan-Nya "
"dalam kematian-Nya, dan dengan segala cara mungkin mencapai kebangkitan dari "
"kematian.\n"
"\n"
"Semoga Allah mengangkat orang-orang di tempat ini yang akan terus berjuang "
"untuk menjadikan hal ini milik mereka, karena Kristus Yesus telah menjadikan "
"mereka milik-Nya. Semoga mereka dapat berkata bahwa mereka melupakan apa "
"yang ada di belakang dan berjuang menuju apa yang ada di depan, terus "
"berjuang menuju tujuan untuk hadiah panggilan Allah yang mulia dalam Kristus "
"Yesus."

msgid "Day 24: Jesus' Power Over Death"
msgstr "Hari ke-24: Kuasa Yesus atas Kematian"

msgid ""
"John 11:1-44 (ESV)\n"
"Now a certain man was ill, Lazarus of Bethany, the village of Mary and her "
"sister Martha. It was Mary who anointed the Lord with ointment and wiped his "
"feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was ill. So the sisters sent to "
"him, saying, \"Lord, he whom you love is ill.\" But when Jesus heard it he "
"said, \"This illness does not lead to death. It is for the glory of God, so "
"that the Son of God may be glorified through it.\" Now Jesus loved Martha "
"and her sister and Lazarus. So, when he heard that Lazarus was ill, he "
"stayed two days longer in the place where he was. Then after this he said to "
"the disciples, \"Let us go to Judea again.\" The disciples said to him, "
"\"Rabbi, the Jews were just now seeking to stone you, and are you going "
"there again?\" Jesus answered, \"Are there not twelve hours in the day? If "
"anyone walks in the day, he does not stumble, because he sees the light of "
"this world. But if anyone walks in the night, he stumbles, because the light "
"is not in him.\" After saying these things, he said to them, \"Our friend "
"Lazarus has fallen asleep, but I go to awaken him.\" The disciples said to "
"him, \"Lord, if he has fallen asleep, he will recover.\" Now Jesus had "
"spoken of his death, but they thought that he meant taking rest in sleep. "
"Then Jesus told them plainly, \"Lazarus has died, and for your sake I am "
"glad that I was not there, so that you may believe. But let us go to him.\" "
"So Thomas, called the Twin, said to his fellow disciples, \"Let us also go, "
"that we may die with him.\" Now when Jesus came, he found that Lazarus had "
"already been in the tomb four days. Bethany was near Jerusalem, about two "
"miles off, and many of the Jews had come to Martha and Mary to console them "
"concerning their brother. So when Martha heard that Jesus was coming, she "
"went and met him, but Mary remained seated in the house. Martha said to "
"Jesus, \"Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died. But "
"even now I know that whatever you ask from God, God will give you.\" Jesus "
"said to her, \"Your brother will rise again.\" Martha said to him, \"I know "
"that he will rise again in the resurrection on the last day.\" Jesus said to "
"her, \"I am the resurrection and the life. Whoever believes in me, though he "
"die, yet shall he live, and everyone who lives and believes in me shall "
"never die. Do you believe this?\" She said to him, \"Yes, Lord; I believe "
"that you are the Christ, the Son of God, who is coming into the world.\" "
"When she had said this, she went and called her sister Mary, saying in "
"private, \"The Teacher is here and is calling for you.\" And when she heard "
"it, she rose quickly and went to him. Now Jesus had not yet come into the "
"village, but was still in the place where Martha had met him. When the Jews "
"who were with her in the house, consoling her, saw Mary rise quickly and go "
"out, they followed her, supposing that she was going to the tomb to weep "
"there. Now when Mary came to where Jesus was and saw him, she fell at his "
"feet, saying to him, \"Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have "
"died.\" When Jesus saw her weeping, and the Jews who had come with her also "
"weeping, he was deeply moved in his spirit and greatly troubled. And he "
"said, \"Where have you laid him?\" They said to him, \"Lord, come and see.\" "
"Jesus wept. So the Jews said, \"See how he loved him!\" But some of them "
"said, \"Could not he who opened the eyes of the blind man also have kept "
"this man from dying?\" Then Jesus, deeply moved again, came to the tomb. It "
"was a cave, and a stone lay against it. Jesus said, \"Take away the stone.\" "
"Martha, the sister of the dead man, said to him, \"Lord, by this time there "
"will be an odor, for he has been dead four days.\" Jesus said to her, \"Did "
"I not tell you that if you believed you would see the glory of God?\" So "
"they took away the stone. And Jesus lifted up his eyes and said, \"Father, I "
"thank you that you have heard me. I knew that you always hear me, but I said "
"this on account of the people standing around, that they may believe that "
"you sent me.\" When he had said these things, he cried out with a loud "
"voice, \"Lazarus, come out.\" The man who had died came out, his hands and "
"feet bound with linen strips, and his face wrapped with a cloth. Jesus said "
"to them, \"Unbind him, and let him go.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God is deeply moved by human suffering. Even though He knows the end from "
"the beginning, He weeps over the pain His children experience in the "
"temporal loss.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to learn about this compassionate attribute "
"of God. He is not far off, observing His children's suffering from a "
"distance – He is near. Pray that His nearness would bring comfort and "
"healing and ask for hearts that would be drawn into a transforming "
"relationship with Him.\n"
"- Pray for Muslims to discover the truth of Jesus' promise in John 11:25, "
"\"I am the resurrection and the life. Whoever believes in me, though he die, "
"yet shall he live\"."
msgstr ""
"Allah sangat tergerak oleh penderitaan manusia. Meskipun Dia tahu akhir dari "
"awal, Dia menangis atas penderitaan yang dialami anak-anak-Nya dalam "
"kehilangan sementara.  \n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini memahami sifat belas kasihan "
"Allah. Dia tidak jauh, mengamati penderitaan anak-anak-Nya dari kejauhan – "
"Dia dekat. Berdoalah agar kedekatan-Nya membawa penghiburan dan penyembuhan, "
"dan mintalah hati yang ditarik ke dalam hubungan yang mengubah hidup dengan-"
"Nya.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim menemukan kebenaran janji Yesus dalam Yohanes "
"11:25, \"Akulah kebangkitan dan hidup. Barangsiapa percaya kepada-Ku, "
"walaupun ia mati, ia akan hidup.\""

msgid ""
"This passage teaches us that death is crushingly difficult for humanity to "
"accept. Deep down, we know that death is not right and that it is not a part "
"of God's original design.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims mourning the loss of a loved one today to know that grief "
"is meant to be processed, not suppressed.\n"
"- Pray that they would hear and understand that death was never God's design "
"and that He ultimately defeated death at the cross."
msgstr ""
"Ayat ini mengajarkan kepada kita bahwa kematian adalah hal yang sangat sulit "
"diterima oleh manusia. Dalam hati yang paling dalam, kita tahu bahwa "
"kematian bukanlah hal yang benar dan bukanlah bagian dari rancangan asli "
"Allah.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah bagi umat Muslim yang sedang berduka atas kehilangan orang yang "
"dicintai hari ini agar mereka tahu bahwa kesedihan dimaksudkan untuk "
"diproses, bukan ditekan.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka mendengar dan memahami bahwa kematian bukanlah "
"rancangan Allah dan bahwa Dia pada akhirnya mengalahkan kematian di kayu "
"salib."

msgid ""
"Every human knows the breathtaking pain that comes when a loved one dies. "
"Often, grief is compounded by regret over harsh words spoken, evil actions "
"taken, or missed opportunities that can never be recovered. Among Muslims, "
"expressions of grief vary from culture to culture. Some cling robotically to "
"repeated phrases of praise to God, reminding themselves of His mercy. Others "
"express grief through acts they consider righteous, hoping to improve the "
"deceased person's chances in the afterlife.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that this pain and grief would move Muslims in this place to seek "
"deeper and more certain answers.\n"
"- Pray that they would encounter Christians who can share the unshakeable "
"hope and assurance found in Jesus' victory over death. May they find joy in "
"learning that those who belong to Christ will share in His resurrection and "
"will never die again."
msgstr ""
"Setiap manusia tahu rasa sakit yang mengguncang hati ketika orang yang "
"dicintai meninggal dunia. Seringkali, kesedihan diperparah oleh penyesalan "
"atas kata-kata kasar yang diucapkan, perbuatan jahat yang dilakukan, atau "
"kesempatan yang terlewatkan dan tak bisa diulang. Di kalangan Muslim, "
"ungkapan kesedihan bervariasi dari satu budaya ke budaya lain. Beberapa "
"orang secara mekanis mengulang kalimat pujian kepada Allah, mengingatkan "
"diri mereka akan rahmat-Nya. Yang lain mengekspresikan kesedihan melalui "
"perbuatan yang mereka anggap benar, berharap dapat meningkatkan peluang "
"orang yang meninggal di akhirat.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar rasa sakit dan duka ini mendorong umat Muslim di tempat ini "
"untuk mencari jawaban yang lebih dalam dan pasti.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka bertemu dengan orang-orang Kristen yang dapat "
"berbagi harapan dan kepastian yang tak tergoyahkan yang ditemukan dalam "
"kemenangan Yesus atas kematian. Semoga mereka menemukan sukacita dalam "
"mengetahui bahwa mereka yang termasuk dalam Kristus akan berbagi dalam "
"kebangkitan-Nya dan tidak akan mati lagi."

msgid ""
"Rahma became a Christian as a young adult and soon faced intense persecution "
"from her family. Her Bible was confiscated, and her brother beat her. A "
"decade later, when her father was dying, she returned home to be with him. "
"One day, she prayed over him and shared much of the Gospel message in that "
"prayer. Though he drifted in and out of consciousness, he woke long enough "
"to say, \"I've heard this before.\" Rahma later discovered that he had "
"secretly kept her confiscated Bible, read it, and treasured it deeply. "
"Eventually he died.\n"
"\n"
"As the family prepared his body and began the custom Muslim burial rituals, "
"something extraordinary happened: a short time later, he rose and removed "
"the shroud from his own face. In the weeks that followed, Rahma confirmed "
"that her father placed his faith in Jesus.\n"
"\n"
"Like Lazarus, Rahma's father died a second time. Yet, also like Lazarus, "
"because of his union with Christ, he had the sure hope of eternal life. Pray "
"for Christians in this place to boldly share the hope they have in Christ "
"and for their lives to reflect they are not enslaved by the fear of death. "
"They know Christ's victory – and it changed everything, including how they "
"live now."
msgstr ""
"Rahma menjadi seorang Kristen saat masih muda dan segera menghadapi "
"penganiayaan yang intens dari keluarganya. Alkitabnya disita, dan saudaranya "
"memukulinya. Sepuluh tahun kemudian, ketika ayahnya sedang sekarat, ia "
"pulang ke rumah untuk menemaninya. Suatu hari, ia berdoa untuknya dan "
"membagikan banyak pesan Injil dalam doa itu. Meskipun ayahnya masuk dan "
"keluar dari kesadaran, ia terbangun cukup lama untuk berkata, \"Aku pernah "
"mendengar ini sebelumnya.\" Rahma kemudian mengetahui bahwa ayahnya telah "
"menyimpan Alkitabnya yang disita secara rahasia, membacanya, dan "
"menyimpannya dengan penuh kasih sayang. Akhirnya, ia meninggal.\n"
"\n"
"Saat keluarga mempersiapkan jenazahnya dan memulai ritual pemakaman Muslim, "
"sesuatu yang luar biasa terjadi: beberapa saat kemudian, ia bangkit dan "
"melepas kain kafan dari wajahnya sendiri. Dalam beberapa minggu berikutnya, "
"Rahma memastikan bahwa ayahnya telah menaruh imannya pada Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"Seperti Lazarus, ayah Rahma meninggal untuk kedua kalinya. Namun, seperti "
"Lazarus, karena persatuannya dengan Kristus, ia memiliki harapan yang pasti "
"akan kehidupan kekal. Berdoalah agar orang-orang Kristen di tempat ini "
"berani membagikan harapan yang mereka miliki dalam Kristus dan agar hidup "
"mereka mencerminkan bahwa mereka tidak terikat oleh ketakutan akan kematian. "
"Mereka tahu kemenangan Kristus – dan hal itu mengubah segalanya, termasuk "
"cara mereka hidup sekarang."

msgid ""
"Father, we thank you for Jesus, who shared in our flesh and blood so that "
"through death He might destroy the one who has the power of death, that is, "
"the devil, and deliver all those who through fear of death were subject to "
"lifelong slavery. (Hebrews 2:14-15)\n"
"\n"
"Free men and women all over this land from the slavery of the fear of "
"death.\n"
"\n"
"Along with followers of Jesus from all over the world, may many in this "
"place join in singing 'Death is swallowed up in victory. O death, where is "
"your sting?\" Thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord "
"Jesus Christ. Therefore, we pray for brothers and sisters in this place to "
"be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing "
"that in the Lord their labor is not in vain. (1 Corinthians 15:55-58)"
msgstr ""
"Bapa, kami bersyukur kepada-Mu atas Yesus, yang telah mengambil bagian dalam "
"daging dan darah kami, sehingga melalui kematian-Nya Ia dapat menghancurkan "
"dia yang memiliki kuasa atas kematian, yaitu iblis, dan membebaskan semua "
"orang yang karena takut akan kematian telah menjadi budak seumur hidup. "
"(Ibrani 2:14-15)\n"
"\n"
"Bebaskanlah semua pria dan wanita di negeri ini dari perbudakan ketakutan "
"akan kematian.\n"
"\n"
"Bersama dengan pengikut Yesus dari seluruh dunia, semoga banyak orang di "
"tempat ini turut menyanyikan, \"Kematian telah ditelan dalam kemenangan. Hai "
"kematian, di manakah sengatmu?\" Terima kasih kepada Allah, yang memberikan "
"kemenangan kepada kita melalui Tuhan Yesus Kristus. Oleh karena itu, kami "
"berdoa agar saudara-saudari di tempat ini tetap teguh, tidak goyah, selalu "
"berlimpah dalam pekerjaan Tuhan, mengetahui bahwa dalam Tuhan, pekerjaan "
"mereka tidak sia-sia. (1 Korintus 15:55-58)"

msgid "Day 25: Jesus' Humility"
msgstr "Hari ke-25: Kerendahan Hati Yesus"

msgid ""
"John 13:1-17 (ESV)\n"
"Now before the Feast of the Passover, when Jesus knew that his hour had come "
"to depart out of this world to the Father, having loved his own who were in "
"the world, he loved them to the end. During supper, when the devil had "
"already put it into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon's son, to betray him, "
"Jesus, knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that "
"he had come from God and was going back to God, rose from supper. He laid "
"aside his outer garments, and taking a towel, tied it around his waist. Then "
"he poured water into a basin and began to wash the disciples' feet and to "
"wipe them with the towel that was wrapped around him. He came to Simon "
"Peter, who said to him, \"Lord, do you wash my feet?\" Jesus answered him, "
"\"What I am doing you do not understand now, but afterward you will "
"understand.\" Peter said to him, \"You shall never wash my feet.\" Jesus "
"answered him, \"If I do not wash you, you have no share with me.\" Simon "
"Peter said to him, \"Lord, not my feet only but also my hands and my head!\" "
"Jesus said to him, \"The one who has bathed does not need to wash, except "
"for his feet, but is completely clean. And you are clean, but not every one "
"of you.\" For he knew who was to betray him; that was why he said, \"Not all "
"of you are clean.\" When he had washed their feet and put on his outer "
"garments and resumed his place, he said to them, \"Do you understand what I "
"have done to you? You call me Teacher and Lord, and you are right, for so I "
"am. If I then, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you also ought "
"to wash one another's feet. For I have given you an example, that you also "
"should do just as I have done to you. Truly, truly, I say to you, a servant "
"is not greater than his master, nor is a messenger greater than the one who "
"sent him. If you know these things, blessed are you if you do them."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God does things that we only understand later: \"What I am doing you do not "
"understand now, but afterward you will understand.\"\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for the message of the upside-down Kingdom -- where the last are "
"first, the poor are blessed, and the greatest is the servant of all -- to be "
"seen for what it truly is: a message from God, not from man. Islam teaches "
"victory through power and the sword; reward is often associated with "
"authority and earthly pleasure. The way of Jesus is through humility, self-"
"sacrifice, and death.\n"
"- Pray that when God allows pain and suffering in the lives of His children "
"in this place, it will drive them deeper into relationship with Him and grow "
"their trust in Him."
msgstr ""
"Allah melakukan hal-hal yang baru kita pahami kemudian: \"Apa yang Aku "
"lakukan sekarang, kalian belum mengerti, tetapi nanti kalian akan "
"mengerti.\"  \n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar pesan Kerajaan yang terbalik — di mana yang terakhir "
"menjadi yang pertama, orang miskin diberkati, dan yang terbesar adalah "
"pelayan semua orang — dipahami sebagai apa adanya: pesan dari Allah, bukan "
"dari manusia. Islam mengajarkan kemenangan melalui kekuatan dan pedang; "
"imbalan sering dikaitkan dengan kekuasaan dan kenikmatan duniawi. Jalan "
"Yesus adalah melalui kerendahan hati, pengorbanan diri, dan kematian.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar ketika Allah mengizinkan penderitaan dan kesengsaraan dalam "
"hidup anak-anak-Nya di tempat ini, hal itu akan mendorong mereka untuk lebih "
"mendalam dalam hubungan dengan-Nya dan memperkuat kepercayaan mereka kepada-"
"Nya."

msgid ""
"One weakness of humanity is thinking that our judgments are better than "
"God's regarding what is or is not appropriate for either Him or us.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to repent of imposing their expectations of "
"who God should be and what they are entitled to. Instead, may they humbly "
"approach God on His terms and with an open heart.\n"
"- Pray for soft hearts that would let Him shape them into His image, rather "
"than trying to shape Him into their image."
msgstr ""
"Salah satu kelemahan manusia adalah menganggap bahwa penilaian kita lebih "
"baik daripada penilaian Tuhan mengenai apa yang pantas atau tidak pantas "
"bagi-Nya maupun bagi kita.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini bertobat dari memaksakan "
"ekspektasi mereka tentang siapa Tuhan seharusnya dan apa yang mereka anggap "
"berhak mereka dapatkan. Sebaliknya, semoga mereka mendekati Tuhan dengan "
"rendah hati sesuai dengan syarat-syarat-Nya dan dengan hati yang terbuka.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka memiliki hati yang lembut yang membiarkan-Nya "
"membentuk mereka sesuai dengan gambar-Nya, daripada mencoba membentuk-Nya "
"sesuai dengan gambar mereka."

msgid ""
"Islam has no teaching, understanding, or capacity for an image of a God who "
"stoops down to wash the feet of His followers. This teaching is shocking, "
"repulsive, and offensive to them -- just as it was to the Jews of Jesus' "
"day. Jesus persevered with them and continued to reshape their "
"understanding, eventually giving them His Spirit, who could transform them "
"from the inside out to see things the way He does.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to encounter Jesus and for God's grace to "
"enable them to receive this message of humble service."
msgstr ""
"Islam tidak memiliki ajaran, pemahaman, atau kemampuan untuk menggambarkan "
"Tuhan yang merendahkan diri untuk mencuci kaki para pengikut-Nya. Ajaran ini "
"mengejutkan, menjijikkan, dan menyinggung bagi mereka — sama seperti halnya "
"bagi orang Yahudi pada zaman Yesus. Yesus tetap bersabar dengan mereka dan "
"terus membentuk pemahaman mereka, akhirnya memberikan Roh-Nya kepada mereka, "
"yang dapat mengubah mereka dari dalam ke luar untuk melihat segala sesuatu "
"sebagaimana Ia melihatnya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini dapat bertemu dengan Yesus dan "
"agar kasih karunia Allah memampukan mereka untuk menerima pesan pelayanan "
"yang rendah hati ini."

msgid ""
"Two Christian families who stepped away from good government jobs in their "
"home country, chose to serve in a 99% Muslim nation as church planters five "
"years ago. When a coup caused their financial support to drop to nothing, "
"the organization asked them to return home.\n"
"\n"
"Still feeling God's call, they sought to return to the Muslim nation without "
"resources. Once there, they embraced the local lifestyle entirely, working "
"in the gardens and farms just like the local people. This humble example was "
"revolutionary. Traditionally, Muslim women in the community stayed home, but "
"seeing these Christian wives working in the fields inspired other women to "
"join them.\n"
"\n"
"They started Discovery Bible Study (DBS) groups, teaching women about "
"healthy diets and how to support their families by sharing and working the "
"land together. This work brought dignity and joy. The men eventually joined "
"the farm work too. Despite floods sometimes sweeping away everything, the "
"couples remain obedient and courageous, continuing to share the gospel. They "
"are making disciples, baptizing people, and seeing Christ manifested in the "
"community because they truly made themselves of \"no reputation.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray for Christians in this place to model the humility of Christ and that "
"it would be a compelling witness, drawing families to follow Jesus."
msgstr ""
"Dua keluarga Kristen yang meninggalkan pekerjaan pemerintah yang baik di "
"negara asal mereka, memilih untuk melayani sebagai pendiri gereja di negara "
"dengan 99% penduduk Muslim lima tahun lalu. Ketika kudeta menyebabkan "
"dukungan finansial mereka berkurang drastis, organisasi tersebut meminta "
"mereka untuk kembali ke negara asal.\n"
"\n"
"Meskipun demikian, mereka tetap merasa dipanggil oleh Tuhan dan berusaha "
"kembali ke negara Muslim tersebut tanpa sumber daya. Setelah tiba di sana, "
"mereka sepenuhnya menyesuaikan diri dengan gaya hidup lokal, bekerja di "
"kebun dan ladang seperti penduduk setempat. Contoh kerendahan hati ini "
"sangat revolusioner. Secara tradisional, wanita Muslim di komunitas tersebut "
"tinggal di rumah, tetapi melihat istri-istri Kristen bekerja di ladang "
"menginspirasi wanita lain untuk bergabung dengan mereka.  \n"
"\n"
"Mereka memulai kelompok Studi Alkitab Penemuan (DBS), mengajarkan wanita "
"tentang pola makan sehat dan cara mendukung keluarga mereka dengan berbagi "
"dan bekerja bersama di tanah. Pekerjaan ini membawa martabat dan "
"kebahagiaan. Para pria akhirnya juga ikut bekerja di ladang. Meskipun banjir "
"kadang-kadang menghanyutkan segalanya, pasangan-pasangan ini tetap taat dan "
"berani, terus membagikan Injil. Mereka sedang membuat murid, membaptis "
"orang, dan melihat Kristus dinyatakan di komunitas karena mereka benar-benar "
"menjadikan diri mereka \"tidak berarti.\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar orang-orang Kristen di tempat ini meneladani kerendahan hati "
"Kristus dan agar hal itu menjadi kesaksian yang menggerakkan, menarik "
"keluarga-keluarga untuk mengikuti Yesus."

msgid ""
"We intercede for our brothers and sisters in Christ in this place, praying "
"Philippians 2 over them. May they be of the same mind, having the same love. "
"We pray they would do nothing from selfish ambition or conceit, but in "
"humility count others more significant than themselves.\n"
"\n"
"As they look not only to their own interests, but also to the interest of "
"others, may it be a compelling testimony that would make nonbelieving "
"onlookers want to know more about the source of the power to put others "
"first.\n"
"\n"
"We pray our brothers and sisters here would have the mind of Christ, who "
"though He was in the form of God, did not count equality with God a thing to "
"be grasped, but emptied Himself, by taking the form of a servant, being born "
"in the likeness of men."
msgstr ""
"Kami berdoa untuk saudara-saudari kami dalam Kristus di tempat ini, dengan "
"mengutip Filipi 2 bagi mereka. Semoga mereka memiliki pikiran yang sama dan "
"kasih yang sama. Kami berdoa agar mereka tidak melakukan apa pun karena "
"ambisi pribadi atau kesombongan, tetapi dengan kerendahan hati menganggap "
"orang lain lebih penting daripada diri mereka sendiri.\n"
"\n"
"Saat mereka tidak hanya memperhatikan kepentingan mereka sendiri, tetapi "
"juga kepentingan orang lain, semoga hal itu menjadi kesaksian yang "
"menggerakkan hati para penonton yang belum percaya untuk ingin tahu lebih "
"banyak tentang sumber kekuatan yang membuat mereka mendahulukan orang lain.\n"
"\n"
"Kami berdoa agar saudara-saudari kami di sini memiliki pikiran Kristus, yang "
"meskipun Ia berada dalam rupa Allah, tidak menganggap kesetaraan dengan "
"Allah sebagai sesuatu yang harus dipegang erat, tetapi mengosongkan diri-"
"Nya, dengan mengambil rupa seorang hamba, dan dilahirkan dalam rupa manusia."

msgid "Day 26: Passover with the Disciples"
msgstr "Hari ke-26: Perayaan Paskah bersama Para Murid"

msgid ""
"Matthew 26:17-30 (ESV)\n"
"Now on the first day of Unleavened Bread the disciples came to Jesus, "
"saying, \"Where will you have us prepare for you to eat the Passover?\" He "
"said, \"Go into the city to a certain man and say to him, 'The Teacher says, "
"My time is at hand. I will keep the Passover at your house with my "
"disciples.' \" And the disciples did as Jesus had directed them, and they "
"prepared the Passover. When it was evening, he reclined at table with the "
"twelve. And as they were eating, he said, \"Truly, I say to you, one of you "
"will betray me.\" And they were very sorrowful and began to say to him one "
"after another, \"Is it I, Lord?\" He answered, \"He who has dipped his hand "
"in the dish with me will betray me. The Son of Man goes as it is written of "
"him, but woe to that man by whom the Son of Man is betrayed! It would have "
"been better for that man if he had not been born.\" Judas, who would betray "
"him, answered, \"Is it I, Rabbi?\" He said to him, \"You have said so.\" Now "
"as they were eating, Jesus took bread, and after blessing it broke it and "
"gave it to the disciples, and said, \"Take, eat; this is my body.\" And he "
"took a cup, and when he had given thanks he gave it to them, saying, \"Drink "
"of it, all of you, for this is my blood of the covenant, which is poured out "
"for many for the forgiveness of sins. I tell you I will not drink again of "
"this fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new with you in my "
"Father's kingdom.\" And when they had sung a hymn, they went out to the "
"Mount of Olives."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God is writing one unified story. We began tracing this story on Day 1 of "
"this prayer campaign with God speaking creation into being. It continued "
"with the promise about the Seed of the woman on Day 3, Isaac's "
"substitutionary sacrifice on Day 8, and the doorways painted with the lamb's "
"blood on Day 10. All of this builds up to today's passage, the fulfillment "
"of the new covenant that Jesus established.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray today for families and groups of friends who have newly discovered "
"God's Word. Pray that they would have the perseverance and hunger to "
"continue discovering Scripture until they get far enough along to see the "
"beauty of the story fully emerge."
msgstr ""
"Allah sedang menulis satu kisah yang utuh. Kita mulai melacak kisah ini pada "
"Hari ke-1 kampanye doa ini, ketika Allah menciptakan segala sesuatu dengan "
"firman-Nya. Kisah ini berlanjut dengan janji tentang Benih Perempuan pada "
"Hari ke-3, pengorbanan pengganti Ishak pada Hari ke-8, dan pintu-pintu yang "
"diolesi darah domba pada Hari ke-10. Semua ini mengarah pada ayat hari ini, "
"yaitu pemenuhan perjanjian baru yang ditetapkan Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah hari ini untuk keluarga dan kelompok teman yang baru saja "
"menemukan Firman Allah. Berdoalah agar mereka memiliki ketekunan dan "
"kerinduan untuk terus menelusuri Kitab Suci hingga mereka cukup jauh untuk "
"melihat keindahan kisah ini sepenuhnya terungkap."

msgid ""
"All of humanity is capable of betrayal. When Jesus said that one of his "
"followers would betray him, they all became sorrowful and asked one another, "
"\"Is it I?\" Pray for people in this land to have honest self-awareness "
"about their capacity to do evil. Pray that this revelation would drive them "
"to the only one who can forgive them of the evil they have done and give "
"them a new heart -- holy, pure, selfless, and loving."
msgstr ""
"Semua manusia mampu melakukan pengkhianatan. Ketika Yesus berkata bahwa "
"salah satu pengikut-Nya akan mengkhianati-Nya, mereka semua menjadi sedih "
"dan saling bertanya, \"Apakah aku?\" Berdoalah agar orang-orang di negeri "
"ini memiliki kesadaran diri yang jujur tentang kemampuan mereka untuk "
"melakukan kejahatan. Berdoalah agar pengungkapan ini mendorong mereka kepada "
"satu-satunya yang dapat mengampuni mereka atas kejahatan yang telah mereka "
"lakukan dan memberikan mereka hati yang baru — suci, murni, tanpa pamrih, "
"dan penuh kasih."

msgid ""
"Radhia grew up in a conservative Muslim family. She led a normal life, "
"marrying, having children, and being a good neighbor. When she inexplicably "
"lost more than 20 pounds, she went to a doctor to seek answers. She "
"discovered she had a very rare intestinal disorder and that she would need "
"an expensive surgery. She reached out to her family to help her, but found "
"that no one was willing to support her. Confused and feeling abandoned, she "
"reached out to her neighbor who was a Christian. Despite this neighbor "
"having even more difficult financial circumstances than Radhia, by God's "
"grace this Christian was able to help her and walk with her through her "
"overwhelmingly difficult circumstances.\n"
"\n"
"Which of us has not experienced betrayal? Muslims are not an exception. "
"Sadly, they do not know a Lord who knowingly accepted betrayal and continued "
"to love his betrayer until the last moment.\n"
"\n"
"Pray that when Muslims in this place experience human betrayal, they would "
"have an opportunity through Christ and/or His followers to experience "
"undeserved acceptance, love, and forgiveness.\n"
"\n"
"Miraculously, while Radhia awaited surgery she put her trust in Jesus and he "
"healed her. The surgery was canceled and Radhia's family is now trying to "
"understand what happened. Pray for many hearts to be drawn to Christ through "
"this testimony."
msgstr ""
"Radhia dibesarkan dalam keluarga Muslim yang konservatif. Ia menjalani "
"kehidupan yang normal, menikah, memiliki anak, dan menjadi tetangga yang "
"baik. Ketika ia secara tiba-tiba kehilangan lebih dari 20 pon berat "
"badannya, ia pergi ke dokter untuk mencari jawaban. Ia menemukan bahwa ia "
"menderita gangguan usus yang sangat langka dan membutuhkan operasi yang "
"mahal. Ia meminta bantuan keluarganya, tetapi menemukan bahwa tidak ada yang "
"bersedia mendukungnya. Bingung dan merasa ditinggalkan, dia menghubungi "
"tetangganya yang beragama Kristen. Meskipun tetangga tersebut memiliki "
"kondisi keuangan yang lebih sulit daripada Radhia, dengan rahmat Tuhan, "
"orang Kristen itu mampu membantunya dan menemaninya melalui situasi yang "
"sangat sulit.  \n"
"\n"
"Siapakah di antara kita yang belum pernah mengalami pengkhianatan? Muslim "
"bukanlah pengecualian. Sayangnya, mereka tidak mengenal Tuhan yang dengan "
"sengaja menerima pengkhianatan dan terus mencintai pengkhianat-Nya hingga "
"detik terakhir.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar ketika Muslim di tempat ini mengalami pengkhianatan manusia, "
"mereka memiliki kesempatan melalui Kristus dan/atau pengikut-Nya untuk "
"mengalami penerimaan, kasih, dan pengampunan yang tidak pantas mereka "
"dapatkan.\n"
"\n"
"Secara ajaib, sementara Radhia menunggu operasi, ia menaruh kepercayaan pada "
"Yesus dan Ia menyembuhkannya. Operasi dibatalkan, dan keluarga Radhia kini "
"berusaha memahami apa yang terjadi. Berdoalah agar banyak hati ditarik "
"kepada Kristus melalui kesaksian ini."

msgid ""
"- Pray for Christians in this area to receive encouragement and a refocusing "
"of their faith each time they share in the Lord's Supper. Pray that it "
"strengthens their resolve and leads to deeper fellowship with Jesus.\n"
"- Pray for believers living in isolation. Pray that God would raise up "
"believers from among their friends and family, so they would experience the "
"blessing of being a part of Christ's body. Pray that they would be sensitive "
"and obedient to the ways God wants to use them to reach those around them. "
"Pray for fellowship for every Christian. May they have brothers and sisters "
"with whom they can share the Lord's Supper."
msgstr ""
"- Berdoalah agar umat Kristen di daerah ini menerima penguatan dan peneguhan "
"iman setiap kali mereka berpartisipasi dalam Perjamuan Tuhan. Berdoalah agar "
"hal ini memperkuat tekad mereka dan membawa mereka ke dalam persekutuan yang "
"lebih dalam dengan Yesus.\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk orang-orang percaya yang hidup dalam isolasi. Berdoalah "
"agar Allah mengangkat orang-orang percaya dari kalangan teman dan keluarga "
"mereka, sehingga mereka dapat mengalami berkat menjadi bagian dari tubuh "
"Kristus. Berdoalah agar mereka menjadi peka dan taat terhadap cara-cara "
"Allah ingin menggunakan mereka untuk menjangkau orang-orang di sekitar "
"mereka. Berdoalah untuk persekutuan bagi setiap orang Kristen. Semoga mereka "
"memiliki saudara dan saudari dengan siapa mereka dapat berbagi Perjamuan "
"Tuhan."

msgid ""
"On the night Jesus was betrayed, he said, \"This is my body, which is for "
"you. Do this in remembrance of me.\" In the same way also he took the cup, "
"after supper, saying, \"This cup is the new covenant in my blood. Do this, "
"as often as you drink it, in remembrance of me.\" For as often as you eat "
"this bread and drink the cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes."
"\" (1 Corinthians 11:23-26)\n"
"\n"
"Pray that every time brothers and sisters take communion – eating the bread "
"and drinking the cup – they would proclaim the Lord's death. Pray this bold "
"proclamation would lead to multitudes of people in this land becoming "
"followers of Christ who participate in communion. Pray that the practice of "
"taking the Lord's Supper would be an act of spiritual defiance against the "
"spiritual forces that try to say, \"Jesus didn't really die.\" May it be "
"taken with eager expectation for the day we will drink it again with Jesus "
"in His Father's Kingdom."
msgstr ""
"Pada malam Yesus dikhianati, Ia berkata, \"Inilah tubuh-Ku, yang diberikan "
"untuk kamu. Lakukanlah ini sebagai peringatan akan Aku.\" Dengan cara yang "
"sama, Ia mengambil cawan itu setelah makan malam, dan berkata, \"Cawan ini "
"adalah perjanjian baru dalam darah-Ku. Lakukanlah ini, setiap kali kamu "
"meminumnya, sebagai peringatan akan Aku.\" Sebab setiap kali kamu makan roti "
"ini dan minum cawan ini, kamu memberitakan kematian Tuhan sampai Ia "
"datang.\" (1 Korintus 11:23-26)\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar setiap kali saudara-saudari mengambil perjamuan kudus – makan "
"roti dan minum cawan – mereka memberitakan kematian Tuhan. Berdoalah agar "
"pengumuman yang berani ini membawa banyak orang di negeri ini menjadi "
"pengikut Kristus yang ikut serta dalam perjamuan kudus. Berdoalah agar "
"praktik mengambil Perjamuan Tuhan menjadi tindakan perlawanan rohani "
"terhadap kekuatan rohani yang mencoba mengatakan, \"Yesus sebenarnya tidak "
"mati.\" Semoga hal ini dilakukan dengan harapan yang penuh gairah untuk hari "
"ketika kita akan meminumnya lagi bersama Yesus di Kerajaan Bapa-Nya."

msgid "Day 27: Jesus Arrested"
msgstr "Hari ke-27: Yesus Ditangkap"

msgid ""
"Matthew 26:36-56 (ESV)\n"
"Then Jesus went with them to a place called Gethsemane, and he said to his "
"disciples, \"Sit here, while I go over there and pray.\" And taking with him "
"Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, he began to be sorrowful and troubled. "
"Then he said to them, \"My soul is very sorrowful, even to death; remain "
"here, and watch with me.\" And going a little farther he fell on his face "
"and prayed, saying, \"My Father, if it be possible, let this cup pass from "
"me; nevertheless, not as I will, but as you will.\" And he came to the "
"disciples and found them sleeping. And he said to Peter, \"So, could you not "
"watch with me one hour? Watch and pray that you may not enter into "
"temptation. The spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak.\" Again, "
"for the second time, he went away and prayed, \"My Father, if this cannot "
"pass unless I drink it, your will be done.\" And again he came and found "
"them sleeping, for their eyes were heavy. So, leaving them again, he went "
"away and prayed for the third time, saying the same words again. Then he "
"came to the disciples and said to them, \"Sleep and take your rest later on. "
"See, the hour is at hand, and the Son of Man is betrayed into the hands of "
"sinners. Rise, let us be going; see, my betrayer is at hand.\" While he was "
"still speaking, Judas came, one of the twelve, and with him a great crowd "
"with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and the elders of the people. "
"Now the betrayer had given them a sign, saying, \"The one I will kiss is the "
"man; seize him.\" And he came up to Jesus at once and said, \"Greetings, "
"Rabbi!\" And he kissed him. Jesus said to him, \"Friend, do what you came to "
"do.\" Then they came up and laid hands on Jesus and seized him. And behold, "
"one of those who were with Jesus stretched out his hand and drew his sword "
"and struck the servant of the high priest and cut off his ear. Then Jesus "
"said to him, \"Put your sword back into its place. For all who take the "
"sword will perish by the sword. Do you think that I cannot appeal to my "
"Father, and he will at once send me more than twelve legions of angels? But "
"how then should the Scriptures be fulfilled, that it must be so?\" At that "
"hour Jesus said to the crowds, \"Have you come out as against a robber, with "
"swords and clubs to capture me? Day after day I sat in the temple teaching, "
"and you did not seize me. But all this has taken place that the Scriptures "
"of the prophets might be fulfilled.\" Then all the disciples left him and "
"fled."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Jesus was completely capable of stopping his arrest and subsequent "
"crucifixion. He submitted willingly, not because of powerlessness, but "
"because of obedience to His Father's will. Multiple times he prayed \"Not my "
"will, but your will be done.\" Pray for the beauty of Jesus' willing "
"sacrifice to bring many in this land to love and follow Him.\n"
"\n"
"We also learn that Jesus experienced the deepest sorrow known to humanity. "
"He was not stoic or detached from suffering. Pray for those in this land who "
"are in deep grief to know that Jesus experienced even greater sorrow and "
"desires to be with them in their pain."
msgstr ""
"Yesus sepenuhnya mampu menghentikan penangkapan-Nya dan penyaliban-Nya yang "
"akan datang. Ia menyerahkan diri dengan sukarela, bukan karena kelemahan, "
"tetapi karena ketaatan-Nya terhadap kehendak Bapa-Nya. Berulang kali Ia "
"berdoa, \"Bukan kehendak-Ku, tetapi kehendak-Mu yang terjadi.\" Berdoalah "
"agar keindahan pengorbanan sukarela Yesus membawa banyak orang di negeri ini "
"untuk mencintai dan mengikuti-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"Kita juga belajar bahwa Yesus mengalami kesedihan terdalam yang pernah "
"dialami manusia. Ia tidak bersikap stoik atau acuh tak acuh terhadap "
"penderitaan. Berdoalah bagi mereka yang berada dalam kesedihan mendalam di "
"negeri ini agar mereka tahu bahwa Yesus mengalami kesedihan yang lebih besar "
"dan ingin berada bersama mereka dalam penderitaan mereka."

msgid ""
"Humans are weak. Our bodies get tired. Peter was full of zeal and claimed "
"that he was willing to go anywhere with Jesus no matter the cost. Yet, after "
"the Messiah asked him to watch and pray, he could not even keep his eyes "
"open. Pray that this example would convince Muslims in this place that they "
"cannot fast enough, pray enough, give away enough. Pray for this conviction "
"to drive them to Jesus' grace.\n"
"\n"
"None of us has been a friend to Jesus like he has been to us. Pray for many "
"in this land to experience friendship with Jesus, allowing that to transform "
"them into His image more and more each day."
msgstr ""
"Manusia lemah. Tubuh kita mudah lelah. Peter penuh semangat dan mengaku siap "
"mengikuti Yesus ke mana pun, tak peduli berapa pun harganya. Namun, setelah "
"Mesias meminta dia untuk berjaga dan berdoa, dia bahkan tidak bisa menjaga "
"matanya tetap terbuka. Berdoalah agar contoh ini meyakinkan umat Muslim di "
"tempat ini bahwa mereka tidak cukup berpuasa, tidak cukup berdoa, dan tidak "
"cukup memberi. Berdoalah agar keyakinan ini mendorong mereka menuju kasih "
"karunia Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"Tidak ada di antara kita yang menjadi sahabat Yesus seperti Dia telah "
"menjadi sahabat kita. Berdoalah agar banyak orang di negeri ini mengalami "
"persahabatan dengan Yesus, sehingga hal itu dapat mengubah mereka menjadi "
"gambar-Nya semakin hari semakin sempurna."

msgid ""
"There is only one way for us to be rescued from this body of death. God the "
"Son cried out to His Father, \"If there is another way, take this cup from "
"me.\" God the Father did not take it away. Only by drinking this cup of "
"suffering was eternal life made available to all who would believe.\n"
"\n"
"Halima had heard the stories of Jesus. She asked for them to be told to her "
"over and over again. She loved the stories and explained Jesus' power by "
"declaring that He is God. But as her family came to visit and her mother "
"fasted and her father went to prayer times, she could not reconcile the "
"outward \"goodness\" of family members who are Muslim with the gospel that "
"Jesus is the only way. She couldn't bear to believe that God would not "
"overlook their unbelief in Jesus because of their devout sincerity. She was "
"sure that God would see their \"good lives\", forgive them, and grant them "
"eternal life. She began saying her Muslim prayers more devoutly, counting "
"them with beads, fasting twice a week, and was careful to dress modestly. "
"She said, \"It is just clear what is good and what is bad. You can feel it."
"\"\n"
"\n"
"Like many others, Halima believed the lie that we define the way to God – "
"that good and evil are determined by how something feels to us.\n"
"\n"
"How, then, can Christians be certain of eternal life? God himself declares "
"that there is One Way to the Father – through Jesus the Son. Pray for "
"humility and repentance."
msgstr ""
"Hanya ada satu cara bagi kita untuk diselamatkan dari tubuh kematian ini. "
"Anak Allah berdoa kepada Bapa-Nya, \"Jika ada cara lain, ambillah cawan ini "
"dari aku.\" Bapa Allah tidak mengambilnya. Hanya dengan meminum cawan "
"penderitaan inilah hidup kekal menjadi tersedia bagi semua yang percaya.\n"
"\n"
"Halima telah mendengar kisah-kisah tentang Yesus. Dia meminta agar kisah-"
"kisah itu diceritakan kepadanya berulang kali. Dia mencintai kisah-kisah itu "
"dan menjelaskan kuasa Yesus dengan menyatakan bahwa Dia adalah Allah. Namun, "
"ketika keluarganya datang berkunjung dan ibunya berpuasa serta ayahnya pergi "
"ke waktu-waktu doa, dia tidak dapat menyatukan kebaikan luar dari anggota "
"keluarga yang Muslim dengan Injil bahwa Yesus adalah satu-satunya jalan. Dia "
"tidak bisa menerima bahwa Allah tidak akan mengampuni ketidakpercayaan "
"mereka pada Yesus karena kesungguhan mereka yang saleh. Dia yakin bahwa "
"Allah akan melihat \"kehidupan baik\" mereka, mengampuni mereka, dan "
"memberikan kehidupan kekal. Dia mulai berdoa dengan lebih saleh, menghitung "
"doanya dengan manik-manik, berpuasa dua kali seminggu, dan berhati-hati "
"dalam berpakaian sopan. Dia berkata, \"Jelas apa yang baik dan apa yang "
"buruk. Kamu bisa merasakannya.\"\n"
"\n"
"Seperti banyak orang lain, Halima percaya pada kebohongan bahwa kita yang "
"menentukan jalan menuju Allah – bahwa baik dan buruk ditentukan oleh "
"bagaimana sesuatu terasa bagi kita.\n"
"\n"
"Bagaimana, lalu, orang Kristen dapat yakin akan kehidupan kekal? Allah "
"sendiri menyatakan bahwa ada Satu Jalan menuju Bapa – melalui Yesus, Anak-"
"Nya. Berdoalah untuk kerendahan hati dan pertobatan."

msgid ""
"When believers suffer for Christ's sake, their families are often unsure how "
"to pray. If we know that \"blessed are those who are persecuted for "
"righteousness' sake,\" is it right to pray for their release from prison? If "
"God works powerfully even in prison, should we grieve and beg for our family "
"to be reunited?\n"
"\n"
"This passage reassures us that in our anguish, we may cry out to God in "
"holiness, \"If it is possible, take this cup from me.\" At the same time we "
"pray, \"Not our will, God, but Yours be done.\" God advances the gospel. God "
"builds His church. We trust Him even when we cannot see.\n"
"\n"
"Through tears, we cry honestly and desperately to God, trusting the perfect "
"sovereignty of the One who hears and who loves.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Christians in this place who are facing deep sorrows, troubles, "
"and persecution to take comfort in knowing that Jesus sees and understands.\n"
"- The Muslim world still waits for multitudes of Christians who will respond "
"to God's call in obedient action, not merely philosophical agreement. Pray "
"that believers would follow the way of their Master – even when obedience "
"leads through sorrow – to bring the Good News to Muslims."
msgstr ""
"Ketika orang-orang percaya menderita demi Kristus, keluarga mereka sering "
"kali bingung bagaimana berdoa. Jika kita tahu bahwa \"berbahagialah mereka "
"yang dianiaya demi kebenaran,\" apakah benar untuk berdoa agar mereka "
"dibebaskan dari penjara? Jika Allah bekerja dengan kuasa-Nya bahkan di dalam "
"penjara, apakah kita harus bersedih dan memohon agar keluarga kita bersatu "
"kembali?\n"
"\n"
"Ayat ini meyakinkan kita bahwa dalam kesedihan kita, kita dapat berdoa "
"kepada Allah dengan kudus, \"Jika mungkin, ambillah cawan ini dari aku.\" "
"Pada saat yang sama, kita berdoa, \"Bukan kehendak kami, ya Allah, tetapi "
"kehendak-Mu yang terjadi.\" Allah memajukan Injil. Allah membangun Gereja-"
"Nya. Kita percaya kepada-Nya bahkan ketika kita tidak dapat melihat.\n"
"\n"
"Melalui air mata, kita berdoa dengan jujur dan putus asa kepada Allah, "
"mempercayai kedaulatan sempurna dari Dia yang mendengarkan dan yang "
"mengasihi.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah untuk orang-orang Kristen di tempat ini yang menghadapi "
"kesedihan mendalam, kesulitan, dan penganiayaan, agar mereka menemukan "
"penghiburan dalam mengetahui bahwa Yesus melihat dan mengerti.\n"
"- Dunia Muslim masih menanti banyak orang Kristen yang akan menanggapi "
"panggilan Allah dengan tindakan taat, bukan sekadar kesepakatan filosofis. "
"Berdoalah agar orang-orang percaya mengikuti jalan Tuhan mereka – bahkan "
"ketika ketaatan membawa melalui kesedihan – untuk membawa Kabar Baik kepada "
"umat Muslim."

msgid ""
"Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of "
"mercies and God of all comfort, who comforts His people in all their "
"affliction, so that they may comfort others with the same comfort they "
"received from God. As believers in this land share abundantly in Christ's "
"sufferings, may they also share in His comfort. (2 Corinthians 1:3-5)\n"
"\n"
"Pray for people in this place, like Paul, to testify in the midst of "
"crushing hardship: \"This was to make us rely not on ourselves but on God "
"who raises the dead.\" (2 Corinthians 1:9)"
msgstr ""
"Terpujilah Allah dan Bapa Tuhan kita Yesus Kristus, Bapa segala belas "
"kasihan dan Allah segala penghiburan, yang menghibur umat-Nya dalam segala "
"penderitaan mereka, sehingga mereka dapat menghibur orang lain dengan "
"penghiburan yang sama yang mereka terima dari Allah. Sebagai orang-orang "
"percaya di negeri ini yang turut merasakan penderitaan Kristus dengan "
"limpah, semoga mereka juga turut merasakan penghiburan-Nya. (2 Korintus 1:3-"
"5)\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah bagi orang-orang di tempat ini, seperti Paulus, untuk bersaksi di "
"tengah penderitaan yang menghancurkan: \"Hal ini dilakukan agar kita tidak "
"mengandalkan diri sendiri, tetapi mengandalkan Allah yang membangkitkan "
"orang mati.\" (2 Korintus 1:9)"

msgid "Day 28: The Crucifixion"
msgstr "Hari ke-28: Penyaliban"

msgid ""
"Luke 23:32-56 (ESV)\n"
"Two others, who were criminals, were led away to be put to death with him. "
"And when they came to the place that is called The Skull, there they "
"crucified him, and the criminals, one on his right and one on his left. And "
"Jesus said, \"Father, forgive them, for they know not what they do.\" And "
"they cast lots to divide his garments. And the people stood by, watching, "
"but the rulers scoffed at him, saying, \"He saved others; let him save "
"himself, if he is the Christ of God, his Chosen One!\" The soldiers also "
"mocked him, coming up and offering him sour wine and saying, \"If you are "
"the King of the Jews, save yourself!\" There was also an inscription over "
"him, \"This is the King of the Jews.\" One of the criminals who were hanged "
"railed at him, saying, \"Are you not the Christ? Save yourself and us!\" But "
"the other rebuked him, saying, \"Do you not fear God, since you are under "
"the same sentence of condemnation? And we indeed justly, for we are "
"receiving the due reward of our deeds; but this man has done nothing wrong."
"\" And he said, \"Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom.\" And "
"he said to him, \"Truly, I say to you, today you will be with me in Paradise."
"\" It was now about the sixth hour, and there was darkness over the whole "
"land until the ninth hour, while the sun's light failed. And the curtain of "
"the temple was torn in two. Then Jesus, calling out with a loud voice, said, "
"\"Father, into your hands I commit my spirit!\" And having said this he "
"breathed his last. Now when the centurion saw what had taken place, he "
"praised God, saying, \"Certainly this man was innocent!\" And all the crowds "
"that had assembled for this spectacle, when they saw what had taken place, "
"returned home beating their breasts. And all his acquaintances and the women "
"who had followed him from Galilee stood at a distance watching these things. "
"Now there was a man named Joseph, from the Jewish town of Arimathea. He was "
"a member of the council, a good and righteous man, who had not consented to "
"their decision and action; and he was looking for the kingdom of God. This "
"man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus. Then he took it down and "
"wrapped it in a linen shroud and laid him in a tomb cut in stone, where no "
"one had ever yet been laid. It was the day of Preparation, and the Sabbath "
"was beginning. The women who had come with him from Galilee followed and saw "
"the tomb and how his body was laid. Then they returned and prepared spices "
"and ointments. On the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"From the cross, Jesus showed compassion to others' agony and pain while He "
"Himself was suffering unimaginably during His unjust death. He comforted the "
"repentant criminal and forgave those who tortured and ridiculed Him.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for people in this place to have eyes that see the contrast between "
"Jesus' heart attitude and actions and those of political and religious "
"leaders throughout human history. Ask that Jesus' model would not only be "
"respected in this land, but that His actions would be emulated.\n"
"- Pray that Jesus' acts of forgiveness would influence those struggling with "
"shame over the wrong actions they have committed. May they come confidently "
"to Him to receive full pardon for their sins. May the freedom that comes "
"from this forgiveness result in ever-increasing love for Him."
msgstr ""
"Dari salib, Yesus menunjukkan belas kasihan terhadap penderitaan dan "
"kesakitan orang lain, sementara Dia sendiri mengalami penderitaan yang tak "
"terkira selama kematian-Nya yang tidak adil. Dia menghibur penjahat yang "
"bertobat dan mengampuni mereka yang menyiksa dan mengejek-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang di tempat ini memiliki mata yang melihat "
"kontras antara sikap hati dan tindakan Yesus dengan sikap hati dan tindakan "
"para pemimpin politik dan agama sepanjang sejarah manusia. Mohon agar "
"teladan Yesus tidak hanya dihormati di negeri ini, tetapi agar tindakan-Nya "
"diteladani.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar tindakan pengampunan Yesus mempengaruhi mereka yang "
"berjuang dengan rasa malu atas perbuatan salah yang telah mereka lakukan. "
"Semoga mereka datang dengan percaya diri kepada-Nya untuk menerima "
"pengampunan penuh atas dosa-dosa mereka. Semoga kebebasan yang datang dari "
"pengampunan ini menghasilkan cinta yang semakin besar kepada-Nya."

msgid ""
"When humanity sees Jesus' actions and character, some respond in faith, "
"while others respond with rejection and ridicule. Pray for many in this "
"place to be the first, not the latter. May His character and actions, as "
"recorded in the Bible, also be reflected in the lives of His followers, and "
"may they be a testimony to Muslim seekers."
msgstr ""
"Ketika umat manusia melihat perbuatan dan karakter Yesus, sebagian merespons "
"dengan iman, sementara yang lain merespons dengan penolakan dan ejekan. "
"Berdoalah agar banyak orang di tempat ini menjadi yang pertama, bukan yang "
"terakhir. Semoga karakter dan perbuatan-Nya, sebagaimana tercatat dalam "
"Alkitab, juga tercermin dalam kehidupan para pengikut-Nya, dan semoga mereka "
"menjadi kesaksian bagi para pencari kebenaran Muslim."

msgid ""
"Muslims esteem Jesus as a prophet and do not believe God would allow Him to "
"be killed in such a humiliating manner. Despite disputing theories common "
"throughout Islam, the eye accounts and history confirm Jesus' death.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for those reading this story to understand how Jesus' death was "
"essential to God's plan for the salvation of mankind.\n"
"- May His innocence, His submission, and the miracles that accompanied His "
"death confirm for them that Jesus was not just a prophet. He was exactly who "
"He claimed to be: the Son of God."
msgstr ""
"Muslim menghormati Yesus sebagai seorang nabi dan tidak percaya bahwa Allah "
"akan membiarkan Dia dibunuh dengan cara yang begitu menghina. Meskipun ada "
"teori-teori yang diperdebatkan dalam Islam, kesaksian mata dan sejarah "
"membenarkan kematian Yesus.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka yang membaca kisah ini memahami betapa pentingnya "
"kematian Yesus dalam rencana Allah untuk keselamatan umat manusia.\n"
"- Semoga ketidakbersalahan-Nya, ketaatan-Nya, dan mukjizat yang menyertai "
"kematian-Nya meyakinkan mereka bahwa Yesus bukan hanya seorang nabi. Dia "
"adalah tepat seperti yang Dia klaim: Anak Allah."

msgid ""
"Imen is living abroad to make money to send to her family. While in her "
"adopted country she came to Christ through reading Discovery Bible Study "
"(DBS)'s Creation to Christ series from the Bible. She immediately began "
"sharing and leading other Muslims to Christ. Early in her journey she shared "
"with her friend Samar. Initially Samar liked what she was hearing, but soon "
"she became distracted by life's concerns. Sometime later, Imen was studying "
"the Crucifixion story. As she was reading, \"By this time it was about noon, "
"and darkness fell across the whole land…\" she received a text from Samar "
"saying Samar's sister had died. Samar had just moved back to her home "
"country to support her sister's dialysis treatments. Tragically the power "
"went out while her sister was having dialysis and that power outage killed "
"her. In response, Imen said somberly, \"God holds time in his hands. No one "
"knows the time or the hour, or when the darkness will fall. We have to get "
"right with Him.\"\n"
"\n"
"We do not know the end of our days here on earth. Pray that Muslims here "
"would not put off until tomorrow what should be done today. May they have a "
"sense of urgency to seek the Lord, that He might forgive their sins and heal "
"their land."
msgstr ""
"Imen tinggal di luar negeri untuk mencari uang yang akan dikirimkan kepada "
"keluarganya. Selama tinggal di negara tempat ia tinggal, ia mengenal Kristus "
"melalui membaca seri \"Creation to Christ\" dari Discovery Bible Study (DBS) "
"dalam Alkitab. Ia segera mulai berbagi dan membimbing orang-orang Muslim "
"lainnya untuk mengenal Kristus. Pada awal perjalanannya, ia berbagi dengan "
"temannya, Samar. Awalnya Samar menyukai apa yang ia dengar, tetapi segera ia "
"teralihkan oleh kekhawatiran hidup. Beberapa waktu kemudian, Imen sedang "
"mempelajari kisah Penyaliban. Saat ia membaca, \"Pada saat itu sudah hampir "
"tengah hari, dan kegelapan meliputi seluruh negeri…\" ia menerima pesan teks "
"dari Samar yang mengatakan bahwa saudara perempuannya telah meninggal. Samar "
"baru saja pindah kembali ke negara asalnya untuk mendukung perawatan "
"dialisis saudaranya. Sayangnya, listrik padam saat saudaranya sedang "
"menjalani dialisis, dan pemadaman listrik itu menyebabkan kematiannya. "
"Sebagai respons, Imen berkata dengan nada sedih, \"Allah memegang waktu di "
"tangan-Nya. Tidak ada yang tahu waktu atau jamnya, atau kapan kegelapan akan "
"turun. Kita harus berdamai dengan-Nya.\"\n"
"\n"
"Kita tidak tahu akhir hari-hari kita di bumi ini. Berdoalah agar umat Muslim "
"di sini tidak menunda hingga besok apa yang seharusnya dilakukan hari ini. "
"Semoga mereka memiliki rasa urgensi untuk mencari Tuhan, agar Ia mengampuni "
"dosa-dosa mereka dan menyembuhkan tanah mereka."

msgid ""
"Hebrews 13:12-21 points out that Jesus suffered outside the gate in order to "
"sanctify the people through his own blood. May believers in this land go to "
"Him outside the camp and bear the reproach He endured. Help people in this "
"land know that we have no lasting city here on earth, but may they seek the "
"city that is to come. Through Christ may many in this land continually offer "
"up a sacrifice of praise to God, that is the fruit of lips that acknowledge "
"His name.\n"
"\n"
"Believers here should not neglect to do good and to share what they have, "
"most importantly the good news of Jesus, for such sacrifices are pleasing to "
"You, God. Now may the God of peace who brought again from the dead our Lord "
"Jesus, the great Shepherd of the sheep, by the blood of the eternal "
"covenant, equip people here with everything good that they may do His will, "
"working in them that which is pleasing in His sight, through Jesus Christ, "
"to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen"
msgstr ""
"Ibrani 13:12-21 menunjukkan bahwa Yesus menderita di luar gerbang untuk "
"menguduskan umat-Nya melalui darah-Nya sendiri. Semoga orang-orang percaya "
"di negeri ini datang kepada-Nya di luar perkemahan dan menanggung penghinaan "
"yang Ia alami. Bantulah orang-orang di negeri ini untuk mengetahui bahwa "
"kita tidak memiliki kota yang kekal di bumi ini, tetapi semoga mereka "
"mencari kota yang akan datang. Melalui Kristus, semoga banyak orang di "
"negeri ini terus mempersembahkan korban pujian kepada Allah, yaitu buah "
"bibir yang mengakui nama-Nya.\n"
"\n"
"Orang-orang percaya di sini janganlah mengabaikan untuk berbuat baik dan "
"berbagi apa yang mereka miliki, terutama kabar baik tentang Yesus, karena "
"persembahan-persembahan seperti itu berkenan kepada-Mu, Allah. Sekarang "
"kiranya Allah damai sejahtera yang telah membangkitkan kembali dari antara "
"orang mati Tuhan kita Yesus, Gembala Agung domba-domba, oleh darah "
"perjanjian yang kekal, melengkapi orang-orang di sini dengan segala yang "
"baik agar mereka dapat melakukan kehendak-Nya, bekerja di dalam mereka apa "
"yang berkenan di hadapan-Nya, melalui Yesus Kristus, kepada-Nya kemuliaan "
"selamanya. Amin."

msgid "Day 29: The Resurrection"
msgstr "Hari ke-29: Kebangkitan"

msgid ""
"John 20:11-31 (ESV)\n"
"But Mary stood weeping outside the tomb, and as she wept she stooped to look "
"into the tomb. And she saw two angels in white, sitting where the body of "
"Jesus had lain, one at the head and one at the feet. They said to her, "
"\"Woman, why are you weeping?\" She said to them, \"They have taken away my "
"Lord, and I do not know where they have laid him.\" Having said this, she "
"turned around and saw Jesus standing, but she did not know that it was "
"Jesus. Jesus said to her, \"Woman, why are you weeping? Whom are you seeking?"
"\" Supposing him to be the gardener, she said to him, \"Sir, if you have "
"carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away."
"\" Jesus said to her, \"Mary.\" She turned and said to him in Aramaic, "
"\"Rabboni!\" (which means Teacher). Jesus said to her, \"Do not cling to me, "
"for I have not yet ascended to the Father; but go to my brothers and say to "
"them, 'I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.' "
"\" Mary Magdalene went and announced to the disciples, \"I have seen the "
"Lord\"—and that he had said these things to her. On the evening of that day, "
"the first day of the week, the doors being locked where the disciples were "
"for fear of the Jews, Jesus came and stood among them and said to them, "
"\"Peace be with you.\" When he had said this, he showed them his hands and "
"his side. Then the disciples were glad when they saw the Lord. Jesus said to "
"them again, \"Peace be with you. As the Father has sent me, even so I am "
"sending you.\" And when he had said this, he breathed on them and said to "
"them, \"Receive the Holy Spirit. If you forgive the sins of any, they are "
"forgiven them; if you withhold forgiveness from any, it is withheld.\" Now "
"Thomas, one of the Twelve, called the Twin, was not with them when Jesus "
"came. So the other disciples told him, \"We have seen the Lord.\" But he "
"said to them, \"Unless I see in his hands the mark of the nails, and place "
"my finger into the mark of the nails, and place my hand into his side, I "
"will never believe.\" Eight days later, his disciples were inside again, and "
"Thomas was with them. Although the doors were locked, Jesus came and stood "
"among them and said, \"Peace be with you.\" Then he said to Thomas, \"Put "
"your finger here, and see my hands; and put out your hand, and place it in "
"my side. Do not disbelieve, but believe.\" Thomas answered him, \"My Lord "
"and my God!\" Jesus said to him, \"Have you believed because you have seen "
"me? Blessed are those who have not seen and yet have believed.\" Now Jesus "
"did many other signs in the presence of the disciples, which are not written "
"in this book; but these are written so that you may believe that Jesus is "
"the Christ, the Son of God, and that by believing you may have life in his "
"name.\n"
"\n"
"Luke 24:50-52 (ESV)\n"
"Then he led them out as far as Bethany, and lifting up his hands he blessed "
"them. While he blessed them, he parted from them and was carried up into "
"heaven. And they worshiped him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- God raised Jesus from the dead just as He promised. Pray for Muslims in to "
"be counted among those who have not seen and yet have believed in the "
"resurrection of Jesus.\n"
"- Who was the first eye witness of Jesus' resurrection? It was Mary. Her "
"role in this story honors and elevates a woman in a culture where a woman's "
"testimony in court would not have been considered meaningful. Pray for women "
"in this land to be led to faith in Christ through knowing how deeply they "
"are loved and valued by God."
msgstr ""
"- Allah membangkitkan Yesus dari kematian sebagaimana yang dijanjikan-Nya. "
"Berdoalah agar umat Muslim termasuk di antara mereka yang belum melihat "
"namun telah percaya pada kebangkitan Yesus.\n"
"- Siapa saksi mata pertama kebangkitan Yesus? Dia adalah Maria. Peran Maria "
"dalam kisah ini menghormati dan mengangkat derajat seorang wanita dalam "
"budaya di mana kesaksian seorang wanita di pengadilan tidak akan dianggap "
"berarti. Berdoalah agar wanita-wanita di negeri ini dipimpin kepada iman "
"kepada Kristus melalui pemahaman betapa dalam mereka dicintai dan dihargai "
"oleh Allah."

msgid ""
"The response of the disciples in this passage highlights how humanity often "
"reacts in the face of danger. The disciples were locked in a room together "
"out of fear. Jesus came to them and repeatedly said, \"Peace be with you.\" "
"Pray that despite the fear that keeps Muslims from asking questions about "
"their religion and discovering what the Bible says, they would sense the "
"peace of Jesus inviting them to follow Him."
msgstr ""
"Tanggapan para murid dalam bagian ini menyoroti bagaimana manusia sering "
"bereaksi di hadapan bahaya. Para murid terkunci di dalam sebuah ruangan "
"karena ketakutan. Yesus datang kepada mereka dan berulang kali berkata, "
"\"Damai sejahtera bagi kalian.\" Berdoalah agar meskipun ketakutan yang "
"menghalangi umat Muslim untuk bertanya tentang agama mereka dan menemukan "
"apa yang Alkitab katakan, mereka dapat merasakan damai sejahtera Yesus yang "
"mengundang mereka untuk mengikuti-Nya."

msgid ""
"Pray for the purpose of John's book, stated in verses 30 and 31, to be "
"realized among Muslims in this place. \"Now Jesus did many other signs in "
"the presence of the disciples, which are not written in this book; but these "
"are written so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of "
"God, and that by believing you have life in his name.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray for Muslims to have both the opportunity and the desire to read this "
"account and that it would cause them to believe that Jesus is the Christ, "
"the Son of God. Thank God for the many Muslims who come to know Jesus "
"through miracles, but pray for multitudes who have not seen, and yet will "
"still believe."
msgstr ""
"Berdoalah agar tujuan kitab Yohanes, yang dinyatakan dalam ayat 30 dan 31, "
"terwujud di kalangan umat Muslim di tempat ini. \"Yesus melakukan banyak "
"tanda lain di hadapan para murid-Nya, yang tidak tertulis dalam kitab ini; "
"tetapi yang tertulis di sini agar kamu percaya bahwa Yesus adalah Kristus, "
"Anak Allah, dan bahwa dengan percaya kamu memiliki hidup dalam nama-Nya.\"\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar umat Muslim memiliki kesempatan dan keinginan untuk membaca "
"kisah ini, dan agar hal itu membuat mereka percaya bahwa Yesus adalah "
"Kristus, Anak Allah. Bersyukurlah kepada Allah atas banyak umat Muslim yang "
"mengenal Yesus melalui mujizat, tetapi berdoalah untuk banyak orang yang "
"belum melihat, namun tetap akan percaya."

msgid ""
"When Saidia was a little girl she heard the words of Jesus on a radio "
"broadcast. She loved what she heard and so she asked for a Bible to be "
"mailed to her home. Her father received the Bible in the mail. Fearful that "
"she would get in big trouble, she said nothing about where it came from, and "
"her father kept it. Years passed and she continued to be interested in "
"learning about Jesus. When her husband left her for another woman, though, "
"she became desperate for Him. She cried out to Him and He came to her in a "
"dream, filling the room with light. He called her to follow Him. One can "
"imagine Him saying, \"Saidia,\" just as He did to Mary.\n"
"\n"
"Pray for many Muslims in this place to be visited by God and to choose to "
"follow Jesus. Pray they would be like Mary – people who go and announce to "
"their friends, \"I have seen the Lord.\""
msgstr ""
"Ketika Saidia masih kecil, dia mendengar kata-kata Yesus dalam siaran radio. "
"Dia menyukai apa yang didengarnya dan meminta Alkitab dikirim ke rumahnya. "
"Ayahnya menerima Alkitab tersebut melalui pos. Karena takut akan mendapat "
"masalah besar, dia tidak mengatakan dari mana Alkitab itu berasal, dan "
"ayahnya menyimpannya. Tahun-tahun berlalu dan dia terus tertarik untuk "
"belajar tentang Yesus. Namun, ketika suaminya meninggalkannya untuk wanita "
"lain, dia menjadi putus asa dan merindukan-Nya. Dia berdoa kepada-Nya, dan "
"Dia datang kepadanya dalam mimpi, menerangi seluruh ruangan dengan cahaya. "
"Dia memanggilnya untuk mengikuti-Nya. Kita bisa membayangkan Dia berkata, "
"\"Saidia,\" sama seperti yang Dia katakan kepada Maria.\n"
"\n"
"Berdoalah agar banyak Muslim di tempat ini dikunjungi oleh Allah dan memilih "
"untuk mengikuti Yesus. Berdoalah agar mereka menjadi seperti Maria – orang-"
"orang yang pergi dan memberitahukan kepada teman-temannya, \"Aku telah "
"melihat Tuhan.\""

msgid ""
"We pray according to 1 Peter 1:8-9 for our brothers and sisters in this "
"land. Though they have not seen Jesus with their physical eyes, may they "
"love him. Though they do not now see Him, they believe in Him. May they "
"increasingly rejoice with joy that is inexpressible and filled with glory, "
"obtaining the outcome of their faith, the salvation of their souls.\n"
"\n"
"1 Corinthians 15:17, 19 and 22 remind us that if Christ has not been raised, "
"our faith is futile and we remain in our sins. If in Christ we have hope in "
"this life only, we are of all people most to be pitied. But we rejoice in "
"the truth that Christ has been raised from the dead. Strengthen our brothers "
"and sisters here to take hope in this. Capture the hearts of Muslims with "
"the truth of the resurrection, and that in Christ, all shall be made alive."
msgstr ""
"Kami berdoa sesuai dengan 1 Petrus 1:8-9 untuk saudara-saudari kami di "
"negeri ini. Meskipun mereka belum melihat Yesus dengan mata jasmani mereka, "
"semoga mereka mengasihi-Nya. Meskipun mereka sekarang tidak melihat-Nya, "
"mereka percaya kepada-Nya. Semoga mereka semakin bersukacita dengan sukacita "
"yang tak terkatakan dan penuh kemuliaan, memperoleh hasil iman mereka, yaitu "
"keselamatan jiwa-jiwa mereka.\n"
"\n"
"1 Korintus 15:17, 19, dan 22 mengingatkan kita bahwa jika Kristus tidak "
"dibangkitkan, iman kita sia-sia dan kita tetap dalam dosa-dosa kita. Jika "
"dalam Kristus kita hanya memiliki harapan dalam hidup ini, kita adalah orang-"
"orang yang paling patut dikasihani. Tetapi kita bersukacita dalam kebenaran "
"bahwa Kristus telah dibangkitkan dari kematian. Kuatkan saudara-saudari kita "
"di sini untuk mengambil harapan dalam hal ini. Tangkap hati orang-orang "
"Muslim dengan kebenaran kebangkitan, dan bahwa dalam Kristus, semua akan "
"dibangkitkan."

msgid "Day 30: Jesus in Heaven"
msgstr "Hari ke-30: Yesus di Surga"

msgid ""
"Revelation 7:9-17 (ESV)\n"
"After this I looked, and behold, a great multitude that no one could number, "
"from every nation, from all tribes and peoples and languages, standing "
"before the throne and before the Lamb, clothed in white robes, with palm "
"branches in their hands, and crying out with a loud voice, \"Salvation "
"belongs to our God who sits on the throne, and to the Lamb!\" And all the "
"angels were standing around the throne and around the elders and the four "
"living creatures, and they fell on their faces before the throne and "
"worshiped God, saying, \"Amen! Blessing and glory and wisdom and "
"thanksgiving and honor and power and might be to our God forever and ever! "
"Amen.\" Then one of the elders addressed me, saying, \"Who are these, "
"clothed in white robes, and from where have they come?\" I said to him, "
"\"Sir, you know.\" And he said to me, \"These are the ones coming out of the "
"great tribulation. They have washed their robes and made them white in the "
"blood of the Lamb. \"Therefore they are before the throne of God, and serve "
"him day and night in his temple; and he who sits on the throne will shelter "
"them with his presence. They shall hunger no more, neither thirst anymore; "
"the sun shall not strike them, nor any scorching heat. For the Lamb in the "
"midst of the throne will be their shepherd, and he will guide them to "
"springs of living water, and God will wipe away every tear from their eyes.\""
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"God's love is so great that it encompasses multitudes from every tribe, "
"tongue, and nation. One day all believers will be in His presence, "
"delighting in Him without condemnation.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this place to put their faith in Christ and be among "
"them.\n"
"- May Christians from a Muslim background take the Good News of Jesus to "
"other Muslims from neighboring people groups.\n"
"- This passage also teaches that it is right to ascribe blessings, glory, "
"wisdom, thanksgiving, honor, power, and might to God for all eternity, "
"literally. Pray for God to raise up more people in this land who would begin "
"living this reality even now."
msgstr ""
"Kasih Allah begitu besar sehingga mencakup banyak orang dari setiap suku, "
"bahasa, dan bangsa. Suatu hari, semua orang percaya akan berada di hadapan-"
"Nya, bersukacita dalam-Nya tanpa penghukuman.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar orang-orang Muslim di tempat ini menaruh iman mereka pada "
"Kristus dan menjadi bagian dari mereka.\n"
"- Semoga orang-orang Kristen yang berasal dari latar belakang Muslim membawa "
"Kabar Baik tentang Yesus kepada orang-orang Muslim dari kelompok etnis "
"tetangga.\n"
"- Ayat ini juga mengajarkan bahwa adalah benar untuk mengarahkan berkat, "
"kemuliaan, kebijaksanaan, ucapan syukur, kehormatan, kuasa, dan kekuatan "
"kepada Allah untuk selamanya, secara harfiah. Berdoalah agar Allah "
"mengangkat lebih banyak orang di negeri ini yang mulai hidup dalam kenyataan "
"ini bahkan sekarang."

msgid ""
"Human hearts long for completion. We often look to tangible things like "
"money, success, sex, relationships, food, or drink to meet this need. Our "
"satisfaction in these things does not last.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray that Muslims in this place will realize that they will find full "
"satisfaction only in the presence of our Creator. Pray that they will taste "
"this completion through a relationship with Jesus and the indwelling of the "
"Holy Spirit provided for us here and now.\n"
"- May the promise of God dwelling with His people, pictured in this passage, "
"provide hope for the fulfillment of this longing."
msgstr ""
"Hati manusia mendambakan kesempurnaan. Kita sering mencari hal-hal konkret "
"seperti uang, kesuksesan, seks, hubungan, makanan, atau minuman untuk "
"memenuhi kebutuhan ini. Kepuasan kita dalam hal-hal tersebut tidak bertahan "
"lama.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini menyadari bahwa mereka hanya akan "
"menemukan kepuasan sejati dalam kehadiran Pencipta kita. Berdoalah agar "
"mereka merasakan kesempurnaan ini melalui hubungan dengan Yesus dan "
"kehadiran Roh Kudus yang diberikan kepada kita di sini dan sekarang.\n"
"- Semoga janji Allah yang tinggal bersama umat-Nya, yang digambarkan dalam "
"ayat ini, memberikan harapan bagi terpenuhinya kerinduan ini."

msgid ""
"Muslims hope that their good deeds will outweigh their bad deeds. They "
"believe they have an angel on each shoulder recording their actions. This "
"passage shows us that God has a superior plan. His plan is not merely to "
"make those who put their faith in Him have more good than bad. His plan is "
"to make us pure, so that we can be in His holy, perfect presence.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray for Muslims in this place to long for true purity and to seek a way "
"for that to be possible.\n"
"- Pray that they would thirst for the springs of living water and meet a "
"believer who can lead them to the one who promised if you drink of Him you "
"will never thirst again."
msgstr ""
"Muslim berharap bahwa amal baik mereka akan melebihi amal buruk mereka. "
"Mereka percaya bahwa ada malaikat di setiap bahu mereka yang mencatat setiap "
"tindakan mereka. Ayat ini menunjukkan kepada kita bahwa Allah memiliki "
"rencana yang lebih tinggi. Rencana-Nya bukan sekadar membuat mereka yang "
"menaruh iman kepada-Nya memiliki lebih banyak kebaikan daripada keburukan. "
"Rencana-Nya adalah untuk menjadikan kita suci, sehingga kita dapat berada di "
"hadirat-Nya yang suci dan sempurna.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar umat Muslim di tempat ini merindukan kesucian yang sejati "
"dan mencari cara agar hal itu menjadi mungkin.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar mereka merindukan mata air kehidupan dan bertemu dengan "
"seorang percaya yang dapat membawa mereka kepada Dia yang telah berjanji "
"bahwa jika kamu minum dari-Nya, kamu tidak akan pernah haus lagi."

msgid ""
"Sonia grew up in a very poor family. She often went without her basic needs "
"being met. Even more devastating, her need to be unconditionally loved by "
"her mom was unmet. As a result, she made some painful decisions in "
"relationships with men, leading to more disappointment, shame, and "
"rejection. She came to know Jesus, sharing His love with others, but the "
"wounds from her childhood have not yet been fully healed.\n"
"\n"
"- Pray Sonia and every believer in this place will be healed from emotional "
"trauma. Ask that God would meet them in the midst of their hurt and "
"suffering now and that He would guide them to springs of living water on "
"this side of eternity.\n"
"- Pray that He would fill them with assured hope and that He will wipe away "
"every tear from their eyes."
msgstr ""
"Sonia tumbuh dalam keluarga yang sangat miskin. Kebutuhan dasarnya "
"seringkali tidak terpenuhi. Yang lebih menyedihkan, kebutuhannya untuk "
"dicintai tanpa syarat oleh ibunya juga tidak terpenuhi. Akibatnya, ia "
"membuat beberapa keputusan menyakitkan dalam hubungannya dengan pria, yang "
"berujung pada kekecewaan, rasa malu, dan penolakan. Ia mengenal Yesus dan "
"berbagi kasih-Nya dengan orang lain, namun luka-luka dari masa kecilnya "
"belum sepenuhnya sembuh.\n"
"\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Sonia dan setiap orang percaya di tempat ini disembuhkan "
"dari trauma emosional. Mintalah agar Allah menemui mereka di tengah luka dan "
"penderitaan mereka saat ini, dan agar Dia menuntun mereka ke mata air "
"kehidupan di sisi ini dari kekekalan.\n"
"- Berdoalah agar Dia mengisi mereka dengan harapan yang pasti dan agar Dia "
"menghapus setiap air mata dari mata mereka."

msgid ""
"May the Lamb receive the reward of His suffering in this land. May this "
"Ramadan mark a turning point where many would take steps towards Christ -- "
"whether it be reading the Bible, talking to a Christian, or humbly praying "
"to God and simply asking Him to reveal himself to them. We pray for families "
"and groups of friends to gather around the Bible to hear the stories we've "
"prayed through this month.\n"
"\n"
"May the living and active Word of God, sharper than any double-edged sword, "
"penetrate them and make them whole. We pray for those in this land to "
"experience God dwelling with them as described in Revelation 21:3-5. Through "
"Christ may they find hope that He will wipe away every tear from their eyes, "
"and death shall be no more. Neither shall there be mourning, nor crying, nor "
"anymore pain, for the former things have passed away. We ask in faith that "
"those we have prayed for this year would say goodbye to the former things "
"and would walk with the One who says, \"Behold, I am making all things new.\""
msgstr ""
"Semoga Anak Domba menerima upah penderitaan-Nya di negeri ini. Semoga "
"Ramadan ini menjadi titik balik di mana banyak orang mengambil langkah "
"menuju Kristus — entah itu dengan membaca Alkitab, berbicara dengan seorang "
"Kristen, atau berdoa dengan rendah hati kepada Allah dan hanya meminta-Nya "
"untuk menampakkan diri-Nya kepada mereka. Kami berdoa agar keluarga dan "
"kelompok teman-teman berkumpul di sekitar Alkitab untuk mendengarkan kisah-"
"kisah yang telah kami doakan sepanjang bulan ini.\n"
"\n"
"Semoga Firman Allah yang hidup dan aktif, yang lebih tajam dari pedang "
"bermata dua, menembus mereka dan menyembuhkan mereka sepenuhnya. Kami berdoa "
"agar mereka yang berada di negeri ini mengalami Allah tinggal bersama mereka "
"seperti yang dijelaskan dalam Wahyu 21:3-5. Melalui Kristus, semoga mereka "
"menemukan harapan bahwa Ia akan menghapus setiap air mata dari mata mereka, "
"dan maut tidak akan ada lagi. Tidak akan ada lagi tangisan, atau ratapan, "
"atau penderitaan, karena hal-hal yang dahulu telah berlalu. Kami berdoa "
"dengan iman agar mereka yang kami doakan tahun ini akan mengucapkan selamat "
"tinggal pada hal-hal yang telah berlalu dan akan berjalan bersama Dia yang "
"berkata, \"Lihatlah, Aku akan membuat segala sesuatu menjadi baru.\""

msgid ""
"One of the primary ways God is drawing Muslims to Himself is through simple "
"Bible studies that highlight passages of scripture from Creation through the "
"Resurrection. <a href=\"https://waha.app/\">The Waha app</a> contains many "
"story sets that have been translated into dozens of languages. Throughout "
"the 30 days we will pray through these story sets that reveal Jesus, the "
"Word made flesh."
msgstr ""
"Salah satu cara utama Allah menarik umat Muslim kepada-Nya adalah melalui "
"studi Alkitab yang sederhana yang menyoroti ayat-ayat Alkitab dari "
"Penciptaan hingga Kebangkitan. <a href=\"https://waha.app/\"> Aplikasi Waha "
"</a> berisi banyak kumpulan cerita yang telah diterjemahkan ke dalam puluhan "
"bahasa. Selama 30 hari ke depan, kita akan berdoa melalui kumpulan cerita "
"ini yang mengungkapkan Yesus, Firman yang menjadi daging."

msgid ""
"As you read these familiar passages, prayerfully imagine what it would be "
"like to read them for the first time – to see the wisdom, power, beauty, and "
"authority of God and to be drawn to trust in Christ and yield your "
"allegiance to Him."
msgstr ""
"Saat Anda membaca ayat-ayat yang sudah familiar ini, bayangkanlah dengan "
"penuh doa bagaimana rasanya membaca ayat-ayat ini untuk pertama kalinya – "
"untuk melihat kebijaksanaan, kuasa, keindahan, dan otoritas Allah, serta "
"untuk tertarik untuk percaya kepada Kristus dan menyerahkan kesetiaan Anda "
"kepada-Nya."

msgid ""
"Pray for your people and place according to what God shows you for today's "
"scripture:"
msgstr ""
"Berdoalah untuk umat dan tempatmu sesuai dengan apa yang Tuhan tunjukkan "
"kepadamu berdasarkan ayat Alkitab hari ini:"

msgid "What this passage teaches us about God"
msgstr "Apa yang diajarkan oleh bagian ini kepada kita tentang Allah"

msgid "What this passage teaches us about humanity"
msgstr "Apa yang diajarkan oleh bagian ini kepada kita tentang kemanusiaan"

msgid "Insight into how this passage connects to Muslims"
msgstr "Pemahaman tentang bagaimana bagian ini terkait dengan umat Islam"

msgid ""
"Insight into how to pray this passage for Christians reaching Muslims in "
"this location"
msgstr ""
"Panduan tentang cara berdoa atas ayat ini bagi umat Kristen yang menjangkau "
"umat Muslim di lokasi ini."

msgid "Related scriptures to pray for this people"
msgstr "Ayat-ayat Alkitab yang berkaitan untuk berdoa bagi umat ini"

msgid ""
"“So whatever you wish that others would do to you, do also to them, for this "
"is the Law and the Prophets. Enter by the narrow gate. For the gate is wide "
"and the way is easy that leads to destruction, and those who enter by it are "
"many. For the gate is narrow and the way is hard that leads to life, and "
"those who find it are few.\" (Matthew 7:12-14) ESV"
msgstr ""
"\"Jadi, apa pun yang kamu inginkan orang lain lakukan kepadamu, lakukanlah "
"juga kepada mereka, sebab itulah hukum Taurat dan kitab para nabi. Masuklah "
"melalui pintu yang sempit. Sebab pintu itu lebar dan jalan itu mudah yang "
"menuju kepada kebinasaan, dan banyak orang yang masuk melalui pintu itu. "
"Sebab pintu itu sempit dan jalan itu sulit yang menuju kepada hidup, dan "
"sedikit orang yang menemukannya.\" (Matius 7:12-14) ESV"

msgid ""
"For those praying today who live in this area, take a moment to imagine what "
"it would look like if everyone would do to others what they would have done "
"unto them. Pray for those Kingdom realities to come."
msgstr ""
"Bagi mereka yang berdoa hari ini dan tinggal di daerah ini, luangkan sejenak "
"untuk membayangkan bagaimana jadinya jika setiap orang melakukan kepada "
"orang lain apa yang mereka harapkan dilakukan kepada diri mereka sendiri. "
"Berdoalah agar realitas Kerajaan itu segera terwujud."

msgid ""
"For those praying today who do not live in this area, pray for Christians to "
"bring meals to the sick, give rides to the carless, listen well to those "
"with burdens, visit those in the hospital, and to share with those in need. "
"May the name of Jesus be exalted in these actions."
msgstr ""
"Bagi mereka yang berdoa hari ini dan tidak tinggal di daerah ini, berdoalah "
"agar umat Kristen dapat membawa makanan kepada orang sakit, memberikan "
"tumpangan kepada mereka yang tidak memiliki kendaraan, mendengarkan dengan "
"baik mereka yang sedang mengalami beban, mengunjungi mereka yang di rumah "
"sakit, dan berbagi dengan mereka yang membutuhkan. Semoga nama Yesus "
"dimuliakan melalui tindakan-tindakan ini."

msgid ""
"We pray today for believers who have chosen the hard, narrow way that leads "
"to life. When they are tempted to be jealous of those who get to \"do as "
"they like\" on the easy, wide way, may they stop and remember the cross. "
"Thank you, Jesus, for coming to reveal God and the way of the cross that "
"loves and sacrifices. We pray that believers will deliberately choose to "
"honor others, to forgive, to offer hospitality, and to serve with humility, "
"giving their lives for Jesus' sake, calling others to the narrow way."
msgstr ""
"Kami berdoa hari ini untuk para pengikut Kristus yang telah memilih jalan "
"yang sulit dan sempit yang menuju kehidupan. Ketika mereka tergoda untuk iri "
"pada mereka yang dapat \"berbuat sesuka hati\" di jalan yang mudah dan "
"lebar, semoga mereka berhenti sejenak dan mengingat salib. Terima kasih, "
"Yesus, karena Engkau datang untuk mengungkapkan Allah dan jalan salib yang "
"penuh kasih dan pengorbanan. Kami berdoa agar para pengikut Kristus dengan "
"sengaja memilih untuk menghormati orang lain, mengampuni, memberikan "
"keramahan, dan melayani dengan kerendahan hati, menyerahkan hidup mereka "
"demi Yesus, dan mengajak orang lain ke jalan yang sempit."

msgid ""
"Adil sat in the back of an old church building in the middle of the week, "
"full of questions about Christianity.  It was forbidden for him to come when "
"foreign Christians gathered there for worship, but he came when a small "
"group practiced for choir. Tears streamed down his face, and he said "
"apologetically, \"I feel such peace here. I can't stop crying.\" Then he "
"asked, \"Is it okay for me to choose Jesus and still continue [in this sin "
"that I love]?\" A brother told him that we all come as we are to God, and he "
"is the one who cleanses us, but he tells us to \"Repent, for the kingdom of "
"God is near.\"  Adil wanted life but was unwilling to turn away from the "
"wide way of destruction to the narrow, hard, holy way. Lord, we pray for "
"those who want you but want their old life, too. Please, stir their souls to "
"repent and live."
msgstr ""
"Adil duduk di bagian belakang gedung gereja tua di tengah minggu, penuh "
"dengan pertanyaan tentang Kristen.  Dia dilarang datang saat orang-orang "
"Kristen asing berkumpul di sana untuk beribadah, tetapi dia datang saat "
"sekelompok kecil berlatih untuk paduan suara. Air mata mengalir di wajahnya, "
"dan dia berkata dengan nada minta maaf, \"Aku merasa begitu damai di sini. "
"Saya tidak bisa berhenti menangis.\" Lalu dia bertanya, \"Apakah boleh bagi "
"saya untuk memilih Yesus dan tetap melanjutkan [dosa yang saya cintai "
"ini]?\" Seorang saudara memberitahunya bahwa kita semua datang kepada Allah "
"apa adanya, dan Dia lah yang membersihkan kita, tetapi Dia menyuruh kita "
"untuk \"Bertobatlah, sebab Kerajaan Allah sudah dekat.\"  Adil menginginkan "
"hidup tetapi enggan meninggalkan jalan lebar yang menuju kehancuran untuk "
"beralih ke jalan sempit, sulit, dan suci. Tuhan, kami berdoa untuk mereka "
"yang menginginkan Engkau tetapi juga menginginkan hidup lama mereka. Tolong, "
"gerakkan jiwa mereka untuk bertobat dan hidup."

msgid ""
"Pray that God would give grace to the church in this region to live out "
"Jesus' Golden Rule, “Do to Others”,  teaching with one another. Pray for "
"simple house churches to model this kind of love to each other and those "
"around them. Pray for believers to proactively serve, visit the sick, listen "
"to the wounded, grieve with the hurting, and show compassion to the weak..."
"instead of waiting to be served, visited, or listened to.\n"
"As they do, lead them to people who they could help form new house churches "
"and Bible studies that would replicate such a way of life for God's glory."
msgstr ""
"Berdoalah agar Tuhan memberikan kasih karunia kepada gereja di wilayah ini "
"untuk hidup sesuai dengan Aturan Emas Yesus, “Perbuatlah kepada orang lain”, "
"dengan saling mengajar satu sama lain. Berdoalah agar gereja-gereja rumah "
"yang sederhana dapat menjadi teladan kasih seperti ini bagi sesama dan orang-"
"orang di sekitar mereka. Berdoalah agar para percaya secara proaktif "
"melayani, mengunjungi yang sakit, mendengarkan yang terluka, berdukacita "
"bersama yang menderita, dan menunjukkan belas kasihan kepada yang lemah... "
"daripada menunggu untuk dilayani, dikunjungi, atau didengarkan.\n"
"Saat mereka melakukannya, bimbinglah mereka kepada orang-orang yang dapat "
"mereka bantu untuk membentuk gereja-gereja rumah baru dan studi Alkitab yang "
"akan meniru cara hidup seperti itu untuk kemuliaan Allah."

msgid ""
"Places of Community\n"
"\n"
"Lead Christians in this region to find ways to serve their community and "
"gain creative access to Muslim families around them. Pray that as Christians "
"love Muslims the way they want to be loved, that Muslim families would want "
"to know more about how they are fulfilling 'the Law and the Prophets'.\n"
"Pray for Christians to stand out in their community for their unselfish "
"love. Pray they would find people of peace who would gather family or "
"friends to read the Bible together and learn more about the source of this "
"unselfish love.\n"
"Pray for community leaders to be softened to the Gospel and desire their "
"community to be shaped by Jesus' teachings of love for enemies, serving "
"others, and selflessness."
msgstr ""
"Tempat-tempat Komunitas\n"
"\n"
"Pimpinlah umat Kristen di wilayah ini untuk menemukan cara melayani "
"komunitas mereka dan mendapatkan akses kreatif ke keluarga-keluarga Muslim "
"di sekitar mereka. Berdoalah agar ketika umat Kristen mencintai Muslim "
"dengan cara yang mereka inginkan untuk dicintai, keluarga-keluarga Muslim "
"akan ingin tahu lebih banyak tentang bagaimana mereka memenuhi 'Hukum dan "
"Para Nabi'.\n"
"Berdoalah agar umat Kristen menonjol di komunitas mereka karena kasih mereka "
"yang tanpa pamrih. Berdoalah agar mereka menemukan orang-orang damai yang "
"akan mengumpulkan keluarga atau teman-teman untuk membaca Alkitab bersama "
"dan belajar lebih banyak tentang sumber kasih tanpa pamrih ini.\n"
"Berdoalah agar pemimpin komunitas dilembutkan oleh Injil dan menginginkan "
"komunitas mereka dibentuk oleh ajaran Yesus tentang kasih kepada musuh, "
"melayani orang lain, dan ketidakegoisan."

msgid ""
"Jesus, you are the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father "
"except through you (John 14:6). Tonight, as Muslims break their fast, go to "
"the mosque, and do their prayers, we pray for dissatisfaction to grow in the "
"sufficiency of their righteous acts. Whether through a dream or vision or "
"talking with a Christian, give many Muslims in this area the chance to hear "
"that \"I am the door. If anyone enters by me, he will be saved and will go "
"in and out and find pasture.\" (John 10:9) As they learn more about you, "
"guide them to engage with friends and family so that they can learn about "
"you together."
msgstr ""
"Yesus, Engkaulah jalan, kebenaran, dan hidup. Tidak ada seorang pun yang "
"datang kepada Bapa kecuali melalui Engkau (Yohanes 14:6). Malam ini, saat "
"umat Muslim berbuka puasa, pergi ke masjid, dan melakukan shalat, kami "
"berdoa agar ketidakpuasan tumbuh dalam kecukupan perbuatan baik mereka. Baik "
"melalui mimpi, penglihatan, atau percakapan dengan seorang Kristen, berikan "
"kesempatan kepada banyak umat Muslim di daerah ini untuk mendengar bahwa "
"\"Akulah pintu. Jika ada yang masuk melalui Aku, ia akan diselamatkan dan "
"dapat masuk dan keluar serta menemukan padang rumput.\" (Yohanes 10:9) Saat "
"mereka belajar lebih banyak tentang Engkau, tuntunlah mereka untuk "
"berinteraksi dengan teman dan keluarga sehingga mereka dapat belajar tentang "
"Engkau bersama-sama."

msgid "Pray as the Lord leads you as you read today's verse"
msgstr "Berdoalah sesuai dengan pimpinan Tuhan saat Anda membaca ayat hari ini."

msgid "Praying with insight"
msgstr "Berdoa dengan penuh wawasan"

msgid "For believers"
msgstr "Bagi para pemeluk agama"

msgid "For the lost"
msgstr "Untuk yang hilang"

msgid "For the church"
msgstr "Untuk gereja"

msgid "For areas of influence"
msgstr "Untuk wilayah pengaruh"

msgid "Declaration of the scripture"
msgstr "Pernyataan Kitab Suci"
